title: summer meadow tea
directions: Boil water and sugar 5 minutes.
Pour over tea bags and cover tightly, allowing to stand 1 hour.
Remove tea bags.
Add
the lemonade and orange juice, undiluted.
This mixture can now be frozen until ready to use.
When serving. add 3 quarts of water to 1 quart of concentrate.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Set aside.
Cream butter, sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Alternately add flour mixture and milk to creamed mixture.
Add extracts and beat until well blended.
Spoon into prepared tube pan and bake in preheated oven for 1 1/4 hours or until cake tests done. Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.

title: independent dream cake
directions: Combine cake mix, whipped topping mix (right from envelope), eggs, orange juice and rind in large bowl of electric mixer. Blend until moistened.
Beat at medium speed 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt
pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until cake tester inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.
Drizzle with Orange Sugar Glaze.

title: quick chicken dumplings
directions: Put cream of chicken soup in large saucepan. Add 1 can water; bring to boil, stirring frequently. Cut or tear biscuits into small pieces (4 to 6 per biscuit) and drop into boiling soup. Cook until biscuits are done.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan lined with wax paper.

title: mighty meat loaf
directions: Pour over meat loaf and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: canned okra
directions: Bring salt, vinegar, and water to a boil.
Add okra and bring to a boil.
Boil 4 minutes; pack into jars and seal.
After opening, rinse in cold water and let drain.

title: mama bill's sweet potato pie
directions: Cook peeled potatoes in salted water. Drain. Add butter, sugar, milk and beaten eggs. Put in uncooked pie shell. Bake at 350 degree oven until firm.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Stir in oats.
Combine milk, honey and egg; stir into dry ingredients. Spread mixture into prepared pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack. Wrap in plastic wrap.
Makes one loaf.

title: mixer pie crust
directions: Crumb shortening and dry ingredients with mixer at low speed. When mixed well, add ice water and mix until rolls into ball. Will work up on mixer, but rolls right off.
Keeps well, rolls out easily and can be rehandled.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Chop and tear broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces and put in big bowl.
Cook, drain and break bacon into small pieces; chop red onion.
Add bacon, onion and cheese to veggies and mix together.

title: diabetic asparagus au gratin(calories: 158)
directions: Heat the evaporated milk, using the top part of a double boiler to prevent burning.
Cut the cheese into small pieces and place in the hot milk.
Heat until the cheese melts.

title: best sweet cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 400°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix and beat first 3 ingredients with mixer 5 minutes.
Pour this mixture over crust.
Slice bananas.
Place pineapple on top of bananas.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Chill 1 hour.
Top with nuts or cherries, if desired.

title: chicken and green pea casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pickled beets (sweet)
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil and pour over beets (1 gallon cooked).
Can and seal jars.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Place carrots in casserole. Saute onion in 1 stick oleo.
Pour over carrots. Sprinkle cheese over carrots. Brown bread crumbs in oleo; sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: oatmeal cake (2)
directions: Mix oats and water and let stand while you mix other ingredients.
Cream together shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, flour and vanilla to oats mixture. Bake in greased pan in 375 degree oven.

title: good 'n easy tuna cakes
directions: Set aside 3/4 cup bread crumbs.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Form 8 patties, coating each side with the reserved bread crumbs.
In nonstick pan over medium heat using about 1 tablespoon oil, cook 4 patties for 4 to 5 minutes on each side. Remove from pan and cook remaining 4 patties (you may need to add a little more oil).
Yummy!

title: quick mix cake devil's food cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add shortening and 2/3 cup milk.
Beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Add remaining milk, unbeaten eggs, melted chocolate and food coloring.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 round 8-inch wax paper lined pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fantastic fudge
directions: Melt chocolate over medium heat until thoroughly melted.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Mixture should be smooth.
If using nuts, add at this time.
Pour into foil lined 8 or 9 inch square pan.
Put in ice box to set.
Cut into 1 inch squares and serve.

title: pork tenderloin stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, melt 2 tablespoons oleo.
Add pork, mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Cook until meat is just browned. Stir in flour, bouillon, parsley, thyme and pepper.
Blend in water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Prepare noodles and drain.
Add 2 tablespoons soft oleo. Toss to coat.
Serve hot meat mixture over hot noodles. Refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: freezer pickles(very good sweet pickles)
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar; set aside to cool.
Let next 3 ingredients stand 3 hours, then drain and dry with paper towel. Add celery seed, pour boiled mixture over and mix.
Put in containers to freeze.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Rub split garlic on inside fondue pot.
Add wine; heat until bubbles form.
Do not boil.
Toss grated cheese with cornstarch and seasonings.
Add to hot wine, a handful at a time.
Stir until cheese is smooth.
Add Kirchwasser.
Serve with cubed French bread.
Good bread is important.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Saute beef until all pink is gone.
Drain.
Adjust all seasoning to taste.
Mix all ingredients in a 4-quart pot.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Makes 3-quarts of soup.

title: easy company breakfast
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place bread slices on bottom of pan (cut where necessary to fit).
Beat eggs.
Add milk and remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour over bread.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 1 hour (let stand 5 minutes before serving). Serves 12.

title: veal cutlets continental(with ham)
directions: About 1 hour before serving, sprinkle veal with salt and pepper.
In large skillet over medium-high heat, in 1/4 cup hot butter, quickly cook cutlets, a few at a time, until well browned and tender.
Drain on paper towels.

title: easy spread
directions: Pour sauce over cream cheese and serve with Ritz crackers. Quick, easy and delicious.

title: gourmet casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well.
Saute the celery, onion and mushrooms and add to rice mixture.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle the top with almonds and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mostaccioli with spinach and feta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. Mix in oil, tomatoes, spinach and onions; cook and stir 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Add cheese; cook 1 minute. Servings: 8.

title: tomato-lemon jello
directions: Drain tomatoes and reserve juice; if not 1 cup, add water. Heat to boiling.
Dissolve jello in juice.
Add everything else. Chill until firm.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: (Use more soup if needed so casserole isn't dry.)

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain peas and beans and put in a bowl. Cut up the amount of celery, carrots and onions you want. Mix sugar and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables and marinate overnight.
Refrigerate.
Drain off juice before serving.

title: corn-sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, set aside.
Fry green pepper and onion in 4 tablespoons sausage drippings.
Blend in flour and salt; remove from heat.
Blend in milk, eggs and corn; return to heat, stirring until mixture is heated through.
Pour into casserole.
Cover with biscuit dough.
Cut slits in dough.
Slip sausages through vertically, leaving sausages partially sticking out.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425°.

title: bambinos(children's snack)
directions: Spread crackers with the mixture of tomato paste and seasonings.
Add hot dogs or pepperoni.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Place in ungreased electric frying pan set at 325° for 5 minutes.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order by hand.
Pour into ungreased, unfloured, 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or toothpick test.
Cake is rich and moist.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add molasses and beaten egg. Beat thoroughly. Sift flour with soda, salt and spices. Add to the creamed mixture and blend well. Roll between palms into walnut sized balls; roll in the sugar and squish. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Steam squash and onion until tender.
Drain.
Add eggs and cracker crumbs.
Season to taste.
Add cheese and mix well. Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with butter and additional cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut braid
directions: Mix peanut butter and margarine until well blended.
Punch dough down, divide in half; cut each half into 3 strips (14 x 3-inch).
Spread mixture down center of strips.
Bring edges to center and pinch to seal.
Form 3 strips into braids; seal ends well.
Repeat with other 3 strips.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Cover.
Rise until double in bulk (1 hour).
Bake at 375° about 20 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with confectioners sugar and sprinkle with chopped nuts (peanuts, walnuts or pecans).
Makes 2 braids.

title: apple or peach kuchen
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and coconut.
Pat into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken piquant
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Drain.
In medium saucepan, melt butter and saute mushrooms and onion until golden; blend in flour.
Add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Add chicken, sour cream and paprika; heat through.
Serve over noodles and sprinkle with cheese.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: no-bake fudge cookies
directions: Boil together cocoa, milk, margarine, vanilla and sugar for 5 minutes.
Pour over peanut butter and oats.
Mix and spoon onto waxed paper immediately.
Let harden.

title: stir-fried broccoli
directions: Cut broccoli into sections (bite size).
Stir-fry broccoli and garlic in hot oil about 7 minutes.
Add pepper last 3 minutes. Stir soy sauce mixture and pour over vegetables.
Cook, stirring until it boils.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6. Has 105 calories each.

title: feather weight pancakes
directions: Combine
dry
ingredients and sift together in a mixing bowl. Combine
egg,
milk and shortening and pour all at once into mixing
bowl with dry ingredients.	Mix until thoroughly blended. Pour
a
small
amount
of	batter onto hot, greased skillet or griddle and cook on one side until bubbles form all over
top
of pancake,
then turn pancake over and cook other side.
Makes 6 to 8 medium sized pancakes.

title: popovers
directions: Stir 2 cups flour and dry ingredients together.
Add heated milk and margarine; stir well, then add eggs and mix.
Add approximately 3 cups more flour until sticky.
Cover bowl with Saran Wrap, let rise until at least double.
Drop in hot oil with teaspoons.
(Dough will pop over; but if it doesn't, turn.) Remove from oil when brown, shake in bowl or bag of powdered sugar.

title: canned pumpkin bread(makes a great gift)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, pumpkin and water. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and spices and beat into the pumpkin mixture.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.
Fill clean, greased, wide mouth pint canning jars half full with prepared batter.
Bake open jars about 60 minutes in an oven at 325°.
When done, quickly remove one hot jar, at a time and clean its sealing edge.
Immediately apply and firmly tighten a two piece wide mouth canning lid.
The lid will form a vacuum seal as the jar cools. Jars of cooled bread may be stored with other canned foods or place in freezer.
The bread is safe to eat as long as jars remain vacuum sealed.
Yields 8 wide-mouth pint canning jars.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients (do not drain corn) in a large casserole.
Bake uncovered 1 hour at 325°.
Stir once every 30 minutes of baking.

title: h. p.'s favorite chili
directions: Brown beef in skillet with onion.
When brown, add to other ingredients in a 4-quart saucepan and simmer until all ingredients blend well.
If more soup is desired, add a medium can of V-8 juice.
Simmer at least 2 hours and serve with crackers.

title: sunshine cake(sponge)
directions: Use Loretta Hilton's Chocolate Cake recipe.
Substitute 3/4 cup cocoa for 2 squares chocolate.
Use sweet milk for sour milk. Reduce soda to 1 teaspoon and add 1 teaspoon double-acting baking powder to dry ingredients.

title: mandarin sorbet
directions: Dissolve sugar in water and bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes, remove from heat and allow to cool.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix together cheese and crackers.
Then place half of mixture in bottom of casserole.
Drain asparagus, saving liquid from one can.
Place asparagus in casserole.
Combine soup with saved asparagus juice then pour over top.
Dot with butter or margarine. Top with reserved cheese/cracker mixture.
(If desired place almonds on asparagus before soup and liquid.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana strawberry salad
directions: Blend well and pour into bowl.
Cover with foil and freeze. Remove from freezer 30 minutes prior to serving.

title: cranberry cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Butter a 9-inch spring-form pan and wrap outside in 2 layers of foil.
Melt the butter; toss melted with crumbs.
Press onto bottom of prepared pan.
Put cream cheese and sugar in a food processor and whir until very smooth.
Add add remaining ingredients except cranberry sauce.
Process just until smooth.
Reserve 1/4 cup of the cheese mixture and pour the rest into the spring-form pan.
Combine cranberry sauce and reserved cheesecake mixture in food processor and pulse until blended.
Pour this mixture onto cheesecake in a spiral.
Put a chopstick or skewer into mixture and draw circles along cranberry spiral to form a swirl pattern.
Put spring-form pan in a larger pan.
Fill halfway with warm water to form a water bath.
Bake until a toothpick inserted in center comes out only slightly moist, 1 3/4 to 2 hours.
Turn off heat and let cake cool in oven with door ajar 1 hour.
Remove cake and let cool completely.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix taco mix, sour cream and Philadelphia cream cheese with your mixer.
Pour onto cookie sheet and spread evenly.
Add over the whole top tomatoes, lettuce and cheese.
That's it.
Serve with nacho chips and let them dip it up.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and boil 2 minutes.
When cool and a little set, add pineapple and oranges.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.
This makes a lot.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter and combine with crumbs; pat down with spoon in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften second stick of butter and combine with sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat this mixture 10 minutes and pour over graham cracker crumbs.
Layer sliced bananas over pudding mixture, strawberries and pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with pecans; top with cherries.
Chill overnight.

title: animal repellent for trees and flowers
directions: Blend well and spray on top and bottom of leaves.
Repeat after rain.

title: christmas fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple, grapes, apples and pecans.
Pour boiling water over jello and candy and cook over low heat until all red hots are dissolved.
Remove from stove; add in juice from can of pineapple and enough water mixed with it to equal a cup of liquid.
Mix well with spoon.
Put in refrigerator (in a bowl) until firm.
Mix in jello mixture (after firm) and mix with fruits, then put in serving dish.
Chill until ready.

title: coco-nutty raisin banana muffins
directions: Mix
flour, granulated sugar, baking powder
and
salt. Stir in 1/2 cup almonds, 1 cup coconut and
raisins;
mix
in bananas. Beat egg, milk, 1/4 cup brown sugar
and
tablespoons
butter. Add to flour mixture;
mix
until	moistened. Spoon into 12 greased muffin pans.
Mix
remaining
coconut, 2 tablespoons almonds, 2 tablespoons brown sugar	and
cinnamon; sprinkle evenly over each muffin.
Bake at 375°
for
about 25 minutes,
or until cake tester inserted in
center
comes
out clean.	If muffins brown too quickly, cover
with foil.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: apple butter jam
directions: Mix and cook for 5 minutes, then stir. Cook for 5 minutes more. Pour into jars and put on lids.

title: plum spice cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; beat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients and add to oil mixture.
Last, add plums and chopped nuts.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.
Sift confectioners sugar on top if desired.
Great for the holidays.

title: chicken imperial
directions: Mix bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, curry, paprika, salt and pepper.
Melt butter with garlic, then add lemon juice.
Roll each piece of chicken in bread crumb mixture.
Arrange in baking dish.
Drizzle butter mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with more cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Baste once or twice while cooking.

title: easy chicken
directions: Follow cooking instructions on Shake 'n Bake box.
Combine soup, sour cream and mushrooms.
Pour mixture over chicken for the last 20 minutes.
Great with baked potatoes.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasonings.
Layer in order of recipe.

title: crock-pot casserole
directions: Keep crock-pot on low for 5 hours.
Can add fresh mushrooms or soup.
Serves 3.

title: pork and corn stuffing bake
directions: Combine corn, stuffing, celery and onion.
In 9-inch greased pie plate, spoon stuffing.
Arrange chops on stuffing, pressing lightly.
Combine sugar and mustard.
Spread mixture evenly over chops.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until chops are no longer pink.

title: delicious chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.

title: deer bologna
directions: Mix everything together.
Make into rolls and wrap in plastic wrap.
Put in refrigerator for 3 days.
Bake 1 hour at 350° on rack.

title: yogurt chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter, add paprika and lemon juice.
Dip chicken in the mixture.
Lay in baking dish and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake for 30 minutes, covered.
Mix mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce and sherry.
Spread over chicken and sprinkle with almonds.
Bake, covered, for an additional 30 minutes.
Put chicken aside.
Blend flour and sour cream and stir in pan juices.
Cook over low heat until thick and smooth.
Pour over chicken and serve with rice.

title: chicken supreme
directions: In skillet in 1 tablespoon hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes. Remove and pour off fat in skillet.
Combine soup, milk and pepper. Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover over low heat 5 minutes.
Stir often.
Serve with potatoes or rice.
Serves 4.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain. Transfer to a large bowl.
Add the next 10 ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle with cheese if desired.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: baked sliced potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch buttered baking dish overlapping slices.
Mix butter and oil; brush slices with mixture.
Pour remaining over potatoes.
Sprinkle with garlic, salt and thyme.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cream cheese candies
directions: Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese.
May take this and divide into parts to make different flavors and colors, but remember it is 1 teaspoon flavoring for the whole amount.
Roll marble size ball in granulated sugar.
Press into rubber mold and pop out.
Let dry on waxed paper.
Can leave in ball if you don't have molds.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Add corn meal last. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp and crab au gratin
directions: Melt butter, low heat.
Add flour and stir milk in slowly. Add salt, paprika, Worcestershire and Parmesan cheese.
Cook until thickened.
Add sherry.
In 9 x 14-inch baking dish, place layer of seafood, layer of sauce, layer of cheese.
Repeat layers. Bake until brown, approximately 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: banana coffee cake(my favorite cake)
directions: Cream together first 6 ingredients.
In another bowl mix together next 4 ingredients.
In a third bowl mix together next 3 ingredients. Add flour mixture to first bowl.
Sprinkle nut mixture on bottom of greased bundt pan.
Pour half of cake in pan and sprinkle the other half of nut mixture and cover with the remaining batter.

title: easy ambrosia salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: hamburg green bean casserole
directions: Cook washed, unpeeled potatoes in salted water until done. Drain and cool.
Cook hamburger and drain off grease.
Thick slice cooled potatoes, with or without peels on.
Gently mix all ingredients and place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off pepper tops and remove inner fibers and seeds.
Drop in boiling water; remove from fire and let stand 10 to 12 minutes. Drain.
Brown meat and add taco mix and water.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add rice and mix.
Cut peppers in half and lay in pan. Fill peppers with mixture and bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes. Pour sauce and grated cheese over peppers 10 minutes before serving.

title: indescribably delicious
directions: Crush crackers by hand.
Set 12 to 15 crushed crackers aside. Melt butter and mix into crackers.
Press crackers into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix pudding and 1 1/2 cups of milk together.
Fold softened ice cream into pudding.
Spoon mixture into pan over crackers. Refrigerate for 1 hour (not in freezer).
Spread Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle remaining crackers on top.
Refrigerate.

title: plum pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, granulated sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat in milk and oil until smooth.
Pour into ungreased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Top with plums.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over plums.
Pour boiling water on plums. Bake 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm and, if desired, with sweetened whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings; 410 calories per serving.

title: poor man's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, syrup and margarine.
Stir in oats. Pour into pie shell and bake at 350°.

title: zabaione con le fragale(zabaglione with strawberries)
directions: In the top of a double boiler, whisk the egg yolks with the sugar until frothy.
Stir in the Marsala.
Place over gently simmering water and whisk until mixture is very thick and double in volume.
Remove from heat and while beating, let cool completely.
Beat the egg white until stiff and fold into the zabaglione.

title: citrus celery seed dressing(makes about 2 cups; 16 calories per tablespoon)
directions: In small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over ReaLemon brand; let stand 1 minute.
Over low heat, stir until gelatin dissolves.
In small bowl, combine gelatin mixture and remaining ingredients; refrigerate overnight.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute
onion
and
pepper.
Add
meat and brown.
Drain grease, if using ground beef.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings to taste.
Add
bay
leaves and simmer 1 hour, then remove bay leaves.
Cook lasagna noodles and drain.

title: pickles
directions: Mix spices together; stir until syrupy.
Fill jar with onions and cucumbers in alternate layers.
Pour syrup mixture over slices and refrigerate for 5 days.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine oil and sugar.
Add slightly beaten eggs and blend well.
Stir in flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Beat several times and add to mixture alternately with finely shredded carrots.
Pour batter into 3 lightly greased and floured layer pans.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting. Sprinkle chopped pecans between layers and top.

title: gazebo cheese soup
directions: I use my food processor to quickly chop veggies.

title: fruit deluxe
directions: Heat cherry juice with 1/2 cup juice drained from pears.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Cool until congealing starts. Pour into ring mold and chill until firm.
Unmold on a large plate. Whip the cream gradually adding sugar and vanilla.
Pile in center of ring.
Arrange pears and apricots around ring.
Serves 6.

title: coffee jelly with macaroon cream
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water and sugar. Stir well.
Let cool for thirty minutes, then add the coffee and vanilla; stir again and put in a nine-inch ring mold.
Chill for five hours.
Turn jellied coffee onto chilled plate and fill the center with Macaroon Cream.

title: summer shrimp salad
directions: Dice first 4 ingredients into small cubes. Cut shrimp into similar sized cubes, (discarding shrimp tails or save for stock). Combine peppers, onion, celery and shrimp. Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice and 1/2 C. fresh dill. Pour mayo mixture over shrimp mixture; add salt and pepper to taste, toss to coat. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Sprinkle with remaining quarter cup of dill when ready to serve.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Do not drain vegetables; pour into 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise together.
Pour this mixture over the vegetables and mix.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top; sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer slowly for 30 minutes, stirring often.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and mix.
Add pineapple; fold in bread gently.
Bake in 2-quart casserole for 60 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade sausage (italian)
directions: Mix
ground
pork, pepper, fennel and salt together and let stand 20 to 30 minutes.
In the meanwhile, soak casings in lukewarm
water and wash well.
A sausage stuffer will come in handy.
You
make
like to make patties.
Fry or broil sausage until thoroughly cooked.
You can bake sausages in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Pork must be cooked thoroughly.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put all in a cooker and cover with water.
Cook for 1 hour at 15 pounds pressure.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Add all in order listed. Chopped nuts, marshmallows and 2 bananas (cut up) may be added. Let set in refrigerator for an hour or more.
Very good and can be made ahead of time.

title: nut bread(easy)
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg and nuts.
Blend well. Bake in 2 well-greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and sugars.
Beat in vanilla, water and egg. Sift dry ingredients together and add to sugar and egg mixture. Mix well; stir in M&M's and pecans.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Yield 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: basic recipe for "philly" frosting
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk.
Add the sugar gradually, blending it in well.
Then add your selected flavoring and mix again.
Enough to frost and fill an 8-inch, 2 layer cake.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt bark and peanut butter; stir in pecans.
Pour onto cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips and drop on top of mixture.
Pull knife through mixture.
Let stand until firm.
Break into pieces.

title: red bell pepper soup
directions: Rinse peppers and cut in half and seed.
Lay cut sides down on a cookie sheet.
Broil 4 - 6 inches from heat until skins are blackened all over
(about 12 min., but keep close watch on them). Remove from oven and place in brown paper bag and close the bag. They will steam in the bag.
After about 10 min., remove them, and remove the skin from the peppers.
Chop up the peppers and set aside.
Stir onions, carrots, and butter for 3 min. in your soup pot and then stir in the chopped peppers.
Add flour, and stir one minute.
Add broth, half & half, and tomato sauce.
Stir and mix well and let it cook approx. 10 min. until it boils and is thickened.
Stir in hot flakes or hot sauce drops and salt and pepper.

title: petit cherry cheese cakes
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until fluffy.
Line muffin tins.
Place 1 wafer in each cup.
Fill 2/3 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until set. Top each with 1 tablespoon of pie filling. Add whipped topping, if desired.

title: chili skillet
directions: Use a 10 to 12 x 3-inch skillet with cover. Heat oil in skillet over medium heat. Briefly saut onion, green pepper and garlic. Push to side of skillet. Add ground beef and pork, breaking into chunks. Saut until no longer pink. Stir in chili powder and cook for 1 minute. Add tomato juice, undrained kidney beans, oregano, salt and rice. Stir and bring to a
boil. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Stir in corn and olives. Cover and cook 5 minutes more. Sprinkle cheeses over top and cover just long enough to melt cheese. Serves 6 to 8.

title: harvest salad
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients well and pour over vegetables.
Mix well.
Let set overnight or longer.

title: fast and easy strawberry jam
directions: Measure 2 cups mashed strawberries into large bowl.
Stir in sugar.
Let stand 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Bring water and pectin to boil in small saucepan on high heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling and stirring for 1 minute.
Stir into fruit mixture in bowl.
Stir for 3 minutes or until sugar is completely dissolved.
Fill containers quickly to within 1/2 inch of top; cover with lids.
Let stand at room temperature for 24 hours.
Jam is ready to use. Refrigerator up to 3 weeks or freeze up to 1 year; thaw in refrigerator.
Makes about 6 cups.
Jam will be soft.

title: apricot rolls
directions: Mix apricots, sugar, nuts and lemon juice.

title: chicken mushroom stir-fry(serves 6)
directions: Combine first six ingredients; toss with chicken.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine chicken broth, cornstarch, water and oyster sauce.
Set aside.
In a wok or large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil over medium-high.
Add ginger root, garlic and onions; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add chicken and continue to stir-fry until chicken is white.
Remove chicken and vegetables from pan.
Add remaining oil; stir-fry carrots 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add mushrooms and pea pods; stir-fry 1 minute. Return chicken and vegetables to pan.
Stir broth mixture and pour into skillet; cook and stir until the sauce is thickened.
Serve immediately.

title: easy microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add other ingredients.
Heat in microwave until butter is melted (about 3 minutes).
Mix and add nuts (optional).
Put in buttered pan.
Cool.

title: old-fashioned shortcake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in milk powder that has been mixed with the water.
Roll out dough lightly on a floured surface until about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in desired shape and bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 450° for approximately 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.

title: appetizer pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk.
Stir in beef, onion, green pepper and pepper and mix well.
Stir in sour cream.
Put into a baking dish.
Top with walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: chicken rice bake
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish, add broccoli and rice. Mix 1 can of mushroom soup and water together.
Pour over chicken. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350 for one hour.

title: yummy broccoli
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to package directions.
Cook onions until tender; drain both vegetables.

title: shish-kabob
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl and mix thoroughly to coat everything with the barbecue sauce.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, if possible.
When ready to cook, put all the meat on 1 or 2 skewers.
Meat usually takes longer to cook.
All other vegetables can be mixed on the skewers.
Preheat grill on medium. Place skewers on grill and turn often.
When veggies turn brownish they are finished, about 15 to 20 minutes.
The meat will take a few minutes longer.
Don't overcook or the meat will be tough. Can be served with rice or salads.

title: nut rolls
directions: Blend the flour, sugar and margarine like pie crust and add the egg yolks, milk, sugar and yeast mixture.
Mix well. Immediately roll thin on floured board.
Spread with nut filling. Roll tight.
Place in greased pan.
Let rise 3 1/2 hours after rolled.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 4 rolls.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and vanilla together.
Add flour, nuts and chips.
Pat and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut while hot.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Wash and peel peaches.
Place in boiler.
Cover with vinegar and pickling spices, adding 1 cup of vinegar to 2 cups of water. Boil until tender.
Place in jar and cover.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix margarine, flour and pecans thoroughly; press into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip until smooth.
Spread over crust.

title: cheddary chicken and broccoli
directions: Place broccoli in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Combine soup and milk in a small saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup cheese. Continue baking 5 minutes or until cheese is melted and chicken is tender.
Serve over noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Combine all three ingredients. Place in 9 x 13-inch dish and bake until done at 350°.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook beef and onion in Dutch oven; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Yields 13 1/2 cups.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, margarine, vanilla and egg in large bowl. Add remaining ingredients.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes, at 400°.

title: cherry torte
directions: Pour this mixture over the already baked crust and bake another 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chicken booyah
directions: Place chicken, salt, bay leaf, cloves, 1 onion and green pepper in 5 cups water; cook until chicken is done.
Remove and debone chicken.
Remove bay leaf and cloves from broth.
Add to broth the potatoes, carrots, onions and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add 3 tablespoons flour to thicken.
Add chicken.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cook dried apples and water for 15 minutes in microwave or 30 minutes on the stove.
Add lemon juice, sugar, oleo and cinnamon to apples and put in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and put on apples.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes, or microwave on Medium-high for 7 minutes.
Rotate pan 1/2 turn.
Cook an additional 7 minutes.
Rotate 1/4 turn and cook 5 more minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; beat well. Add eggs; beat. Add dry ingredients; mix. Add nuts and grated carrots. Stir by hand. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Makes 3 (8-inch) layers.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Grease bottom of large casserole dish.
Cover bottom of dish with tortillas.
Dilute mushroom soup with 2 tablespoons chicken stock; dilute chicken soup with 2 tablespoons stock.
Sprinkle chicken over tortillas.
Spoon mushroom soup over chicken. Sprinkle onion and chili powder over soup.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Spread chicken soup over cheese.
Spread Ro-Tel tomatoes over (adding more or less according to taste).
Top with remaining cup of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Beat peanut butter, butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar and vanilla in a large mixer bowl until creamy.
Beat in eggs; beat in flour.
Stir in 3/4 cup morsels.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Remove from oven. Immediately sprinkle with remaining morsels.
Let stand for 5 minutes; spread.
If desired, sprinkle colored sugar or colored candies over melted chocolate.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut into bars when cool.

title: upside-down rhubarb cake dessert
directions: Place rhubarb in greased (like Pam) 9 x 11-inch pan.
Mix jello and sugar together and put on rhubarb.
Put marshmallows on jello. Pour cake mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve upside-down with Cool Whip.

title: traditional jam cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9-inch tube pan or two 9-inch pans.
Start oven at 325° for tube pan or 350° for layer pans.
Combine butter and sugar; beat at high speed until creamy and smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Remove beaters and stir in jam, then sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Put in prepared pans.
In tube pan, bake 1 1/2 hours.
In layer pans, bake about 35 minutes.
Test near center with toothpick; if it comes out clean, remove from oven.
Cool. Frost with caramel or cream cheese frosting.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and water chestnuts.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish. Heat Cheez Whiz in microwave until pourable.
Mix with vegetables until well blended.
Sprinkle Ritz crackers on top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk; whip until thick in electric mixer. Stir in Cool Whip.

title: egg nog
directions: Separate eggs; beat yolks until fluffy.
Add sugar.
Beat egg whites.
Beat whipping cream.
Fold in egg yolk mixture and flavoring, then egg whites.
Top with nutmeg.
Serve plain or with spirits.

title: raw apple loaf
directions: Sift together the soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and flour.
Add to the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Put in loaf pans (2 large pans or Bundt pan), greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: perfect brownies
directions: Mix together.
Butter and flour 9 x 13-inch (glass is best) pan.
Put in batter.
Can sprinkle a little sugar on top.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Check with toothpick.

title: fruit cake
directions: Dust flour on fruit as you cut it up.
Add nuts and leftover flour and the 1 tablespoon of baking powder.
Stir well.
Line pans with foil for easier removal (no oil required).
Mix all ingredients and put into 4 small loaf tins and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: italian delight
directions: Fry the meats and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Combine all ingredients listed, then add spaghetti and macaroni that have been cooked and drained in amount desired to the ingredients; top with Italian cheese.
Simmer all together for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, brown sugar, salt, vanilla and butter.
Mix. Add beaten eggs.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with pecans all over the top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lobster and chicken in sour cream-sherry sauce
directions: Melt margarine in a double boiler over simmering water.
Blend in flour; slowly add broth and heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth.
Mix in seasonings, sour cream and sherry. Add chicken and lobster and heat, stirring, 4 to 5 minutes.
Can be served over pasta or rice.

title: curried chicken wings
directions: Disjoint chicken wings and place into a large bowl (save tips for soup or stock).
Add poppy and sesame seed, mint, curry powder, salt and lemon juice.
Toss until wings are thoroughly coated.

title: sour cream swordfish
directions: Wipe fish.
Place in broiler and broil for 5 minutes.
Turn over and spread with sour cream.
Sprinkle with spices, return to 425° oven for 25 minutes.

title: french bread(with sourdough starter)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 1/2 cups warm (not hot) water.
Add Sourdough Starter, sugar, salt and 3 cups flour.
Beat well; cover with towel and let rise in warm place until double in volume. Stir down and blend in 1 cup flour mixed with 1 teaspoon soda. Gradually add another cup of flour to make a soft dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth.
Shape into 2 long loaves; let rise on lightly greased cookie sheet (covered).
Brush with water. Make diagonal slashes across top.
Bake about 45 minutes at 400°.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Wash, don't peel, cut ends off and shred in food processor. Add onions and bell pepper.
Sprinkle
3 T salt over and let set 3 or more hours.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Get out the mixer to make cookies.
Search through the toy boxes looking for beaters.
Return to find three helpers on three chairs assembled eagerly at the cookie construction site.
Scoot chairs enough to get in.
Get out cookie recipe.
Add two ingredients.
Remove hands of Helper #3.
Clean hands of Helper #2. Send Helper #1 to refrigerator for eggs.
Add next ingredient. Clean egg off floor while alternately adding eggs to mixture as Helper #2 vigorously cracks them.
Find Helper #3 removing recipes from recipe box.
Put recipes back in box in new creatively filed order.
Put recipe box back in cabinet where it should have been. Back to the cookies!
Find Helper #1 sifting flour as directed. However not necessarily into bowl.
Helper #2 decides to help Helper #1 with the flour.
Clean flour off cabinet, floor, helpers. Smell something!
Change diaper of Helper #3.
Return.
Wash hands. Helper #2 screams that she wants to be on chair that Helper #1 is on.
Helper #1 screams that he wants to be on chair that Helper #3 is occupying.
Helper #3 just screams.
Mother screams!
Helpers look shocked.
Add next ingredients.
Get out chocolate chips. Hands everywhere.
Add remaining chips to cookies.
Laugh - or was it cry?
Put cookies onto cookie sheet from three spoons and of 15 sizes and shapes.
Put cookies in oven.
Time to clean kitchen. Helpers disappear.
Eat three dozen cookies to calm nerves!

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in salted butter for 5 minutes. Drain well.
Mix together sour cream, chicken soup and carrots. Fold in zucchini and onion.
In separate bowl, combine melted butter and stuffing mix.
Spread 1/2 stuffing mix in baking dish. Spoon zucchini over that, then top with remaining stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: raisin oat cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, cream butter and both sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Blend thoroughly.
Stir in raisins and oats.

title: mountain pie
directions: Melt butter in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix together the milk, sugar and Bisquick.
Pour in butter; do not stir.
Pour in fruit; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 to 60 minutes, or until brown and firm.
Baking time differs; just keep checking.

title: poached salmon steaks with fresh dill
directions: Combine water, wine, onion, dill sprig, bay leaf and salt in deep skillet and bring to boil.
Boil gently 3 minutes.
Add salmon steaks.
Turn heat to high and return to boil.
Cover and cook over low heat until fish is cooked through, about 7 minutes for 1/2-inch-thick salmon steaks and longer for thicker steaks.
Remove from heat.

title: banana cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine butter, sugar, egg, bananas, vanilla and milk; blend well.
Stir in flour, baking soda, salt, lemon juice and nuts.
Pur into 4-cup microproof ring mold.
Cook on High 7 to 7 1/2 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Rotate dish, if cake is rising unevenly.
Cool on heat-resistant surface. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil milk, sugar and salt until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Then add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla. Place in pan and refrigerate.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Take bag of potato chips and crush them in bag or use a food processor.
Put crushed chips and 1 cup of Parmesan cheese in a bowl.
Mix together.
Melt oleo.
Dip pieces of chicken in oleo and then dip in mixture of chips/Parmesan and place in a Pyrex dish.
Salt with garlic salt before placing in the oven.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked rice florentine
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add rice, spinach and seasonings.
Beat eggs; stir into rice mixture.
Turn into buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb soup(rabarbrasuppe)
directions: Wash rhubarb and cut into 1/2-inch lengths.
Place in a saucepan with 1/2 cup water, sugar and cinnamon.
Cook until tender, about 15 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with other 1/2 cup water.
Remove boiling rhubarb from stove; add cornstarch and stir.
Return to stove for another boil, then remove and cool. Serve cold after main dish.

title: speedie hot rolls
directions: Combine warm water, sugar and yeast; stir until dissolved. Add salt and 2 cups flour; beat 2 minutes with mixer.
Add eggs and shortening; beat 1 minute.
Work in 4 1/2 cups flour.
Knead until dough is smooth.

title: marshmallow chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line bottom of three 1 1/2-inch deep (8-inch) layer cake pans.
Into large mixing bowl, sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Drop in shortening; pour in chocolate, 3/4 cup milk and vanilla extract.
With mixer at medium speed, beat 2 minutes, scraping bowl and beaters as necessary.
Add baking powder, 1/2 cup milk and eggs.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Turn into pans; bake 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tester, inserted in center, comes clean.
Cool in pans on wire racks about 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; remove paper and place layers on racks.

title: w w pina colada pie
directions: Mix together and press into a 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: cheese stuffed meat loaf
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Spray a 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch glass pan. Using only 1 cup of spaghetti sauce, combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Mix well.
Divide meat mixture into thirds.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Top with 1/2 stick of butter and crushed Ritz crackers.
Top with extra cheese if you prefer.
Heat and serve.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening until fluffy.
Add sugar 1 cup at a time, cream thoroughly.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients and milk into creamed mixture.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: strawberry delight(individual serving)
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Splenda and extract.
Simple, but good ... great for people on low carb diets.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients; chill for several hours before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, syrup, sugar, vanilla and salt; mix well. Blend spices with butter; add to egg mixture.
Combine pecans with flour; stir in egg mix.
Put in pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Continue to bake 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cook beef until done. Add onion and seasonings. Cook 5 minutes. Add can of tomatoes (do not need all of the juice) or you can add just a little water.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fruit-cheese dip
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir together Neufchatel cheese, bananas and nutmeg until smooth.
Stir in crushed pineapple or chopped fruit.
Cover and chill in the refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Serve with apple and pear wedges, strawberries or other fruit dippers as desired.
Makes 1 1/4 cups (14 servings).
Also serve Fruit-Cheese Dip as a dessert.
Serve with fruit dippers or cake cubes.

title: make ahead breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread bottom with bread.
Top with a layer of sausage, then a layer of cheese.
Mix milk, eggs, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over top of bread, sausage and cheese.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes.

title: three bean roast
directions: Beans should be cooked in separate pans as dry as possible. Mash beans separately through a fine sieve.
The addition of cream and butter to beans will give an extra rich flavor.
Carefully alternate bean layers in loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until solid throughout.
Serve in slices with a cream sauce topping.

title: chicken stew
directions: Saute onions.
Add broth, water, potatoes, chicken and carrots; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 25 minutes. Add green beans and chicken-broccoli soup.
Allow these to heat. Serve over biscuits.

title: maw maw wannie's casserole
directions: Mix ground beef and onion together.
Brown in a large skillet.
Drain off fat and add vegetable beef soup.
Simmer while peeling and cutting the potato into wafer-thin slices.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until well blended.
Beat egg yolks and add the flour alternately with the milk, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour half batter into a greased oblong pan.
Cover with floured blueberries, then with the remaining batter.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar while warm and cut in 2-inch squares.

title: sweet 'n' sour meatballs
directions: In large bowl, combine meat, water chestnuts, eggs, bread crumbs, bouillon and Worcestershire; mix well.
Shape into 1 1/4-inch meatballs.
In large skillet, brown meatballs.
Remove from heat; pour off fat.

title: harvest meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix lightly with fork.
Shape into a loaf and bake in greased 8 x 8-inch pan for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix together the green beans, corn, soup, cheese and water chestnuts.
Put into a 2 quart casserole.
Combine the melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake for about 40 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil until a drop forms a ball when dropped in water.
Remove from heat and quickly put in a drop of vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir constantly until smooth.
Pour into buttered (not greased) pan.

title: chilled jello salad
directions: In a large bowl, fold in jello with Cool Whip.
Drain oranges and pineapple and add to Cool Whip and jello.
Add in cottage cheese and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Mix well and chill.
Jell-O can be substituted for different flavor for a different color (ex. strawberry makes pink).

title: barbecued sandwiches
directions: Fry hamburger.
Drain off fat.
Mix all together and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, then oatmeal and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to oatmeal mixture, mixing well.
Pour into large rectangular pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Is good without frosting.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Roux:
Brown flour in oil (this can be done in the microwave, 2-2-1-1-30-30 seconds.
(Dark brown roux.)

title: world's easiest ever ice cream
directions: Stir together and freeze firm in refrigerator tray.
Break up in pieces.
Whip until fluffy and refreeze.
Enjoy!

title: chef's salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large salad bowl or divide ingredients into individual salad bowls.
Garnish with hard-cooked egg slices.
Serve with desired dressing.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stir-fried chicken(low-fat)
directions: In skillet or wok over high heat, heat oil.
Cut chicken into strips.
Stir-fry until opaque; remove and set aside.
Add 1 tablespoon oil to skillet and stir.
Saute vegetables, any combination, until crisp-tender.
In a cup, mix chicken broth, cornstarch, ginger and soy sauce.
Add to skillet with the reserved chicken.
Cook until mixture thickens, stirring frequently.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate syrup icing
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cook for 2 minutes.
This icing is so delicious served warm over a yellow cake.
This is my family's favorite dessert.

title: jalapeno cheese grits
directions: Add grits gradually to water and salt, stirring until thick, about 5 minutes.
Add margarine and cheese.
Stir often over low heat until ready to be served.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover diced potatoes with water to about 1-inch above potatoes. Leave room for all other items. Cook potatoes until done. Add rest of ingredients and cook slowly until delicious! Stir often and keep heat low.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Cook noodles 7 to 8 minutes in salt water.
Drain.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan with butter (margarine).
Mix ingredients well with electric mixer, then add it to noodles.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool.

title: kibbi(ground lamb with wheat grain)
directions: Grind meat and onions together.
Wash bulghur and squeeze water well from grain by hand.
Mix with meat and onions.
Season with salt and pepper.
Grind a second time.
Mix, using a little water to make the mixture pliable and smooth.

title: spicy black-eyed peas
directions: Mix and cook all ingredients together in a large kettle.
Goes good with Mexican corn bread.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook macaroni by directions; drain.
Mix 1/2 of macaroni and 1/4 stick of butter (melted).
In a separate bowl, mix onion, green pepper, cheeses and sour cream.
Add macaroni to mixture. Mix other half of the macaroni with remaining butter and add to mixture.
Pour in glass casserole and top with spaghetti sauce. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Peel and cut up apples to small bite size pieces and place in a bowl.
In a small bowl, mix the mayonnaise, sugar and milk. Pour this mixture over the apples and make sure the apples are well covered with the mayonnaise mixture.
Wash and split in half the grapes and add to the salad along with the raisins, nuts and celery.
May put lettuce leaves on a plate and spoon salad on top.

title: chicken pileau
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Take chicken off bones.
Put chicken and sausage in the broth and cook until sausage is tender. Fry bacon and onions and add to chicken and sausage, then add rice, margarine, Kitchen Bouquet, salt and pepper.
Cook until rice is done.

title: orange slice candy cake
directions: Cut candy and dates in small pieces; mix with 1 cup flour. Mix in pecans and coconut.

title: creamsicle fudge
directions: Bring to a full boil the sugar, margarine and milk. Cook 5 minutes. Take off stove and add morsels and marshmallow cream. Mix well. Take out 1 cup and set aside. To the remaining mixture, add extract and food coloring. Mix well and put in buttered dish. Add the cup of reserved mixture to top of mixture and swirl in pan. Cool and cut in small pieces. May be refrigerated.

title: jewel's cinnamon applesauce jelly
directions: Peel and core apples; cut into small pieces.
Place in large saucepan.
Add a little water; cook apples and make applesauce. Do not add sugar.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix butter, sugar and salt in mixer or by hand.
Add eggs, one at a time, then stir in Eagle Brand milk.
Stir the rest of ingredients but do not heat.
Pour mixture into suitable size dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake for about 25 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven while still shimmery in center.

title: roast fresh brisket
directions: Place beef fat side up in large heavy covered kettle over 1/2 of cut up vegetables.
Spread some ketchup, generously over meat. Sprinkle with pepper and garlic clove.
Top with rest of vegetables and 1 bay leaf.
Add water to almost cover.
Bring to a boil.
Place in 325° oven for 3 or 4 hours.
Remove meat and slice fat off top.
Wrap in foil.
Refrigerate overnight with heavy weight on top.
Keeps well.
Reheat for dinner or slice for sandwiches.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add vanilla to mixture and blend well.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add to the mixture.
Beat at medium speed for 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour batter into lined greased tube pan.
Bake in a preheated oven of 325° for 1 hour or until cake springs back when touched lightly with finger. Remove from oven and allow to cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Season pork chops with salt, pepper and paprika.
In skillet, brown pork chops slowly on both sides.
Drain off excess fat.
Add the cup of water, celery and soup mix.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Turn chops and cook 20 minutes more (or longer).
Remove chops from skillet.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Place 3 cups of peaches in pie shell.
Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs and sour cream, stirring until well blended.
Spoon over peaches.
Combine 1/2 cup of sugar and remaining flour.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle evenly to cover top of pie (there may be extra topping).
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Use sliced peach for garnish.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Wash and peel cucumber.
Cut thin, thin slices (takes a steady hand and a little time, but it is worth it).
Sprinkle with salt and sugar; add vinegar.
Then press slices with back of spoon until salad is quite juicy.
Cool, crisp and delicious eaten with meat, fish or sandwiches.

title: crisply fresh salad
directions: Saute all ingredients, except tomato sauce, in the olive oil over medium heat until the onion is clear.
Add tomato sauce and saute for about 5 minutes.
Add to your main dish.

title: baked pork chops and potatoes
directions: Brown pork chops and place in baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place potatoes and onion on top of pork chops. Gradually add milk to the soup and stir until smooth.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Makes its own gravy.

title: lentil soup
directions: Braise onions, carrots, celery and garlic in the oil. Wash and pick out lentils.
Put lentils, onions, carrots, celery and garlic in large saucepan and simmer for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Add the tomatoes that have been chopped or broken up.
Add salt to taste and simmer another 30 minutes.

title: whipped cream icing
directions: Combine gelatin and cold water in small saucepan.
Let stand until thick.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly, just until gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Whip the cream, sugar and vanilla until slightly thickened.
While beating slowly, gradually add gelatin to whipped cream mixture.
Whip at high speed until stiff.
Yield: 2 cups.
Cakes iced with this icing must be refrigerated.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix lemon Jell-O and 1 cup hot peach juice.
Let slightly jell.
Add cottage cheese and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped cream, peaches and nuts.
Chill.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put single
layer of bread slices on bottom of buttered 13 x 9-inch
casserole.	Saute mushrooms in butter and alternate layers of
ham,
mushrooms and cheese.
Cover with bread slices.	Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour egg mixture over casserole. Sprinkle
with bread crumbs; dot with butter. Refrigerate overnight.	Bake
in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Yields 12 small servings.

title: olive cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans; mix well. Shape into a ball; coat with pecans.

title: cherry-coconut bars
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter or margarine.
Beat together the egg, milk and vanilla and add to mixture.
Spread in 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Top with thin layer of cherry preserves.

title: sticky buns
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Put frozen rolls in pan.
Sprinkle with 1 box of pudding mix.
Melt oleo with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour hot mixture over rolls.
Sprinkle pecans (optional).
Seal with foil and let set at room temperature overnight.
Remove foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Invert on serving plate and serve while hot.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa and milk to a boil.
Stir in remaining ingredients and spread on hot cake.

title: german's sweet chocolate pecan pie
directions: Beat cream cheese in a large bowl with electric mixer at high speed until smooth.
Add half and half.
Beat at low speed until well mixed.
Add pie filling mix.
Beat until blended 1 minute. Fold in whipped topping, chocolate and pecans.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Saute onions and garlic in pan until onions are clear.
Add chicken breasts; turn up heat to brown meat.
Add soy sauce while chicken is cooking.
When chicken is almost done, add 1/4 cup or more of teriyaki sauce.
Thicken with cornstarch; thin with pineapple juice.
Garnish with pineapple chunks.
Serve with broccoli, carrot and cauliflower vegetable medley.

title: fruit enchiladas
directions: Spread 2 tablespoons fruit on each tortilla.
Roll up and place in pan with seam down.
Cut in half.
Mix and heat in microwave the oleo, water and 2 cups sugar until melted.
Mix well and pour over the tortillas.
Let sit 2 hours at room temperature.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over the enchiladas.
Put back in oven 10 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail
directions: Put the banana, 2 cups milk and 1 tablespoon sugar in a blender and blend until creamy consistency is achieved.
Fill serving glass halfway with mixture.
In a clean blender, again, put the strawberries, water, 2 tablespoons sugar and lemon juice and blend until smooth.
Again, in the serving glass, fill the other half with the second mixture (do not mix the two juices) and serve.

title: peach ice cream
directions: In heavy saucepan,
heat milk over low until hot, but not boiling.
Sir in sugar and salt until dissolved.
Gradually stir a quarter of the hot mixture into eggs, mixing constantly.
Continue to cook and stir for 10 to 12 minutes or until mixture coats the back of a metal spoon.
Remove from heat; cool.
Chill at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cornflakes and 1/4 cup butter. Pour into a well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Toss crushed cornflakes and margarine together and sprinkle over potatoes. This freezes well and is very good!

title: country coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage, onion, carrot and green pepper together in a large bowl.

title: cottage cheese cloud
directions: Mix all together.
Let stand before serving.

title: pineapple spice drops
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix shortening, sugars, spices and egg until creamy.
Blend in pineapple then blend in flour mixture.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12-15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar before cooling.
Makes 3 1/2 - 4 dozen.

title: vanilla icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Turn dough out on a piece of waxed paper.
Roll into a 2 x 2-inch log.
Chill several hours. Slice in 1/4-inch slices.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: maple syrup
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugars, corn syrup and water.
Stir until dissolved and bring to a boil.
Cover and boil gently for 10 minutes.
Do not stir!
Remove from heat, cool slightly.
Add vanilla and maple flavor.
Stir only until mixed.
Makes 1 quart.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Mix and boil first 4 ingredients.
Place dill and garlic in bottom, center and top of gallon jug.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together well; roll into bite-size balls. Fry in small amount of oil; pour off excess fat.

title: spoon burgers on buns
directions: In a large skillet, saute the onion and celery in oil until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add the beef and cook and stir until meat is browned; spoon off any fat.
Stir in cheese and tomato sauce, vinegar and sugar.
Add 2 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes until cheese is melted, stirring often.
Serve in buns with your favorite toppings.

title: ann's crab pate
directions: Heat undiluted soup until it stirs easily.
Remove from stove and add to gelatine which has been dissolved in cold water.
Add softened cream cheese and remaining ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Spoon into an oiled 4-cup mold and chill.

title: black bean soup
directions: Over medium heat, saute onion in oil until transparent; add chicken pieces and stir until slightly browned. Add beans in their broth, then chicken broth. Season with chili powder, garlic and cumin. Bring to boil, then simmer for 30 minutes. Serve with grated Cheddar or Mexican cheese, sour cream and tortilla chips.

title: chicken maciel
directions: Bring cream and butter to a boil.
Add cornstarch and curry powder.
Mix smoothly.
Add sherry.
Cook until sauce is thickened and add chicken.

title: cocoa cappuccino mousse
directions: Heat milk, cocoa, butter and coffee over low heat until butter melts, stirring constantly.
Cool.
In a large bowl, beat whipping cream until stiff.
Gradually fold in chocolate mixture.
Spoon into dessert dishes; chill about 2 hours before serving.

title: italian bread
directions: Dissolve yeast, sugar and shortening in water.
Stir in 4 cups flour, salt and egg; beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to form a stiff dough.
Turn out onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and allow to rise in a warm place, punching dough down every 10 minutes, for 1 hour. Then allow dough to rise for 1 additional hour, or until doubled. Punch dough down; let rest 10 minutes.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in a jar and shake well. Drain juice from canned vegetables. Place vegetables in large container with lid. Add tomatoes and dressing. Stir well. Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator. Keeps up to 2 weeks. Great for picnics or barbecues.

title: field pea jambalaya(this recipe designed for rice cooker)
directions: Saute seasonings in butter.
Add meat and cook about 10 minutes. Add peas, rice, and broth and transfer to rice cooker. Cook
until rice is done.

title: marinated london broil
directions: Soak London Broil in saucepan with garlic slices, oil, salt and pepper for 2 hours prior to cooking.
Put in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn London Broil occasionally.
Slice meat as thin and as raw as desired.
Serve with baked potatoes and biscuits with vegetables.

title: low-fat mexican stromboli
directions: Filling:
In a large skillet, brown meat; drain fat.
Stir in half of the beans and all the salsa.
Mash the remaining beans with a fork and add to mixture.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Grease cookie sheet.

title: out of this world bars
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine; press into pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix milk and coconut and spread over crumb mixture. Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage and boil 10 minutes until tender.
Drain and combine with cheese soup.
Crush crackers and mix with melted oleo.
Place cabbage mixture in casserole and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Especially good served with baked ham and tossed green salad and rye rolls.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix crab meat, salt, mustard, pepper, egg yolk, Worcestershire sauce and mayonnaise.
Make mixture into small cakes.
Dip cakes into flour and egg, then into crumbs.
Quickly fry in salad oil on high heat until brown.

title: grandma hixon's recipe for coconut pie
directions: Mix together and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes. Makes a delicious pie.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with artichokes or cut up veggies.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix very well all ingredients until mixture holds its shape. Make small walnut size sausage balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake about 350° until golden brown.

title: escarole and rice soup
directions: Separate the escarole leaves and discard any wilted or bruised ones.
Soak in a bowl of water; dunk up and down.
Drain briefly. Stack the leaves, a bunch at a time, and cut crosswise into 1-inch wide pieces; set aside.

title: chocolate ripple cake
directions: Cream butter, oleo and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk until smooth after each addition.
Pour 2/3 of batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Combine chocolate syrup and baking soda.
Lightly blend with remaining batter.
Pour over batter in pan.
Do not mix!
Bake in 350° oven for 75 minutes or until tested done.
Cool completely before removing from pan.
Can be frosted or dusted with 10x sugar.

title: brown rice with black beans
directions: In a large, deep skillet, heat oil and stir onion until tender, but not browned.
Add tomatoes, beans, oregano and garlic powder.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Return to a boil.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 10 minutes.
Put cooked broccoli in casserole.
Cover with Velveeta cheese slices.
Crumble Ritz crackers and sprinkle over top.
Add melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine 3 boxes Jell-O with 3 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and let thaw.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Layer cake torn in pieces
in cake pan and pour Jell-O mixture over top.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cauliflower delight
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and chill several hours or overnight.

title: apple cranberry deep dish pie
directions: In
a
mixing bowl, stir together 1/4 cup sugar, flour, apple pie spice or nutmeg and orange peel.
Stir in cranberry sauce. Add
apples;
toss	to coat.
Transfer to 10-inch deep dish pie plate or 1 1/2 quart casserole.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Mash bananas with beater.
Add lemon juice and mix. Cream the shortening and sugar with electric mixer at medium speed.
Add eggs and continue to beat about 4 minutes.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold in bananas and nuts. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Wrap in plastic and let stand overnight before slicing.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Cook onions, bell pepper and celery in butter until tender. Add mushroom soup and Worcestershire sauce, stirring gently.
Stir in crawfish, rice, salt and pepper.
Pour into buttered casserole. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy apple dumplings
directions: Butter 4 custard cups large enough to set apples into them.

title: scrumptious turnip greens
directions: Cook onion, red pepper flakes and salt pork in water in a very large Dutch oven.
Wash all greens carefully and add to pot.
Cook until greens are tender.

title: spinach squares
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder. Add milk and margarine. Mix well. Add all other ingredients.
Mix well. Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Pour in pan and bake at 375° about 30 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut off top of peppers; remove seeds and cores.
Combine tuna with olives, onions, capers and parsley.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour oil over peppers.
Cool and chill for several hours.
Serves 6.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in large heavy pan.
Place over medium heat.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Cover and cook 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Cook until soft ball stage (234°); add peanuts and cook until candy reaches hard crack or brittle stage (300°).
Remove from heat, add soda and butter; stir well. Spread on well-buttered 14 1/2 x 17-inch cookie sheet.
As candy cools, loosen sides and pull; stretch candy as thin as possible. Break into pieces.

title: french toast
directions: Mix above ingredients thoroughly in a bowl or dish deep enough to dip bread into.
Completely soak the slices of bread and place in a frying pan;
cook, flipping occasionally.

title: hosenflickens
directions: Beat eggs and salt together.
When well beaten, add cream and beat again.
Add flour and mix.
Roll out on table.
Cut in slices, and put about 3 slits in each slice.
Slices should be about 3 inches wide and 6 inches long.
Fry in deep grease.
When fried done, sprinkle with sugar.
Let cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add other ingredients.
Bake in uncooked pie shell for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin pie crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of cake pan.
Combine pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs, sugar, spice and salt in large bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over pumpkin mixture.
Top with pecans.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown. Cool completely.
Serve cold with Cool Whip.
Flip pieces so top is on plate.
Refrigerate.

title: confectioners sugar icing
directions: Melt margarine; mix in sugar and slowly add milk until icing is smooth. Add vanilla. More or less milk may be needed for smooth icing.

title: pudding in a cloud
directions: Tear up angel food cake.
Mix up pudding and pour on top of cake, then add Cool Whip to top.
Chill and serve.
May be garnished with cherries, strawberries, grapes, coconut, etc.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Cream
the
sugar
and butter.	Add flour and eggs; mix well. Add
flavoring.
Bake
at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until done.

title: instant cappuccino mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Place one heaping tablespoonful mix in cup.
Add boiling water.
Makes 2 1/4 cups of mix.

title: baked vidalia onions
directions: Peel onions.
Cut 3/4 down through the onions, criss-crossing until onions fan out like a floweret.
Do not cut through to the bottom.
Fill the center with butter, and Worcestershire sauce. Sprinkle with Nature's Seasoning.
Place each onion on large square of foil.
Bring edges of the foil to the top center and twist firmly.
Place on a flat cooking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until soft.
Serves 4 - 6.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: *Use a bottle of Frank's poppy seed.

title: fried tacos
directions: Brown ground beef; add salt, garlic powder, and pepper.
Then mix the ground beef and beans.

title: low-fat, easy and elegant dessert
directions: Bake an angel food cake according to box directions.
Split in middle (horizontally) after baking and cool.
Use Cool Whip and chocolate syrup, mixed together.
Ice the inside layer first, then the sides and top.
Can decorate with nuts, strawberries or cherries.
May be frozen.

title: bachelor chicken
directions: Cook in crock-pot.
Season chicken; add all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
Skin and slice when cool.
Pour water over sliced potatoes, then drain.
Chop onion and mix with potatoes.
Cut bacon in small pieces and fry.
Pour fat and bacon over potatoes and mix well.
Salt to taste.

title: cajun maquechou (mach shoe)
directions: Heat bacon drippings in a heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add corn, onion, garlic and green pepper.
Cook until onion is thoroughly wilted and transparent, about 10 minutes.
Stir often to prevent sticking.
Add tomatoes, salt, black pepper, sugar and cayenne; stir until combined.
Add stock or broth.
Reduce heat. Barely simmer, stirring often, until liquid has almost evaporated, about 30 minutes.
The mixture will be thick and mushy.
Stir in milk.
Cook until reduced by 1/2.
Increase heat slightly.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine oil, buttermilk, soda, allspice, nutmeg, sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt together.
Add stewed prunes, vanilla, eggs and nuts to first part.
Bake in hot oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Measure biscuit mix into mixing bowl.
Stir in wheat germ and cardamon.
Add honey, eggs, water, orange peel and butter.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.

title: cheese ring
directions: Soften grated cheese.
Mix cheese, onions and mayonnaise, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Add pecans.
Shape into a ring on a plate. Chill.
Pour preserves into center of the ring.
Serve both preserves and cheese together on a cracker.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, combine apples, sugar, flour, spices and salt.
Spoon into shell.

title: chocolate coca-cola cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour together in a large bowl; set aside.
Put butter, Wesson oil, cocoa and Coca-Cola in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add miniature marshmallows and stir until they are melted. Mix until well blended.
Mix buttermilk and soda; add eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: belly stickers
directions: Soften active dry yeast in warm water (110°) or compressed yeast in lukewarm water (85°).
Combine milk, 2 tablespoons of sugar, shortening and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup of flour.
Beat well.
Beat in softened yeast and egg.
Gradually add remaining flour to form soft dough, beating well.
Cover and let rise in warm place (82°) until doubled (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Turn out on lightly floured surface and shape as desired.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix ground chuck, cornflakes, applesauce, onion, salt and pepper.
Make into balls.
Place in baking dish (lined in foil). Mix together catsup, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake, covered, about 1 hour.
Remove cover and brown a little.

title: frozen chocolate pie
directions: Cook crust.
In small bowl (mixer) blend 1 cup confectioners sugar and butter on low speed until fluffy.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
