On high speed beat in eggs one at a time; beat thoroughly after each addition.
Pour into baked shell.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Freeze until firm (several hours).
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before eating for easier serving.

title: homemade bread
directions: Put the jello in a bowl. Put milk in it.
Then you put it in the refrigerator and freeze.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick of margarine together to make crust.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Thaw and drain shrimp well (may press in paper towels to remove all water).
Combine cream cheese, onion, garlic salt, hot sauce, mayonnaise and salt (if needed).
Add shrimp and mix well. Form into a ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill until ready to serve.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with assorted crackers. Make a day ahead so flavors will blend.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine
shrimp
and
crabmeat with as much pickles and mayonnaise as you like.
Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle 1 stick melted butter over cookies and freeze.
Spread ice cream over cookie crust and re-freeze.

title: steak sauce
directions: Mix, chill and use as a sauce to brush on grilled steaks and chops as grilling.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix jelly, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and mustard in large saucepan.
Heat until melted.
Add wieners, sliced in thirds. Cover and simmer 45 minutes over medium heat.

title: tacos
directions: Brown beef; add salt, onions, peppers, sauce and chili powder. Serve with shredded lettuce, shredded cheese, sour cream (optional).

title: citrus salad
directions: Section grapefruit and oranges over a bowl to catch juices. In a large bowl combine citrus sections, cucumber and onion. Measure reserved fruit juices; add orange juice to make one cup. Combine juice mixture, vinegar, sugar, salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper; pour over fruit.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.
At serving time, use a slotted spoon to remove the fruit from marinade.
Arrange on lettuce-lined plates. Drizzle marinade atop each salad.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Brown sausage; put in onion and pepper.
Add cheese, cut in small pieces.
Add spices.
Take off stove when cheese is melted. Set aside.
Put on bread.
Freeze and heat in oven when needed at 350°.

title: tomato french dressing
directions: Mix all dressing ingredients together in jar and shake well.

title: lynda's swiss steak
directions: In a shallow dish, beat eggs.
Set aside.
In another shallow dish, combine flour, garlic powder, black pepper and salt to your liking.
Set aside.
In a large pan, cook 2 Tbsp. olive oil, 1 Tbsp. butter, onions and mushrooms on medium heat.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Using the same large pan, add remaining olive oil and butter and set on medium-low heat.
Dip cubed steaks into eggs and then dredge through flour mixture.
Place into pan and sear both sides.
Add extra olive oil if pan becomes dry.

title: olive cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: speedy quiche
directions: Saute cubed Spam, onion and peppers in oil until tender. Spoon into lightly greased 10-inch deep dish pie pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top of meat mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients in a separate bowl until smooth.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let set for 5 minutes before cutting.

title: herb cheese wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine Bisquick, onion, sugar and herbs.
Mix the egg and milk together.
Beat softly. Add this, the butter and wine to the dry ingredients. Beat until blended.
Turn out onto a well-greased round 8-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle the cheese on top. Bake at 400° until brown and crusty, about 25 minutes. Allow to sit for 10 minutes. Cut in wedges and serve with butter. Serves 6 to 8.

title: one big pot of chili
directions: Boil hot sausage 15 minutes, chop.
Brown ground meat and sausages.
Dump everything in big pot.
Cook 1 1/2 hours on simmer. Serve with cooked rice or mashed potatoes (can make hotter).

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together. Add eggs.
Mix soda with buttermilk. Alternately add milk and flour. Mix well.
Add flavorings last. Grease only tube pan sides and tube. Line bottom of the pan with chopped pecans. Pour batter over nuts.
Bake slowly at 325° for 1 hour or longer. Doesn't need icing.

title: lemon cream cheese pie
directions: In saucepan combine water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat and stir for 2 more minutes.
Beat 1 cup hot mixture into egg yolks. Transfer back into saucepan and bring to gentle boil.
Cook for about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, add 1/3 cup lemon juice, margarine and salt.
Stir until margarine melts.
Cover with clear plastic wrap and chill for a couple hours.
Beat sweetened condensed milk, cream cheese, 1/3 cup lemon juice and pudding mix. Pour this mixture into 2 pie crusts.
Over this layer, add the cooled lemon mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cranberry-hazelnut white chocolate fudge
directions: Lightly butter 9 x 13 pan. Set aside. Heat sugar, butter, cream and salt in heavy 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until boiling. Continue cooking 5 minutes or candy thermometer reaches 240°. Remove from heat.

title: cranberry orange sauce(no fat)
directions: Cook cranberries, sugar, ginger and juice on high, covered, for 7 to 11 minutes until the berries pop.
Stir in oranges and nuts.
Chill.
Makes 3 cups.

title: spiced apple cookies
directions: In a saucepan, cover raisins with water.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain.
Cream brown sugar and butter.
Beat in egg and milk.
Sift together flour, spices and baking soda; add to butter mixture.
Beat until blended.
Stir in nuts, apples and drained raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately cool on wire rack.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Cook all ingredients together on slow heat until thickened. Put in hot jars.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions. Combine margarine, soup, spices and milk together. Add chicken; combine with cooked noodles. Pour in casserole dish. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: In electric skillet, saute bacon and onion.
When bacon is almost done, add 1 stick margarine.
When margarine is melted, add chopped cabbage.
Stir.
Add seasoned salt, lemon pepper and seasoned pepper to taste and sugar.
Stir continuously so that cabbage is well coated with seasoning and bacon drippings.
Add sliced smoked sausage and continue stirring.
When cabbage has simmered on low about 15 minutes, add 2 cans diced Rotel and stir until cabbage is coated.
Cover and simmer about 20-30 minutes until cabbage is tender.

title: marshmallow snow
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Cool, then add whipped cream and crushed pineapple.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham cracker crumbs.
Pour in marshmallow mixture.
Sprinkle crumbs on top. Chill.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Dissolve sugar in milk.
Stir in salt, vanilla and cream.
Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze.
Makes one gallon.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Combine water, sugar, salt and shortening; stir. Add yeast cakes and stir until dissolved. Add flour gradually. Cover after kneading lightly.
Let rise until doubled in size. Knead lightly and roll out on slightly floured board 1/2-inch thick. Cut out and dip in melted shortening. Cover and let rise again. Bake in 450° oven.

title: fruit pie filling for strawberries, blueberries or raspberries
directions: Cook oleo and flour until smooth. Add water, vanilla and sugar. Cook until thickened; add berries. Pour into pie crust.

title: date nut cake
directions: Scald dates, baking soda and butter with the cup of boiling water.
When cool, add all other ingredients.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 to 55 minutes (use an angel food cake pan or Bundt pan).
Cool upside-down and when removed from pan, glaze with powdered sugar/water or just sprinkle with powdered sugar. Decorate with cherry halves and nuts.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix eggs, onion and 1/2 package seasoning in blender.
Add to beef and mix well.	Roll in meat balls.
Put in shallow pan and bake until they are well done.
Put tomato sauce in pan with the other half seasoning; heat.
Add meatballs and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: chicken-in-a-garden
directions: Combine garlic powder, 1 tablespoon oil, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, salt, pepper and chicken; mix well and let set 20 minutes.
Pour remaining oil in wok; add green peppers and cook 4 minutes.
Add celery, scallions and thawed pea pods; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove vegetables and set aside.
Add chicken to wok and stir-fry 3 minutes; add stir-fried vegetables, tomatoes and cooked bouillon mixture.
Stir-fry over low heat (225°) for 3 minutes or until thickened and bubbly.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: sausage balls in hot sauce
directions: Form sausage into balls about 1 to 1 1/4 inches in diameter. Brown well.
Remove cooked sausage balls from pan and pour off grease.
Add jelly and mustard to skillet and blend well to make the hot sauce.
The sauce and the balls may be stored separately until ready to serve.
Put balls in sauce and keep hot in a chafing dish to serve.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Cream together sugar, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Sift and add flour, cocoa and baking soda, then add lukewarm water.
Grease and flour pans, one 13 x 9-inch pan or three 8-inch round pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: loretta's crab chowder
directions: Fry bacon.
Spread on paper towels and set aside.
Chop potatoes and onion in small amount of water, stirring occasionally.
Chop crab meat and add to mixture.
Add balance of water, seasoning and sour cream.
Cook until vegetables are done. Make paste from flour and small amount of water.
Add to soup mixture and cook.
Add crumbled bacon last.
Serve with crackers.

title: hush puppies
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine cornmeal and flour in bowl.
Add buttermilk and mix thoroughly.
Add egg, chopped onion and dissolved yeast and mix well.
Drop from teaspoon into deep, hot fat.
Cook until golden brown.
Serve while hot.

title: joanne's chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in salted water.
Drain.
Mix chicken, pimento, pepper and onion.
Add soup.
Rinse out can with broth.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 1/4 cups cheese and toss all together well with fork until well mixed.
Sprinkle the 1/2 cup grated cheese on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add wings and marinate overnight or longer, the longer, the better!
Spread foil in pan.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Place candies in 2 cups water.
Boil until candies melt. Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add applesauce, lemon juice and 1 cup cold water.
Chill until set.
Mix cream cheese and milk. Spread on top of jello.
Cut into squares.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken paprika(a "quick meal" that kids love!)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in glass baking pan in oven.
Mix other ingredients in bowl.
Wash and pat dry chicken; dip in mixture.
Lay chicken, skin side down, in buttered dish. Bake 30 minutes.
Turn over and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: bonnell's irish pasta
directions: Slice basil into 1/8-inch wide strips.
Chop tomatoes in 1/2-inch pieces.
Saute onion in oil in heavy skillet until soft. Add tomatoes and sugar to skillet.
Cover and cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate angel dessert
directions: Place 1/2 cake pieces in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chips over hot water and add 1 tablespoon sugar; let cool slightly.
Beat egg yolks and add to chocolate.
Beat egg whites and add 1 tablespoon sugar.
Whip the whipping cream and prepare the Dream Whip (follow package directions) and combine the two.
Add the egg whites to the whipping cream; fold into chocolate mixture.
Put 1/2 of chocolate mixture over cake and add next layer of cake and then finish with layer of chocolate.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half.
Wash and remove seed.
Place peppers in pot.
Cover with water.
Let boil 3 minutes.
Drain off water. Brown beef and drain off liquid.
Mix corn flake crumbs with milk, egg and ketchup.
Fold browned beef into mixture.
Season with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon the mixture into pepper halves.
Place in a baking dish or pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: instant wassail
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in covered container.
For instant Wassall, stir 2 to 3 teaspoons of mix into 1 cup hot water.

title: fast fruit salad
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl.
Drizzle pudding over fruit and stir.
Very quick and good!

title: blueberry pie
directions: Let cheese get soft.
Add sugar, beat real well.
Add Cool Whip and vanilla.
Put into two graham cracker crusts.
Make at night and put in refrigerator until morning.
Keep blueberry pie filling in refrigerator also.
Put half of can on each pie.

title: easy cheesy potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon in large bowl. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle crumbled bacon over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are done. Yield: 8 to 12 servings.

title: white lily pancakes
directions: *For thicker pancakes, use less milk.
For thinner pancakes, use more milk.

title: chocolate zucchini loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients; add to egg mixture alternately with milk.
Fold in orange peel, zucchini and nuts.
Turn into 2 greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake for 50 minutes, or until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Turn out; cool completely on wire rack.

title: pork chops
directions: Put tenderizer, vinegar, salt, garlic salt and Adobo in a bowl.
Marinate pork chops for 3 to 4 hours.
After marinating, fry chops in 2 tablespoons oil until cooked.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Combine eggs, brown sugar, margarine, cream and vanilla. Stir in pecans.
Pour mixture in unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle top with pecans.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: bayou broccoli
directions: Cook rice and broccoli.
Drain broccoli, mix rice and broccoli together.
Add margarine, cheese, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Put in casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until top is golden and bubbly.

title: five hour beef stew
directions: Mix together. Cook in slow cooker for 5 hours.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt in large bowl. Add wet mixture, eggs, milk and oil.
Mix all ingredients well. Fill muffin tins half full (well-greased).
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: stir-fried turkey or chicken and veggies
directions: In a medium bowl combine sugar, cornstarch, ginger and soy sauce.
Mix well.
Add turkey and chicken.
Stir-fry to coat. Let stand 15 minutes.

title: applesauce pancake topping
directions: In a saucepan, heat applesauce, raisins and cinnamon on medium heat until raisins plump up.
Allow applesauce to reach desired temperature; remove from heat. Add honey and serve immediately.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and margarine; cook for 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Quickly drop by tablespoons onto greased surface.
If it hardens too quickly before spooning, add a few drops of milk, stirring rapidly.

title: mulled tea punch
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags.
Cover and
let stand 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Heat apple juice, syrup drained from crab apples, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg in saucepan.
Simmer 2 minutes to blend flavors.
Combine with tea.
Garnish each tea serving with crab apple and cinnamon stick.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil spaghetti as directed on package.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Wash and dry tomatoes and cucumbers.
Dice tomatoes and cucumbers.
Toss lightly with spaghetti.
Add cucumber dressing and Italian dressing.
Chill 1 hour.

title: oven easy pork chops
directions: In a pie pan, combine crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
In a small bowl, blend milk and egg.
Coat chops with crumbs; dip in egg mixture and again in crumbs.
Melt margarine in oven in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place chops in pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Turn chops; bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook onion, celery and pepper in squash juice.
Mix together and bake at 400° until firm.
Top with cheese and cover until served.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread crumbs in bottom of 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Cook and drain sausage.
Place sausage on top of bread crumbs.
Add cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper and mustard together.
Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: almond cheese ball
directions: Mix milk, Miracle Whip and dry dressing mix.
Add cream cheese and beat well with electric mixer.
Add Cheddar cheese and blend. Cover and freeze for 30 minutes. Shape cheese mixture into a ball. Roll cheese ball in toasted almonds.

title: parsley-buttered new potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and remove 1/2-inch peel around center of each potato with a small knife.
Place potatoes and water in a 2-quart glass casserole, arranging them in a circle with small potatoes in the center.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap or lid.
Microwave on High (100%) 14 minutes.
Let sit, covered, 6 minutes.

title: pork chops
directions: Place
pork chops in shallow pan.
Put pat of butter on each pork
chop.
Mix
all other ingredients and pour mixture over pork chops;
sprinkle with brown sugar.	Cook at 375° for 1 hour.

title: linguine salad
directions: Do not add onion or celery.
Slice mushrooms on top, if desired.
This is better made the day before.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in water until done.
Add sugar and Jell-O. Take off heat.
Add pineapple and juice, celery and walnuts.
Pour in 8 x 11-inch glass dish.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix vanilla pudding, 4 cups milk and 3/4 of the Cool Whip. In a separate bowl, mix chocolate pudding, 3 cups milk and remainder of Cool Whip.
Put a layer of graham crackers (about 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick) in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour a layer of chocolate pudding mix, then a layer of vanilla pudding mix 1 to 1 1/4-inches thick.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add other ingredients and fold in egg whites last.
Makes 3 round layers.
Bake at 300° until lightly browned.

title: just cookie
directions: Boil together the sugar and syrup.
Add the peanut butter and mix. Add the cereal and pecans. Spread in a 17 1/4 x 11 1/2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Add sweet milk to finish out the quart.
Add peaches or strawberries; freeze.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Combine cream and mayonnaise.
Fold in horseradish and salt. Yields 3 1/4 cups.

title: death by chocolate cake
directions: Bake brownies as directed on box.
Cool and crumble into walnut-size pieces.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding mixes with milk and sour cream.
Pour over brownies and top with Cool Whip.
Put Heath bars in blender until real fine, then sprinkle over Cool Whip.
Nuts may be added if desired.
Keep refrigerated.

title: jamie's famous cheese plate
directions: You will need toothpicks and serving plate.

title: baked garlic cheese grits casserole
directions: Cook grits.
Stir in cheese, butter and onions.
Pour mixture into a buttered 2-quart casserole pan and let cool.
Blend eggs and milk and pour over grits.
Bake about 1 hour in preheated oven at 375°.

title: beet salad
directions: Layer cabbage and onion in bowl; pour 3/4 cup sugar over.
Do not mix!
Combine oil, vinegar, salt, dry mustard, celery seed and sugar in saucepan.
Let come to a boil.
Pour hot dressing over cabbage and onion.
Do not mix!
Let set in refrigerator for at least 3 hours or overnight.
(Years ago you set it on the cellar floor.)
Mix before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, baking soda and baking powder in large bowl (set aside).
Mix sugars until blended.
Add eggs, margarine and peanut butter to sugars.
Mix thoroughly.
Add flour slowly.
Mix only until batter is smooth.
Place small balls of dough on ungreased cookie sheet, approximately 1 to 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
(For soft cookies, bake approximately 9 to 10 minutes).
Yield depends on size of cookies.

title: nana's wine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except brown sugar, on medium speed for 12 minutes. Spray bundt pan with non-stick spray. Pour 3/4 of batter into pan. Sprinkle 1/3 cup brown sugar. Pour on remainder of batter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45
minutes. "Always tastes it's best the day after."

title: turkey picadillo
directions: In a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, brown the turkey, onion, peppers and garlic powder. Saute until turkey is no longer pink. Drain. Stir in next 6 ingredients. Bring mixture to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 25 minutes. Serve over hot rice.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening together.
Add sugar and eggs. Sift dry ingredients together and add vanilla.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Bake in a 9 or 10-inch tube pan at 325° for about 80 minutes.

title: mocha coffee basque
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Add condensed milk.
Add coffee slowly, stirring constantly.
Add evaporated milk, cinnamon and salt and heat almost to the boiling point, beating with rotary eggbeater.
Add vanilla and serve.
Yields 4 servings.

title: banana apple bread
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, mixing well.
Stir in apple and banana.
Add nuts, if desired.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to mixture, stirring just until blended.
Pour into a greased and floured (or use Pam/Baker's Joy) 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove.

title: chicken salad
directions: Blend together mayonnaise, garlic powder, onion powder and dry mustard. Combine all ingredients. Cover and chill before serving. Store refrigerated. Delicious.

title: christmas puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add salt and cream of tartar and sugar.
Beat until peaks form.
Add flavoring, coloring and chips.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Turn off oven.
Leave overnight.

title: chili
directions: Chop up a large onion and a clove of garlic.
Fry in a deep pan in 3 tablespoons of olive oil.
Add a pound of good ground beef and cook slowly.
When all is brown, put in a can of whole tomatoes and chop them.
Add a chopped green pepper, a good pinch of celery salt, the same of red pepper, cumin, bay leaf, chili powder, basil and salt to taste.
Stir and simmer some more.
Now pour in a can of chili beans; cover and simmer until everything is slightly cooked down and well blended.
Serves 4.

title: easy time holiday squares
directions: Gradually add sugar to butter in large mixer bowl, creaming at medium speed until light and fluffy.
At medium speed add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
At low speed, add flour and lemon extract.
Pour batter into well greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Mark off 20 squares.
Place 1 heaping tablespoon pie filling in center of each square.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hot chicken dinner
directions: Mix together and put in baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Top with almonds.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix salt with vegetables and bury 1-quart cracked ice in mixture.
Cover and let stand 3 hours; drain thoroughly.
Remove garlic cloves.

title: mrs. woodard's buttermilk pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream shortening and sugar together. Add eggs.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with 1 cup buttermilk.
Add lemon flavoring.
Pour into greased tube or Bundt pan and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli to al dente stage.
Rinse in cold water and drain well.
Chop tomatoes in 1/2 to 3/4 inch pieces.
Mix ingredients together, adding miracle mix and mayonnaise; season to taste.

title: butter toffee
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add syrup, sugar and water. Stir constantly, heating to hard crack stage, 290° to 300°.
Pour in 3/4 cup almonds; stir well.
Pour out onto well buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place chocolate on top and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup almonds.
Break into pieces when cool. This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: layered overnight lettuce salad
directions: Break up lettuce; place in serving bowl.
Layer the following ingredients in order: celery, onions, green pepper, green peas, cheese and bacon.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar and spread on salad like frosting.
Be sure to spread dressing all the way to the edge of the bowl so the salad is sealed.
You can top with some reserved shredded cheese and a little bacon.
You can also add sliced hard-boiled eggs either in the salad or use as a garnish. Chill several hours or overnight.
Good for potlucks.

title: fruit dip
directions: Drain juice from pineapple chunks into a large mixing bowl. (Save pineapple chunks for dipping.)
Add cream cheese and marshmallow cream to juice.
Mix all three ingredients until smooth and creamy.
Dip apple slices, grapes, pineapple chunks or any other fruit in dip.
Refrigerate dip until ready to use.

title: sugarless spice cake
directions: In saucepan, boil raisins and water until water is all gone. Add applesauce, eggs, liquid sweetener and oil; mix well.
Blend in baking soda and flour.
Stir in cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla. Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until done.
Cut into small bars.

title: creamy italian dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: no weep meringue
directions: Mix water, cornstarch and sugar.
Cook until thick.
Cool. Beat egg whites until stiff; add to cooled cornstarch mixture and beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: pineapple chicken(diet)
directions: In a small saucepan, combine the pineapple, soy sauce, water, vinegar, mustard and ginger.
Heat until mixture begins to boil. Remove from heat and add sweetener.
Place chicken in a shallow baking dish.
Pour marinade over chicken making sure they are well coated.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 30 minutes.
Add mushrooms; baste chicken and mushrooms with marinade.
Continue to bake, covered, for 15 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes more or until chicken is browned and liquid is absorbed; baste during browning.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: party peanuts
directions: Place all ingredients in sauce pan and boil until liquid is gone.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300 degrees 10 minutes. Remove from oven.
Salt and stir.
Bake 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir good.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Saute onion and celery; add brown rice, Vegaburger, salt and seasonings.
Simmer 5 minutes more.
Steam cabbage leaves for 5 to 8 minutes each.
Put 1/2 cup mixture in each leaf and roll up and place rolled edge down in pan.
Cover with seasoned tomato sauce or 1/2 spaghetti sauce and 1/2 tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot dog macaroni casserole
directions: Cook and drain hot dogs.
Cook and slice hot dogs crosswise in circles.
Combine soup, water, thyme and pepper.
Add tomatoes, hot dogs and macaroni.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes uncovered.
Top with cheese and bake until melted.

title: hamburger eggplant bake
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 6 slices.
Melt oleo in large skillet; saute eggplant until lightly browned on both sides. Remove.
Form meat into 6 thin patties; brown lightly 1 to 2 minutes.
Place eggplant in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan; top with meat patty and sprinkle with oregano.
Pour sauce over all.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Place cheese on sauce; bake 5 to 6 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: low-fat homemade ice cream
directions: Beat Egg Beaters until fluffy.
Gradually add other ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into 6-quart ice cream freezer. Add milk to fill line.
Freeze according to freezer directions.

title: meatball vegetable soup
directions: Blend the ground beef with the egg, salt and pepper.
Cut onions in 1/2-inch lengths and set aside.
Meanwhile, bring broth to boil.
Shape meat into 1-inch balls.
Drop them into broth, along with the onions, celery, carrots, cabbage, tomatoes, tomato juice, rice, bay leaf and basil.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Discard bay leaf.
Stir in soy sauce.
Top each serving with parsley.
Also good served with a dollop of sour cream in each soup bowl.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Wash and sort the peas.
Place them in a saucepan; add the water and discard any peas that float.
Gently boil the peas with the ham hock, pepper and onion, uncovered, until tender, but not mushy, about 1 1/2 hours or until 2 cups of liquid remain.
Add the rice to the pot, cover, and simmer over low heat for about 20 minutes, never lifting the lid.
Remove from the heat and allow to steam, still covered, for another 10 minutes.
Remove the cover, fluff with a fork, and serve immediately.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees to 375 degrees for 1 hour.
Seems better if frozen awhile.
Mmmmm good!

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil first 2 ingredients; add remaining ingredients and pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread Pillsbury crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Press seams together and bake at 375° for 10 minutes; cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add broccoli and simmer 15 minutes.
Add soup, cheese and 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Stir in and melt cheese.
Pour in greased casserole.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Store in air tight container.
Makes approximately 4 Tbsp. (enough to season 1 pound of meat) or the equivalent of 1 package of taco seasoning.

title: weight watchers stew
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook 1 hour.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Place shredded cabbage into a greased roasting pan.
Add browned ground beef, onion, garlic and rice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour 1 can of tomato soup plus 1 can of water over the casserole.
Cover the pan with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook onion and pepper in oil or bacon grease.
Cook hamburger until stands apart, then add onion, pepper, tomatoes, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and salt to taste.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Put layer of rice, layer of hamburger and layer of cheese.
Put another layer of each.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 25 or 30 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour and soda to creamed mixture.
(If you use cornflakes, add 1 teaspoon salt.)
Add crushed potato chips and butterscotch morsels.
Drop by teaspoon on a cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute celery and onion in a small amount of butter or spray. Add the soups, then the chicken. Cook noodles or spaghetti as directed; drain. Place on platter or bowl. Pour the chicken mixture over top and sprinkle with the cheese.

title: spiced tea
directions: Shake all together until well blended.
Store in airtight container.
Add 2 or 3 spoonfuls to each cup of boiling water.

title: zucchini cheese casserole(makes 3 servings.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil zucchini 5 minutes; drain.
(Use liquid in soup.)
Combine eggs, cottage cheese, rice, onion, salt, marjoram and chives.
Place 1/2 zucchini in bottom of a buttered casserole.
Top with 1/2 rice mix, then repeat layers.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: baked sesame chicken
directions: Beat egg with soy sauce.
Combine sesame seed and bread crumbs.
Dip chicken in egg mixture then in crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet or baking pan and drizzle with margarine.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese microwave
directions: Combine in a 3-quart dish all but cheese.
Cook on High, covered, for 10 minutes.
Stir and recover.
Add cheese and cook on 50% power (usually on Medium) for 5 to 8 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir and serve.

title: self-rising biscuits
directions: Blend flour and shortening, then add buttermilk.
Roll out 1/4-inch thickness.
Fold over and roll out again, then cut out biscuits.
Put immediately into 475° oven.
When biscuits begin to brown, remove from oven and put under broiler and brown to desired color.

title: all-in-a-package steak supper
directions: Place steak in center of 2 1/2 foot length of 18-inch foil. Sprinkle soup mix over steak.
Cover with carrots, celery and potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with salt.
Fold foil securely to hold in juices.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours in a 450° oven.

title: easy pink punch
directions: Put sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour drinks and ginger ale over sherbet.
Mash with potato masher or ladle.
Serves 40 to 50.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Pour seasoning and oil over crackers, stirring carefully until crackers are coated well.
Keep in an airtight container (the crackers will dry quickly).

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with raw vegetables.
May be doubled for a crowd.

title: hot beef and cheese dip
directions: Crumble and brown ground beef with onions; drain.
Place meat in crock-pot.
Cut cheese into cubes and put in crock-pot.
Cook on high 1 hour or until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Add green chilies and tomatoes and mix well.
Serve with chips as an appetizer or over rice, toast or tortillas as main dish.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, mixing well.
Refrigerate.

title: mac and cheese primavera
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package. Saute vegetables in margarine until crisp and tender.
Add dinner and oregano.
Mix lightly.
Makes 6 servings.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack quart jars with washed small cucumbers.
Allow 2 medium sized heads of dill for each quart.
Cover with brine.

title: cajun red beans and rice
directions: In a deep pot, bring the beans to a boil; set aside and soak overnight. Drain. Cover with fresh water. Add the parsley, onion, garlic, green onions, celery, pepper and smoked sausage. Add red pepper flakes to taste. Cook on low heat until thick and creamy (2 to 2 1/2 hours). May need to add salt, depending on the sausage. Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: sausage egg brunch(servings:  8)
directions: Add ingredients to sausage and top with grated cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: jiffy pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix 10 minutes (electric mixer).
It is important to mix 10 minutes.
Bake in Bundt or tube pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
When cool, dust with powdered sugar.
Make sure to grease pan.

title: stack cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add molasses.
Mix well; add eggs and mix again.
Add milk.
Combine ingredients; mix well.
Pour batter into six 8-inch well-greased cake pans.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool completely.
Spread filling between layers and on top.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: payday candy
directions: Bring Karo and sugar to a boil and immediately add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over Rice Chex and nuts.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Keep in airtight container.

title: green pepper casserole
directions: Cook green peppers in a small amount of water until tender. Melt butter in saucepan, blend flour and gradually add milk, cook and stir until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Stir in peppers, pour into baking dish and cover with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: mexican cheese spread
directions: In bowl, mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, garlic powder and crushed red pepper.
Spread in bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Spread cheese sauce over mixture.
Mix cooked hamburger and salsa together.
Spoon over cheese mixture.
Cook in microwave 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Put 2 tablespoons cooking oil in baking pan and place in a 400° oven to heat.
Peel and slice eggplant into 3/4-inch slices.
Soak in salted water 15 minutes; drain.
Spread each side with mayonnaise and bread with seasoned bread crumbs.
Place in the heated pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Turn and bake 10 minutes more.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all
together,
then
put in pie plate pan (Pyrex). Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar, oil, sifted flour, salt, cinnamon and baking powder.
Then add vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Grease and flour a 10 x 14-inch or 13 x 9-inch or a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle on top of warm cake (after taken out of pan) 2 tablespoons of sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Cakes looks better if baked in Bundt pan!

title: crab ball
directions: Mix all but cocktail sauce together well.
Shape as desired. Pour cocktail sauce on top and serve with crackers.
Pour extra cocktail sauce on top as needed.

title: sweet potato casserole(the deep south)
directions: Mix all above ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Add topping.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all except 1 cup pecans.
Roll with 1 cup of pecans.

title: orange rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all but the last ingredient together and put in a 9-inch crust.
Add butter on top.
Make lattice strips from crust and place them on top.
Seal the edges.
Sprinkle the top crust with 2 teaspoons sugar.
Cover the edges of the crust with foil before baking.
Bake 45 minutes at 425°.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in oleo.
Set aside.
Heat soups until warm (undiluted).
Add shrimp and sauteed ingredients; mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Line bottom and sides of casserole dish with rice, 1-inch thick.
Pour shrimp mixture over rice; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9-inch square pan.
Beat together first four ingredients in a bowl to make a smooth batter.
Pour over the melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Pour fruit over the batter.
If fruit is unsweetened, sprinkle top with 1/2 cup sugar.
Do not use prepared pie filling, but use regular canned fruits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and center test as for cake doneness.

title: grandmaw's corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs until thick. Add corn. Combine flour, sugar, salt and pepper. Stir milk into dry ingredients. Blend in melted butter. Combine with corn mixture. Beat well. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Pudding is done when knife inserted in middle comes out clean. Serves 5 to 6.

title: apple salad
directions: Boil red hots and water until red hots are dissolved.
Add cherry jello.
Let partly set.
Add apples, celery and nuts.

title: bacon swiss meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine the egg, milk, 1 cup Swiss cheese, 3/4 cup bacon, bread crumbs, garlic powder and onion powder.
Crumble beef over mixture and mix well.
Shape into a loaf in a greased 11-inch x 7-inch x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour or until meat is no longer pink and a meat thermometer reads 160°.
Drain.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bacon.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Let stand for 10 minutes before slicing.
Serves 6.

title: jim's bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Mix all wet ingredients in large bowl.
Combine all ingredients and drop in muffin tins sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen muffins.
Add more honey for sweeter muffins.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Core and slice tomatoes (they can be either green or red). Dip the slices in flour, to which some salt and sugar have been added.
Brown slices on both sides in butter or bacon fat (bacon fat is better) until crisp.
Turn just once.
When brown on both sides, put the slices in a casserole in a warm oven.

title: bats in a bag or rudolph's antlers
directions: Melt chocolate in large bowl in microwave.
Add noodles.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Chill.
Place stickers on Baggies for decoration, i.e., Halloween and Christmas.

title: "heavenly" cookies
directions: Combine 3 ingredients, adding nuts if desired. Roll tablespoons of mixture in powdered sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: eggplant rolls
directions: Per-heat oven to 350°F.
Trim both ends from eggplant and slice into rounds.
Soak slices in salted water for 10 minutes then drain.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown beef and drain off fat. Add soup, salsa,
milk and 1/2 of cheese together. Place Doritos in baking dish and add meat and soup mixture. Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until hot. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: apple crispy
directions: Put the sliced apples in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix the other ingredients and spread over the apples.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring all ingredients to boil except the vanilla on a low heat. Then let boil without stirring until it is at a soft boil stage. Add vanilla.
Cool, beat and then pour into a glass 8 x 10-inch dish.

title: dairy-free thousand island dressing
directions: Measure all ingredients into a large bowl.
Combine with a whisk or hand blender.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant in
bite-sized
pieces;
add
enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook
over kerosene fire for about four weeks at 485°. This will
serve
about
people.
If more are expected, 2 rabbits may be
added; but do this only in case of emergency. Most people don't like hare (hair) in their stew.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Place celery, onion, parsley and whole cranberries on cutting board. Chop fine. In pan, saut all in butter. Stir in bread crumbs, salt, poultry seasoning, sugar and pepper. Stuff into pork chops. Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour; turn pork chops and then bake for 1/2 hour more.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and wet ingredients in separate bowls. Add liquid to dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pans (2). Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When finished, remove from oven and poke holes in each loaf.
Make powdered sugar glaze and pour over each loaf.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and margarine; add eggs.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Put into greased spring-form pan or 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Cut peaches into thick slices and lay on top of batter. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: never fail popovers
directions: Break eggs into 4 cup measuring cup.
Add flour, milk and salt. Mix with spoon well, but some lumps still in dough.
Fill oiled muffin tins 3/4 full.
Place in cold oven, then set at 450° to bake 30 minutes.
Do not open oven until done.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and milk and bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes more (stir constantly).
Take off heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream (also nuts, if desired).
Put in an 8 x 11-inch pan and cool.

title: christmas spiced punch
directions: Boil and simmer first 4 ingredients for 10 minutes and chill. Add wine and juice, chilled. Make an ice ring with orange slices at bottom, the day before; optional. Strain punch base. Pour everything into the punch bowl. Serves 14.

title: cheese and egg sandwiches
directions: Cut half of the cheese into cubes and dice eggs. Mash together the cheese, eggs and mayonnaise. Stir until creamy. Put on bread like sandwiches and cut diagonally. Serve with potato chips.

title: mimi's fruit
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and oranges.
Stir in pudding mix; heat until slightly thick.
Add this to fruit cocktail in bowl. Cut in 3 or 4 bananas to suit taste.

title: orange crush cake
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add orange drink alternately with sifted flour.
Add flavorings.
Pour batter into a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Frost cake when cool.

title: light punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare pudding as directed using skim or low-fat milk.

In a large punch bowl, crumble one angel food cake for bottom layer. Continue layering with 1/2 of the pudding mixture, 1 can of pineapple, 1 can cherry pie filling and 1/2 of the Cool Whip container respectively.
Repeat the above layers and refrigerate. (The recipe can be cut in half for a smaller bowl.)

title: hot sweet onions
directions: In a small bowl, combine honey and mustard.
Sprinkle onions with paprika, salt and pepper.
Place in foil.
Fold foil loosely and seal edges tightly.
Can be cooked on grill, in oven or microwaved (without foil).
However, cook until onions are tender. This is good with steaks.

title: cock 'n bull stew
directions: Combine steak sauce, bouillon cubes, salt, pepper, sugar and hot water in crock-pot; stir well.
Add remaining ingredients except flour; mix carefully.
Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours (high setting 4 hours).

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in a large pan of water until done.
Remove chicken, debone and cut into small pieces.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix sugar, Tang and both kinds of tea.
Add cloves, cinnamon and ginger.
Mix all together thoroughly.
Put 3 teaspoons into a cup of hot water.
Makes a wonderful hot drink on a cold morning or anytime you would like a different hot drink.
Store in tightly sealed container.

title: turtle cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Pour one half of the batter into greased & floured 13 X 9 X 2 baking dish.
Bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 20 - 25 minutes.
Melt and mix together the caramels and Eagle Brand milk.
Spread over the baked layer.
Sprinkle generously with chopped pecans.
Cover with remaining cake batter.
Bake 25 - 35 minutes longer.
Frost with Turtle Cake Frosting (recipe follows).

title: spaghetti with broccoli, pine nuts and parmesan
directions: Steam broccoli for 10 minutes.
Set aside when done.
Cook spaghetti in 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a large wide skillet over low heat.
Saute garlic and pine nuts until garlic is golden color.
Add broccoli and stir until broccoli is heated through.
Drain pasta and toss at once with the broccoli mix.
Add Parmesan and parsley.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: molasses pudding
directions: Mix soda with molasses and add boiling water.
Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients together and combine the two mixtures.
Bake in a greased frying pan or baking dish at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: rice with chilies and sour cream
directions: Cook rice.
Combine rice, sour cream and salt to taste. Arrange half mixture in buttered casserole.
Top with strips of green chilies and strips of cheese.
Layer again and top with butter.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: soup mixture for canning
directions: Chop peppers and carrots.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Can in sterilized jars and seal.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with bananas to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice and zucchini
directions: Fry onion in 3 tablespoons oil until soft, not browned.
Add the peeled and sliced zucchini and the tomatoes, parsley, basil, salt and pepper.
Fry until tender but not soft.
Keep adding enough stock or water to make a loose stock to pour over rice.
If you like it more soupy, add 1 can of chopped tomatoes and cook with other tomatoes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese and ground meat. Brown ground meat.
Drain well.
Pour 1/2 corn bread mixture in skillet.
Add ground meat on top and spread evenly.
Sprinkle cheese over ground meat.
Pour remaining corn bread mixture over cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in a 10-inch skillet.
Serve with green salad.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil
and debone chicken.
Layer chicken and soups (mix soups together first).
Melt margarine and stir into stuffing mix.
Put stuffing
mix
on
top.
Bake
at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: 5 alarm chili
directions: Chop onion, peppers and garlic; saute in a large pot.
Brown ground beef and add to pot.
Saute with chili powder and red pepper for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add chili beans, kidney beans, tomatoes and tomato bisque.
Simmer and add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours or longer.
Serve over spaghetti or with oyster crackers.

title: chinese rice
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in casserole dish.
Cut butter or oleo into small slices and float them on top.
Cover and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
(Stir after 1/2 hour.)

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Spray a 9 x 12-inch pan with Pam (or grease).
Place mixture in pan; bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until brown on the top.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter; mix together.
Add seasoning and mix well.
Make ball and roll in nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Follow directions pertaining to your ice cream freezer for the exact amount of time required to freeze.

title: spicy punch
directions: Place all ingredients in a percolator and let perk.
Serve hot.
Yield:
8 cups.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on box.
Layer or mix the soup, cheese and shrimp.
Add to cooked rice.
Bake about 35 to 40 minutes until bubbly in center.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all but last 2 ingredients well.
Then crumble crackers on top of this.
Then dot the crackers with butter and put in oven. Brown at 350°.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cauliflower, broccoli, grapes, onions and Mozzarella cheese. Combine the mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, sugar and vinegar; pour over vegetable mixture and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Add bacon bits before serving. Transfer to a lettuce-lined bowl. Garnish with grapes if desired. Yield: 15 to 20 servings.

title: aunt fanny's baked squash
directions: Boil squash until tender and drain.
Mash squash.
Add all the ingredients, saving half of the butter.
Melt butter that is left and pour over top of squash mixture you have placed in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with small amount of cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage into a saucepan.
Cook over med-low heat.
Add onion, cook and stir until transparent.
Drain, discarding all but 2 Tbsp. of drippings.
Stir in flour and cook over med-low heat, for about 6 minutes, or until mixture turns golden.
Stir in milk and add seasonings.
Cook and stir continuously until thick.

title: honey-spice glazed spareribs
directions: In a small bowl, combine honey, vinegar, hoisin sauce, oil, aniseed and cinnamon; mix well.
Trim excess fat from ribs and place in a shallow 8 x 12-inch pan.
Pour marinade over and turn ribs to coat.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight, turning once.
Heat oven to 450°.
Remove ribs from marinade (reserve marinade) and place on rack in broiling pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Add peanuts. Drop on wax paper until firm.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Melt butter over low heat in top of double boiler.
Stir in flour, seafood, nutmeg, salt, paprika and sherry.
Beat egg yolks slightly in small bowl.
Add cream; mix well.
Slowly pour egg mixture into seafood mixture.
Cook over hot water, stirring until just thickened.
Serve over toast points, cooked rice or pastry shells.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend together well. Serve.

title: double delicious potatoes
directions: In casserole, cook garlic in oil, covered, on High 1 1/2 to 3 minutes in microwave until garlic browns slightly.
Add onions and potatoes; stir to coat with oil.
Cook, covered, 3 minutes.
Add peppers, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, on High 18 to 20 minutes, until tender, stirring 3 times during cooking.

title: 6-week bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add Crisco, eggs and buttermilk and mix well.
Store mix up to 6 weeks in the fridge. To bake, fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: garden slaw
directions: Toss vegetables.
Heat remaining ingredients to a boil.
Boil 1 minute while stirring.
Toss liquid into vegetables, mixing well.
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, mix first 13 ingredients.
Transfer to a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Dish will be full.
Sprinkle with cheese and French fried onions.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 16 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake cake at 325° for 1 hour and reduce heat to 300° for the last half hour.

title: krout casserole
directions: Brown bacon and onion in large skillet.
Add rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Put into 2 1/2 quart casserole dish. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and nuts together in large mixing bowl.
Let stand about 1 hour, stirring occasionally, so mixture makes its own juice (if apples are not tart, add 1 tablespoon lemon juice). Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well again.
Pour into greased, floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: split pea soup
directions: Boil water and peas for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; set aside for 1 hour.
Stir ham, onion, salt and pepper into peas; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer for about 1 hour.
Stir carrots, celery and potatoes into soup.
Simmer until vegetables are tender, about 45 minutes.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: 5 flavor cake
directions: Cream together margarine, shortening, sugar and flavoring. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each egg.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Then add flour and milk alternately.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Try this sometime with English walnuts.
Also good.

title: summertime lemonade
directions: Place lemonade mix into a 3-quart or larger pitcher.
Add soda and water.
Squeeze lemon and orange slices into pitcher; add squeezed slices to pitcher.
Mix until powdered mixture is dissolved.
Add ice or pour over ice.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs (one at a time).
Gradually add dry ingredients and milk.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured pan and bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325° or until done.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients
in a large bowl, except nutmeg.
Pour into a 9-inch pie crust (unbaked). Sprinkle nutmeg on top. Bake 15 minutes at 425°, then turn oven to 350° and bake 45 minutes more.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Beat together first five ingredients until blended.
Combine and add the remaining ingredients and stir until dry ingredients are just moistened.
Do not overmix!
Spray or butter muffin tins. Fill cups 3/4 full.
Bake for about 25 to 35 minutes at 350°. Makes about 2 dozen muffins.

title: sister loretta's little pizzas
directions: Break up sausage and ground beef with a fork.
Cook together until fat can be taken off.
Cut cheese into cubes.
Remove meat from fire and blend in cheese until it melts.
Cut bread into bite size.
Spread with mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Toast in 400° oven until bread is brown on bottom.
Serve hot.
Can be made night before, toasted as needed.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Saute onion in olive oil until limp.
Add garlic and tomatoes. Cook for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until sauce thickens.
Puree sauce in food processor or blender.
Freezes well.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together and pat into pan.
Bake at 325° until done (firm and lightly browned).
Double the recipe and it makes 3 small pie crusts in aluminum
pans.

title: cheese cake
directions: Save 1 tablespoon graham crumbs for topping before mixing with butter and sugar.
Melt butter.
Mix with crumbs and sugar.
Pat into a 9-inch cake pan.

title: beef and mushroom quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Prick bottom of pie shell, bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove and reduce heat to 350°.
Brown beef, drain and set aside.
In medium bowl, mix soup, milk, eggs, spices and Tabasco sauce.
Add beef, mushroom pieces and cheese.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover edges with foil.
Bake 60 minutes or until toothpick or knife comes out clean.

title: chicken patty bake
directions: Place chicken
breasts,
bone
side
down
in
an
11 x 15-inch Pyrex casserole dish.
(Boneless breasts can be used.) Put a
slice
of
Swiss
cheese on top of each chicken breast. Cover with
the
cans	of
undiluted cream of chicken soup. Melt the margarine
and
mix with the dry Stove Top dressing. (Do not
mix in	the seasoning spice packet included in box.) Spread the crumbs
on	top.
Cover
with foil and refrigerate overnight. Bake for 2 hours in a 275° to 300° oven.

title: polish sausage in sauce(appetizer)
directions: Cook Polish sausage in a little water for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into 1/4-inch chunks.
Mix sauce ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Add sausage chunks.
Serve hot.

title: german bundt pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Sift the 2 sugars together.
Add egg yolks, one at a time; beat until smooth.
Add almond extract.
Add flour and milk to batter; mix well.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Put 2 tablespoons meat on a flour pattie and sprinkle a little of each item and roll up and put in an oblong baking dish, six to seven to a dish.
Make gravy and pour over patties and sprinkle rest of cheese and pour 1 cup of mild taco sauce over.
Bake 10 minutes in microwave.

title: sherry beef
directions: Place uncooked meat in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
(Add Kitchen Bouquet if desired to color sauce.
Add fresh or canned mushrooms, if desired.)
Bake 3 hours in a 325° oven or longer.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: kris kringles
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and Karo in large saucepan; bring to full rolling boil and take off heat.
Add rice cereal; mix well and pat into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let stand.
Melt together the chocolate and butterscotch chips; spread over cereal mixture. When cold, cut into squares.

title: texas hash
directions: Fry meat; season with salt, pepper, garlic or other seasonings.
Drain grease from meat.
Add 1 can stewed tomatoes and 1 can tomato sauce and bring to a low boil.
Add macaroni. Put lid on skillet and let cook until macaroni is soft.
After macaroni is done, add mushrooms, corn and green beans.
Let cook 15 minutes.
Mix up real good.
Put in casserole dish.
Add Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables (frozen), soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onion rings.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: southwest chili
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion.
Cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tomatoes, chilies with liquid, chili powder and cumin.
Bring to a boil.
Add beans with liquid.

title: quick blueberry coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 8-inch cake pan.
Combine Chex, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Add butter.
Mix well.
Sprinkle half over bottom of pan.
Arrange biscuits over crumb mixture.
Top with fruit and then with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine, pecans and brown sugar; pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pork barbecue and macaroni (rice)
directions: Drain juice from pork; cut pork
up and put in pan with barbecue sauce.
Cook on medium 30 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Cook broccoli and onion until onion is done. Mix all ingredients, except corn muffin mix. Add muffin mix and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: nancy's homemade pimento cheese
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Taste to see if seasonings are okay. If not, add a little more.
The consistency should be easily spreadable.
If not, add a little more mayo or dressing.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Pour onto a 15 x 10 x 1-inch cookie sheet.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn this over onto a towel that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll this up like a jelly roll with the towel rolled up with it.
Let this cool for about 1 hour. Unroll and spread filling on it and re-roll.
Let chill for 2 hours before slicing.

title: pralines
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in boiler.
Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Beat lightly; drop on a greased platter.

title: moms spritz cookies
directions: Fill Spritz machine, with your favorite cutter.
Bake 350 degrees 6-8 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar while warm.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix flour, butter and eggs together.
Add oatmeal, sugar and raisins.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook until it forms soft balls. Remove from heat and cool.
Beat well and pour into a buttered pan.
Cut into squares when cool.
Yields 12 squares.

title: tamale pie
directions: Pour milk over cornmeal. Saute onion, pepper and ground beef in bacon fat. When light brown, add tomato juice, salt, sugar, chili powder, corn and juice from the bottle of stuffed olives. Simmer a few minutes.
Add cornmeal mixture and whole olives.
Mix with the hot water and put in greased casserole. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and brown 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: punch
directions: Mix
all ingredients together and refrigerate.	Makes 2 gallons.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill before serving.

title: cocktail smokies
directions: Mix jelly and mustard together and heat in crock-pot or pan. Allow jelly to melt. Add cocktail Smokies and allow to heat.

title: chocolate and peanut butter sandwiches
directions: Beat butter, sugar, eggs and cocoa.
Mix in flour and baking powder.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place on cookie sheet. Butter flat-bottomed glass and dip in sugar before flattening each cookie.
Bake for 8 to 9 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Combine peanut butter, powdered sugar and milk and spread on half the cookies, then press on the rest of the cookies to make sandwiches. Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: skillet supper
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Dredge in flour.
Brown in small amount of fat in skillet over medium heat.
Add vegetables and soup.
Let cook until steam escapes.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer for 40 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In small bowl, beat milk, butter and eggs; combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine with egg mixture.
Stir until just moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon batter into 12 prepared muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bread pudding
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Place bread in baking dish. Mix all remaining ingredients and pour over bread, mashing together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: moon cake
directions: Bring water and oleo to a boil.
Add flour and mix.
Remove from heat and cool to room temperature.
Beat in eggs with wooden spoon.
Will be consistency of pizza dough.
Spread on 11 x 13-inch sheet pan, ungreased.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Cool.
Crust will look like moon craters.

title: turkey gumbo
directions: In a large pot, boil the turkey carcass.
Remove from broth and debone.
Set aside along with any leftover turkey.

title: peanut butter fudgies(no-bake cookies)
directions: Have peanut butter and oatmeal measured and ready.

title: stewed blueberries
directions: Wash berries.
Place berries, water and sugar in pan.
Cook until open.
Mix cornstarch with a little water; add to berries and cook until thickened.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with chow mein noodles or grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly hot. Serves 6 to 8.

title: 10 minute fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil and continue boiling for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool and cut.

title: norwegian slaw
directions: Mix all vegetables which have been chopped and mixed with 3 tablespoons salt.
Let stand 1 hour, then drain.
Mix the sugar, water, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Add to vegetables.
Refrigerate.

title: double chocolate bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In 2-quart saucepan, heat cream, sugar, and milk over medium heat until sugar dissolves, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add chopped chocolate, stirring with wire whisk until mixture is smooth and chocolate melts completely.
Gradually whisk in eggs and vanilla until well combined.
Place bread in shallow 1 1/2-quart or 8-inch square glass or ceramic baking dish.
Pour chocolate mixture over bread. Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top of bread mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes or until set.
Cool 10 minutes to serve warm, or cover and refrigerate to serve cold later.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: holly (christmas)
directions: Melt marshmallows in butter.
Add vanilla, color and corn flakes.
Dip out by teaspoonfuls and form 3 leaves on wax paper. Put 3 cinnamon candies in center of leaves.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Saute bell pepper and onion in butter. Add shrimp and saute until done (pink). Add chestnuts or mushrooms. Stir in cooked rice. Add cream of mushroom and Cheddar soup; stir. Pour in greased casserole dish and bake until cheese is melted, about 10 minutes.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Beat shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add
banana,	then dry ingredients.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Combine lettuce, bell pepper, and boiled egg with some Miracle Whip.
Sprinkle with salt and pour in pickle juice.

title: hrutka
directions: Crack eggs and add milk; beat with eggbeater until thoroughly mixed; add salt to taste.
Put mixture in large saucepan or pot and place in a still larger saucepan or pot filled with water.
This will prevent egg mixture from sticking and burning at bottom of pot as it cooks.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often until mixture pulls away from sides of pot and looks curdled.
Line in large strainer with cheesecloth and strain mixture through the cheesecloth.
Pull sides of cheesecloth together and shape egg mixture into a ball.
Tie very tightly at top with string and hang to let drain for 2 or 3 hours.
Cool in refrigerator.
Unmold from cheesecloth and serve.

title: cranberry pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in pan sprayed with Pam. Sprinkle with salt.
Place 3 chops in greased baking dish. Combine chopped fresh cranberries, honey and cloves.
Spread half of the cranberry mixture over chops in dish.
Arrange the remaining 3 chops on top and pour over the remaining cranberry mixture.
Cover and bake in slow oven at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream sugar & margarine together.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour, spices & buttermilk.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12-15 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: creole black-eyed peas
directions: Combine water, black-eyed peas, onion, bacon, salt and red pepper.
Cook on low heat 2 hours.
Add rice; cook 20 minutes. Stir in shrimp and scallions.
Cook 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: boursin cheese
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add spices and blend well. Chill 12 hours.
Serve as you please.

title: luscious crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crab, in a bowl.
Fold in crab. Put in small casserole dish.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake at 375° until bubbling, about 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers or French bread pieces.

title: fried apple casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in apples.
Pour butter over apples.
Combine sugar, cheese and flour.
Pour over apples. Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and cook until golden brown.

title: coconut crunch delight
directions: In a bowl, combine the first five ingredients. Press lightly into a greased 13x9-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes or until golden brown, stirring every 10 minutes to form coarse crumbs.

title: strawberry, pineapple, banana jello
directions: Mix together all ingredients except sour cream.
Place half on bottom of dish.
Pout sour cream next.
Put rest of jello mixture on top.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage until limp.
Line bottom of dish with crackers. Layer cabbage on top.
Layer onion; continue to layer.
Put 4 pats of butter on top.
Top with more crackers, then cheese.
Mix 1/2 cup broth and 1/2 cup milk; pour to just under top layer.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: noel apple salad
directions: Partially peel apples, leaving some skin on for color.
Then quarter and coarsely chop.
Sprinkle lemon juice on apples to prevent apples from discoloring and toss thoroughly.
In another bowl cut up the dates, cherries and nuts.
Sprinkle apples with sugar.
Refrigerate both bowls of fruit.
Just before serving, mix all together, adding as much sour cream as desired for dressing. Serve immediately.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Dice eggplant and boil in salted water 10 minutes.
Drain well and add other ingredients.
Bake in casserole 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna croquettes
directions: Mix together tuna, egg, oats and milk.
Make into croquette shapes.
Roll in meal and brown in enough oil to brown on all sides (medium heat).

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Place lettuce in a 3-quart bowl.
Fry bacon in 8-inch skillet over medium heat until crisp.
Remove bacon with slotted spoon; sprinkle over lettuce and onion greens.

title: baked scallops en casserole
directions: Crush crackers.
Add to melted butter.
Alternate scallops and crackers in buttered dish.
Pour egg over top.
Season with pepper, onion powder and dill weed, or as desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle sherry over it before serving.
(Could be prepared ahead, then baked.)

title: oyster crackers
directions: Combine dressing, salad oil and dill weed in bowl. Add crackers and gently stir to coat until all oil is absorbed in crackers. Stir for 30 minutes. Store crackers in sealed container.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; cool. Add 7-Up. Pour in 9 x 13 pan. Cool until congealing begins. Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows. When congealed, frost with dressing.

title: jello waldorf salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Add ginger ale and lemon juice. Place in 1 1/2-quart glass container and refrigerate until just slightly thickened.
Remove glass container from the refrigerator and fold in the remaining ingredients.
Return to the refrigerator until thoroughly thickened.
Place a few maraschino cherries on top for decorations, if desired.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Scald cabbage in hot water; drain well.
Mix all ingredients except tomato sauce.
Form small rolls of beef mixture.
Place in cabbage leaves; fold ends.
Roll up and fasten with toothpicks. Place in a buttered casserole dish and pour on tomato sauce. Cover and bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Remove lid 15 minutes before serving.

title: cinnamon-glazed baked apples
directions: Set the oven at 375°. Have on hand a 9-inch round baking dish. Use an apple corer or sharp knife to core the apples. Cut a slice from the bottom of each (so they stand without wobbling) and place them in the dish.

title: italian wine cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks and beat until light. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with wine and mix well. Chill.
Roll out thin on floured board and cut with 2-inch cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets, brush with slightly beaten egg white and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 9 dozen.

title: cherry delight salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Cool.
Add flavoring and pie filling.
Put in 10 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Partially drain pineapple.
Mix with cream cheese.
Spread over gelatin mixture.
Makes 16 servings.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Layer.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown. May add mushrooms.
Only good when hot.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together pumpkin, oil, water and eggs.
Add dry ingredients to pumpkin mix.
Beat until smooth and add nuts.
Bake in 3 greased loaf pans at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: dill bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill weed, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and yeast. Gradually add flour to form stiff dough, beating well after each addition.
Cover; let rise until double.
Knead down dough.
Place in well-greased loaf pan; let rise until double.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix ginger ale, cranberry sauce and pineapple.
Dissolve Jell-O and water.
Chill until set.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes in dish.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and then sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake 10 minutes longer until cheese has melted.

title: no aging candied fruit cake
directions: Set oven at 275°.
Cut and mix fruit in large bowl.
Mix dry ingredients in small bowl.
Add dry ingredients to cut fruit and stir until fruit is well covered.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla, beating well after each addition.
Add the flour mixture and beat well. Roll dough into ball and chill for several hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Remove dough onto floured surface.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Combine all together.
Mix well.
Put in graham cracker crust. Refrigerate and serve.

title: sinfully rich brownies
directions: Double number of eggs called for on box of brownie mix. Use milk or cream in place of water.

title: banana strawberry shake(healthy drink)
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and mix until smooth, about 45 seconds. If too thick, add more milk to taste. Yields one 20 ounce shake.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Add butter to potatoes and beat smooth. Add beaten egg yolks, sugar and flavoring. Stir in milk and fold in beaten egg whites. Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Boil beans.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook in the last 2 hours.
Add sauteed garlic, onions and green pepper, then add ham or cook Eckrich sausage.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with rice and corn bread.

title: baked haddock
directions: Place fish in
the
middle
of large baking dish.
Pour milk over fish.	Put
butter
on
top
of
fish.
Add salt and pepper. Slice an onion and place over fish.
Let fish bake at 300° to 350° heat for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple puffs
directions: Thoroughly mix cream cheese and sugar.
Stir in pineapple. Fill cookies and serve.
Refrigerate leftovers (if there are any).

title: glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil and cook, stirring constantly for 5 minutes. Beat about 1 minute with a spoon.
Pour over hot cake.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water. Let stand 10 minutes. Stir in flour, soda and sugar. Add oil. Mix in well with flour. Add milk and yeast mix. Let stand 10 minutes. Knead small amount and roll out. Bake at 350°. This will keep in the refrigerator to use as you need it. Brush with melted butter and garlic powder.

title: waffles
directions: Beat egg yolks; add milk and flour alternately (baking powder and salt added to flour).
Heat waffle iron until very hot before cooking waffles.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Put 1/2 cup coconut in each pie shell. Combine the eggs and sugar. Add the buttermilk, oleo, dash of salt and vanilla.
Pour mixture into shells over coconut.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked beans extra ordinair
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: strawberry-romaine salad
directions: Combine oil, sugar, vinegar, garlic salt or powder, salt, paprika and pepper. Place in large jar and shake vigorously. Tear lettuce into bite size pieces and combine with strawberries, cheese and nuts. Pour dressing over top.

title: idiot bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water (large bowl).
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Grease a deep bowl.
Put dough in and let rise until double (about 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down and put into two 9-inch pie pans.
Let rise again. When loaves are double, melt 1 stick of margarine and pour equally (and carefully) over loaves.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into crust and refrigerate.
Can be served plain or with a Cool Whip topping.

title: milk pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: celestial chicken(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes with poultry shears.
Combine flour, salt, paprika, Accent, pepper and sesame seed.
Pour cream over meat and let stand for at least 30 minutes.
