Coat each piece with seasoned flour and fry in oil 1/2-inch deep until golden brown and fully cooked (doesn't take long).

title: baked beans(men's favorite)
directions: Use large slow cooker or crock-pot for 4 hours.
Stir every so often or use small roaster pan and bake 3 hours at 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and cook.

title: ground beef hot dish
directions: Brown meat, celery and onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until cheese melts.
Remove from heat.
Slice French bread.
Place on cookie sheets and spread pizza mixture on the slices.
Heat under broiler for approximately 1 minute.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and
pour into two greased pie pans. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
(Good!)

title: chicken 'n' dumplings
directions: Stew chicken (with onions and celery, optional) and remove from broth.
Use 3/4 cup hot broth and stir in shortening.
Add this to flour and mix well to make a soft dough.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13 Pyrex dish. Remove from freezer 30 minutes prior to serving.
Cut into squares for servings.

title: cheesy baked chicken
directions: Crush crackers to make 2 cups.
Melt margarine.
Dip pieces of chicken in margarine; sprinkle with salt and roll in crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add to other ingredients.
Place on floured surface and knead 10 times.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with 2-inch cutter and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let rest 5 or 10 minutes, then bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: strawberry rhubarb squares
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and sugar together. Cut in oleo as you do for pie crust.
Put vanilla into sour cream; add to flour mixture.
Handle as pie crust.
This is very delicate.
Roll out or put over half of batter dropped by spoonfuls over bottom of greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread over pan and up the sides of pan partway.
Pour filling over the dough.
Roll out the rest of dough and put over the filling.
(It will fall apart.) Top with Crumb Filling.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 40 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: golden glow pickles
directions: Peel and scoop out seeds from cukes.
Cook 20 minutes or until transparent.
Jar hot.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry ground beef and onion together. Drain off all the grease. Add taco seasoning; mix well and let cool. Add lettuce, cheese, tomatoes, olives and beans; mix well. Just before serving, add Doritos. Serve with Catalina dressing. Add more raw onions if you prefer.

title: frozen salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Combine Cool Whip with cream cheese mixture.
Fold in fruit and freeze.
(Keeps 1 to 2 months.)

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese and 2 packages of dried beef (chopped).
Shape in two oblong balls and roll in 1 package dried beef (chopped).

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Combine yellow cake mix, except for 2/3 cup, with butter and 1 egg.
Pat cake mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Take 2/3 cup yellow cake mix and combine with syrup, 3 eggs and brown sugar, mixing well.
Pour over prebaked crust and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool, cut into bars and serve.

title: party cups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Combine barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar in bowl.
Add meat.
Line cupcake pan with biscuits (form bowl).
Add meat in biscuits.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: bruschetta
directions: Grill bread slices over hot coals or broil in an oven broiler until golden brown on each side.
Watch carefully.
While toast is hot, rub one side of it with the cut side of 1/2 garlic clove. Arrange the toast on a platter with the garlic side up; brush or drizzle with olive oil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix tomatoes and basil (or other herbs, if desired) and spoon some on each piece of toast.
Salt lightly if desired.
Serve at once.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles; saute beef, onion, garlic, oregano and salt.
Add soup and water, cooked noodles and mushrooms.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade egg substitute
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender or food processor.
Process 30 seconds.
Refrigerate up to one week or freeze in an airtight container up to 1 month.
Yield:
3/4 cup (90 calories per 1/4 cup).

title: copper pennies salad
directions: Drain carrots and cool.
Blend all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add cheese and milk until melted.
Stir in macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles according to instructions.
Rinse and drain. Melt butter in skillet.
Stir in meat and cook.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Fold together noodles, cottage cheese, sour cream and onion.
Put half of this mixture in bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole, then 1/2 meat mixture on it and repeat layers.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream peas
directions: Cook onion with the peas until soft, then drain.

title: * calico beans *
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon drippings; drain and crumble bacon.
Saute onion in bacon drippings until it is transparent.
Thoroughly drain onion.
Drain green beans and lima beans.
Combine green beans, lima beans, pork and beans, kidney beans and their liquid, onion and bacon.
Combine brown sugar, vinegar, garlic salt, mustard and pepper.
Add to bean mixture and mix well.
Bake, uncovered, in 3-quart casserole or 2 smaller casseroles in oven preheated to 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 16.

title: shrimp elegante
directions: Saute onion in butter until brown.
Add cooked shrimp and mushrooms.
Saute and stir until shrimp are pink.
Combine salt, pepper, chili sauce and water.
Add shrimp.
Bring to a boil. Stir in rice.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add sour cream to rice mix.
Sprinkle with parsley or chives.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine with
sugar in large pot.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add	sifted dry ingredients, vanilla and chocolate chips. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.	Cut and cool.

title: medium white sauce
directions: Melt butter or margarine in pan over low heat.
Blend in flour and pepper. Add milk all at once, stirring constantly and cook on high until sauce thickens and bubbles.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
If you cook it too much, the butter will separate and it will be too thick.
To correct this, just add a little more milk and cook quickly, stirring constantly until it bubbles.

title: shrimp pelou
directions: Melt butter and saute vegetables.
Place sauteed vegetables and all other ingredients in a casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°, stirring after 30 minutes.

title: connie's apple cake
directions: Put in bowl the apples, oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla; stir with spoon.
Stir in flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and walnuts with a spoon. Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast with 1/2 teaspoon sugar in the lukewarm water. Set aside while beating eggs lightly.
Add 3/4 cup sugar, the chunks of butter and salt to eggs.
Stir in boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and flour.
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes, then cover and refrigerate several hours at least or overnight.

title: shrimp sausage gumbo
directions: Put salt and crab boil on shrimp; stir and set aside.
In Crisco over medium heat, cook vegetables until crisp-tender; drain. Return oil to pan and heat until moisture is removed.
Brown flour in oil adding bouillon cubes.
Return vegetables to flour mixture; add sausage and few of the shrimp.
Heat through, stirring constantly.
Pour into stew pot; add 2 quarts water and bay leaves. Heat to boil; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook 10 to 12 more minutes.
Add salt to taste.
Serve over rice.

title: christmas bourbon cake
directions: Combine cherries, pineapple, pecans and bourbon.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Drain fruits and nuts.
Reserve bourbon.
Cream butter and sugars together until light.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Sift flour, nutmeg and baking powder together.
Add flour mixture and bourbon alternately to butter mixture, beating well after each addition.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff, but not dry.
Gently fold egg whites into flour mixture. Fold soaked fruit and nuts into batter.
Turn into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 275° for 3 1/2 hours.
Cool and remove from pan.
Wrap in cheesecloth.
Sprinkle with bourbon and store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: glazed carrots with bacon and onion
directions: Cook carrots, covered, in a small amount of boiling water for 15 minutes, or until crisp-tender; drain.
Cook bacon in a skillet until crisp; drain, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings in skillet. Crumble bacon; set aside.
Saute onion in reserved drippings until tender.
Add brown sugar, pepper and carrots; cook until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Yields 4 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 12-inch pan with Pam.
Sprinkle pan with coconut and pecans.
Prepare cake mix according to directions on box. Pour over nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° until done.
Remove from oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: Turn on oven to 350°.
Beat eggs in a 2-quart bowl.
Stir in sugar, syrup and melted margarine.
Stir in pecans.
Bake in center of oven for 40 minutes or until filling is slightly firm. Center of pie may look soft when pie is gently shaken but will become firm when cool.

title: old fashioned potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Put hot mashed potatoes in a roomy bowl.
Add lard or shortening, sugar, salt and mix well. Add eggs, beat well.
Add yeast and milk.
Stir in the flour to make a soft dough.
Place in a greased bowl.
Turn over once to cover top with fat.
Cover.
Set in a warm place and allow to rise until double in bulk.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie crust as directed on package.
Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until clear.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Cool slightly.
Add strawberries, sliced.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: pumpkin mousse pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in large bowl.
Spread in shell and use bottom of spoon to make tips on pie.
Chill at least 5 hours or overnight.
Top with cinnamon, walnuts or carob chips.

title: florida squash delight
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until tender.
Drain. Add margarine and mash.

title: squash pudding
directions: Cook, drain and mash squash.
Combine all other ingredients. Add squash and coconut last.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top before baking.
Bake in 425° oven about 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer until berries begin to pop and mixture thickens.
This will take approximately 15 to 20 minutes with low heat.
Chill.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat the eggs until foamy.
Add the remaining ingredients, except apples and chopped nuts; mix.
Add the chopped raw apples and chopped nuts.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press edges of dough together on a cookie sheet for crust. Brown crust.

title: italian meat sauce
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion in hot oil until almost tender. Add meat and garlic.
Brown lightly.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, for 2 1/2 hours or until sauce is nice and thick.
Stir occasionally.
The longer it cooks, the better the flavors blend together.
Serve over hot spaghetti with Parmesan cheese.
Don't forget to remove the bay leaf.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice and water in microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir and cook 5 more minutes with onion in microwave.
Brown ground beef in skillet with a little water.
Drain well.
After rice mixture is ready, add salsa, browned ground beef and spices.
Cook in microwave 2 more minutes to make sure it is hot and serve.

title: lime punch
directions: Place
Kool-Aid, pineapple juice, 7-Up, Sprite and half of the sherbet
in punch bowl 15 minutes before serving.
When bowl is half empty, add remaining sherbet.
May need additional Sprite.

title: strawberry crush
directions: In food processor, blend frozen strawberries with knife blade. Will look like shaved ice.
Add yogurt and confectioners sugar and blend.
Makes 4 servings.

title: perfect vehicle pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Beat in eggs, 1 1/4 cups milk and butter just until well mixed.
Do not try to get batter completely smooth.
Let batter stand for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: crabmeat english
directions: Melt margarine, add cheese spread, mayonnaise, garlic salt and seasoned salt.
Add crabmeat after all the cheese is melted. Spread over English muffin halves.
May freeze if you want.
Put from freezer to oven broiler.
Broil until golden brown on top. Cut into pie pieces.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain the hamburger and onion. Add tomatoes and beans. Mix in taco mix and Ranch dressing. Simmer for approximately 1 hour.

title: every day ham
directions: Combine honey, mustard and cinnamon. Cook ham about 3 hours at 350°. Brush sauce on ham after 1 1/2 hours. Reserve half sauce to serve with ham. Serves 10.

title: dilly cheese bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until loaf is golden brown.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: no fool pie
directions: Melt oleo in 8 or 9-inch baking dish while oven is heating to 350°.
Set aside.
Combine flour, sugar and 1/2 of the milk.
Stir until dry ingredients are moist.
Add remaining milk and stir until smooth.
Pour batter over oleo.
Do not stir.
Place drained fruit over top of mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly brown and center springs back when touched.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to package directions, then drain.
In large bowl, combine noodles, tuna, pepper, milk, cheese and salt; mix lightly, but well.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings. The green pepper can be omitted.

title: potato yeast rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan.
Cook potatoes, saving water.
Mix sugar, butter and salt; add hot potato water.
Let cool.
Add mashed potatoes and egg; stir.
Mix yeast with warm water; add to mixture.
Stir.
Add flour, a little at a time; mix until stiff, then start kneading rest of flour into it until no longer sticky (about 7 minutes).
Let rise until double.
Punch down; form balls.
Let rise again until double.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Makes about 20.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine cornbread, green onions and bacon bits (I do this the night before).
Refrigerate.
Next day, add other ingredients before serving.
Toss in dressing.

title: caramel banana syrup
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, mix brown sugar, cream, corn syrup and butter. Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil and stir until mixture thickens, about 3 minutes; remove from heat. Stir in vanilla and imitation rum extract. Slice bananas diagonally into syrup.

title: french bread
directions: Mix together yeast, sugar and warm water.
When yeast foams add flour, salt and oil.
Add more flour, if needed, to make a soft dough.
Knead for 10 minutes.
Let rise to double.
Punch down and make into loaves.
When doubled, slash tops with a sharp knife. Bake at 375° about 40 minutes or until it sounds hollow when you rap on it.

title: chicken sticks
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken in blender.
Skin, bone and cut chicken into strips.
Thread on oriental wooden sticks. Marinate 2 plus hours (overnight okay).
Grill 12 to 15 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: whoopie pie
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Sift and add to mixture the next 6 ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: spice cupcakes
directions: Combine sugar, raisins, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, salt, water and shortening in a saucepan and bring to a boil for 3 minutes. Let cool overnight. Add flour, baking soda and vanilla and mix by hand. Pour into 12 muffin tins. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Cut eggplant in 1/2-inch slices.
Grate the cheese.
Combine the tomato sauce, oregano and garlic.
Combine the egg whites and water in a shallow bowl and put the bread crumbs in another.

title: zganci(buckwheat crumbles)
directions: Slowly pour buckwheat flour into briskly boiling salted water. Cook over low fire for 15 minutes without stirring.
With a wooden spoon, make a hole in the center of the flour; allow the water to come over the flour.
Simmer for another 15 minutes. Pour off half of the water and stir in the flour and the remaining water until you get an even mixture.
Melt butter; pour it over the mixture.

Cover the pot and let it stand for a few minutes. With a wooden spoon, pick up portions of the mixture and with a fork, scrape crumbles off the spoon and pile them fluffily into a bowl (do not press down).
The zganci may be put in clear chicken or beef soup or served with pork crackling or browned buttered bread crumbs.
A traditional combination is buckwheat crumbles and sauerkraut.

title: cereal squares
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop into a greased cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 325°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in well-greased Bundt pan. Cook at 400° for 1 hour.

title: saucy florida beans
directions: Saute celery in melted butter until tender.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Gradually blend in milk; cook over low heat, stirring frequently until thickened.
Add cheese and stir in drained green beans and pimento.
Heat thoroughly over low heat.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pineapple walnut stir-fry
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Pour water over walnuts. Let stand 2 minutes.
Drain.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in wok or skillet.
Stir-fry walnuts until brown.
Remove and drain.

title: confetti salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and cool.
Add Italian dressing and Miracle Whip.
Add vegetables to macaroni and dressing.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken wings. Split chicken wings.
Place marinade into large bowl or Ziploc bag.
Add chicken wings. Marinate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn wings over 1/2 through cooking.

title: sherbet squares
directions: Crumble enough macaroons to cover bottom of Pyrex dish (13 x 9 1/2-inch).
Fold nuts in whipped cream; put 1/2 of cream-nut mixture on top of macaroons.
Let harden in freezer.
Spread four kinds sherbet, softened, over cream-nut mixture.
Let harden in freezer.
Put rest of cream-nut mixture on top.
Crumble more macaroons over all.
Freeze.
Soften enough to cut to serve.

title: patio dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Serve with chips.

title: cheese snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into a ball.
Bake on greased pan at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crock-pot chuck roast
directions: Place roast in crock-pot. Sprinkle with dry soup mix. Top with cream of mushroom soup. Cover and cook on high 1 hour and then on low for 8 hours. Slice and serve with mashed potatoes or cooked noodles.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round baking pans or one 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In large mixing bowl, stir together sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla; beat on medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer; stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes for round pans, 35 to 40 minutes for rectangle pan or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar,
butter,
syrup and eggs.
Lay pecans in pie shell. Pour
batter
over
pecans.
Bake	in 350° oven for 10 minutes, 300° for next 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven 325 degrees. Beat eggs at high speed until fluffy in a mixing bowl.

Beat in flour, sugar, and brown sugar, until well blended. Beat in softened butter. Stir in nuts and mini chocolate chips. Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 325 degrees for 55 - 60 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef; drain excess fat.
Add the soup and water; stir ingredients (add more water if dry to moisten).
Drain excess grease.
Cook spaghetti noodles according to directions.
Add spaghetti noodles, ground beef and soup mixture.
Also add Ragu sauce.
Fold ingredients.
Pour ingredients into deep baking dish. Top with Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella.
Add pepperoni (optional).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Grind meat, then combine with stock, garlic, onion, chili powder, cumino and salt.
Cook 15 minutes.
Stir in olives.
Make a stiff mush by scalding cornmeal with boiling water and 1 tablespoon of salt.
Line baking dish with the mush; reserve enough for topping.
Pour the meat mixture into bottom crust. Make a top crust with remaining mush.
Bake to golden brown for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: overnight cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix together the 1/4 cup sugar and 1 tsp. cinnamon.
Place frozen dinner rolls in Bundt pan. Sprinkle brown sugar and pudding over them.
Pour on melted butter, nuts and cinnamon mixture. Cover with foil and towel.
Let set on counter overnight (8 hours).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Invert on serving plate.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar. Add beaten eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add sifted flour, salt and baking soda.
Add oatmeal and walnut meats.
Mix well and form in long rolls.
Chill thoroughly.
Slice 1/4-inch thick. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes a delicious crisp cookie!
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: uncle george's celery casserole
directions: Cut celery into slices, put into a pan of boiling salt water. Cook for 10 to 15 minutes, until tender.
Reserve 1/2 cup of this water, drain the rest.
Make a white sauce by melting the butter; stir.
Add the flour and continue stirring while you add milk and celery water.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Mix with other vegetables.
Combine dressing and sugar and pour over vegetables.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for several hours, stirring occasionally.

title: german style red cabbage
directions: Heat margarine.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Heat vinegar, water and bouillon cubes.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Cover and cook over moderately low heat for about 10 minutes or until cabbage is tender-crisp.

title: sfinge
directions: Put water in pan and heat on stove with butter. When it comes to a boil, add flour all at once, stirring constantly from beginning. Remove from heat.

title: shrimp and crab au gratin
directions: Saute shrimp and crab in butter.
In separate pan melt butter. Add dry ingredients.
Slowly add milk, Tabasco sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Then add cheese until it melts.
Then add shrimp and crab.
Place mixture into casserole dish.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: pecan breaded chicken breasts
directions: In a small saucepan, melt 6 tablespoons butter.
Whisk in 2 tablespoons mustard until blended.	Put butter/mustard mixture in a shallow dish.
Place chopped pecans in another shallow dish.
Dip chicken pieces in butter mixture and then in pecans.
Heat remaining 2 tablespoons butter and the tablespoon of cooking oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook 4 to 6 minutes per side or until browned and tender.
(You can pound thick breasts before breading if desired.)
Remove chicken to serving platter.
Cover with foil to keep warm.
Add sour cream to pan turning heat to low.
Whisk in 1 tablespoon mustard, salt and pepper.
Blend well, heating mixture.
Do not boil.
Pour over chicken breasts and serve.

title: christmas caramel custard
directions: Heat 1/2 cup of the sugar slowly in a heavy metal skillet, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon until sugar melts and turns a light caramel color.
Pour a spoonful of the syrup in each of 5 custard cups and let stand until cooled.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In a small bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until mixture holds stiff peaks.
Add sugar one tablespoon at a time, beating well after each addition.
Continue beating until mixture holds very stiff peaks when beaters are raised.
Lightly fold in peanut butter just until mixed.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Grind Longhorn cheese and pimentos in a meat grinder.
Mix well together.
Put in sweet relish, 1/3 cup or enough to suit you.
Pour a little juice from pimentos into spread.
Add mayonnaise to make spreadable.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Stir all of this together and spoon into a lightly greased baking dish (9 x 13-inch).

title: skillet candy
directions: Melt margarine in heavy black skillet; add dates, sugar and egg. Cook until dates are soft. Remove from heat and let cool slightly; add
vanilla, Rice Krispies and pecans. Form balls when cool enough to handle and roll in powdered sugar; place on waxed paper to completely cool.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk, eggs and sugar in a double boiler.
Cook over simmering water, stirring constantly until mixture coats a metal spoon.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Add raisins, currant or dates, if desired, and mix well.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: strawberry souffl salad
directions: Drain strawberries. Reserve syrup. Add water to syrup to make 3/4 cup liquid. Dissolve gelatin and 1/4 teaspoon salt in boiling water. Stir in reserved syrup and lemon juice. Beat in mayo. Chill until partially set.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off fat.
Mix hamburger, beans and soup together.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with the Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until Tater Tots are golden brown.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour, sugar and brown sugar and mix.
Add butter.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Can be doubled.
Can be frozen.

title: sensational chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Make oatmeal powder by putting 1 cup at a time in blender or food processor and process until powder.
Mix dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Gradually add to sugar and butter mixture.
Mix well.
Add chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts.
Mix.
Place golf ball sized balls on ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
May take longer.

title: african ugali
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil.
In a bowl, stir milk into cornmeal until smooth.
Slowly pour cornmeal paste into boiling water, stirring for a few minutes until mixture thickens.
Cook slowly over low heat (with pan on a heat diffuser if available), stirring briskly once a minute then smoothing over bottom of pan again.
After a while the Ugali will become stiff and pull away from the sides of the pan.
Turn Ugali into a cool damp bowl. With dampened hands, shape into a smooth ball and serve.

title: sour cream-pumpkin pie
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Add pumpkin and sour cream; stir well.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Stir into pumpkin mixture.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 55 minutes, or until set.

title: tempting pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs in small mixing bowl until frothy.
Set aside. Combine sugar and water in 2-quart thick saucepan.

title: cooked corn
directions: Fry side meat.
When done, remove meat and cool drippings. Add corn, salt, pepper and enough water to cover corn.
You may add more water to make the corn soupy when it is done (or milk is even better). Stir flour and water to make a smooth mixture and add to the corn.
Cook for a few minutes.

title: easy oven roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with salt and pepper and place in a Dutch oven. Combine soup and wine, blending well; add onions, mushrooms and capers.
Pour over roast.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours for medium-well doneness.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: jello topping
directions: Mix and frost jello.

title: chili beef soup
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in Dutch oven until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in sauce mix, water, beans (with liquid), corn (with liquid), mustard, salt, pepper and tomatoes (with liquid).
Break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes.
Stir in margarine.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients at low speed.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: haley's oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in large skillet.
Boil 2 minutes.
Take off heat, let set 4 minutes.
Add raw oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until all oats are completely coated. Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.
Serve when cooled.

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning according to package directions.
Add refried beans and hot sauce.
Cook for 15 minutes on low setting.

title: old fashioned pot roast
directions: Bake at 300° until done and tender in covered ovenproof cookware.

title: bavarian congealed salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in water over low heat. Add jello.
When it gets thick like jelly in refrigerator, add pineapple, nuts and cream.
Stir together.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Serve (using ice cream scoop) on lettuce leaves.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in greased baking dish.
Place chicken on broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice in bowl.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tomato ruff
directions: Chop all vegetables in small cubes.

title: corn salad
directions: Chop ingredients and mix with drained corn.
Pour dressing over all and mix well.
Refrigerate for several hours before using.

title: quick brown bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: In a large pot, bring water, sherry, salt, curry powder, onion and celery to a boil.
Add chicken and cook until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken.
Reserve broth.
Remove chicken from bone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook rice according to package directions, using reserved broth instead of water and butter. Combine chicken, cooked rice, mushroom pieces, sour cream and mushroom soup.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with almonds and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: "one pot" dinner(for crockpot)
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain off fat and put beef in crockpot. Brown bacon and onions; drain off fat. Add bacon, onions and remaining ingredients to crockpot. Stir together well. Cover and cook on low 4-9 hours. If using a 2 qt. pot, reduce recipe by half. Yield: 8 servings.

title: italiano spinach cups
directions: Thaw spinach.
Squeeze dry.
Mix in Ricotta, Parmesan, onion, oregano, salt and egg.
Line greased muffin pans or custard cups with cooked crepes (recipe in Breads, Rolls & Pastries).
Sprinkle pepperoni in bottom of each.
Spoon about 3 tablespoons cheese-spinach mixture into each crepe cup.

title: kay's cookies
directions: Mix cake mix with melted butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Take half of the mixture and pat into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Grease a large casserole dish.
Pour pie filling into dish. Sprinkle with dry cake mix, then nuts.
Melt margarine and pour over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be served warm with ice cream or whipped cream.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan. While hot, stir in egg, oleo, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Stir until well mixed. Spread evenly.

title: gotta have some lasagna
directions: Scramble cook ground round.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Place 1/4 of meat sauce in bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cook 13 noodles as per box directions.
Cover first layer of meat sauce with 4 noodles, then add 1/4 of the meat sauce, 1/3 of the pizza cheese.
Beat Ricotta cheese and egg together and add 1/3 Ricotta/egg mixture to baking dish.
Be sure to spread each layer evenly.
Repeat layering process, alternating direction of noodles.
Top last layer with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; uncover and bake another 15 minutes. Let stand about 10 to 15 minutes and serve.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice together.
Stir in other ingredients and pour into two 9-inch graham cracker pie crusts.
Chill and serve.

title: corn pudding supreme
directions: In a mixing bowl, blend cream cheese, eggs and sugar.
Add all of the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 x 2 in. baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45-50 minutes or until set.

title: peanut creme pie
directions: In food processor, chop peanuts and set aside.
In food processor, chop peanut butter morsels.
Heat water and Amaretto in a glass dish in microwave oven.
Dissolve sugar and salt into water/liqueur mixture.
Start food processor and while peanut butter chips are whirling around, pour in hot mixture until morsels dissolve.
Slowly reduce speed, whirl in egg until well blended.
Cool slightly.
Pour into mixing bowl, fold in nondairy topping until well blended.
Sprinkle 1/2 of chopped nuts over bottom of crust.
Spoon in creme filling.
Garnish with remaining peanuts.
Chill until firm.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Add butter, sugar, milk, egg and vanilla.
Beat until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Stir in oats.
Roll out on lightly floured board or canvas to 1/2-inch thickness.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: In oblong Pyrex pan, mix for crust the flour, melted butter, brown sugar and crushed pecans.
Pat into pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let crust cool to room temperature.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix
flour, sugar, baking powder, egg, milk and cooking oil. Dip
fritters;
deep
fry
about 1 1/2 minutes per side. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: easy meatballs and sauce
directions: Roll in 1-inch meatballs.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350° on cookie sheet.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown crumbled sausage.
Place bread in pan; brush cubes with butter.
Sprinkle half cheese, then sausage alternately over bread. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over ingredients in pan (do not press down on bread).
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: island carrots
directions: Reserve pineapple tidbits.
Combine juice and the next 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in pineapple; continue to cook 5 minutes.
Stir cornstarch and water mixture into carrots; stir until thickens. Remove from heat.
Place in serving dish; garnish with nuts. Makes 8 servings.

title: tuna mac
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Drain; add cheese and stir until cheese is melted. Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat Cheddar cheese and cream cheese with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add juice, bell pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce and ground pepper.
Mix well.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: slush
directions: Freeze ingredients.
Serve 1/2 glass of slush with 1/2 glass of 7-Up soda.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl and make a well. Add oil, eggs, water, and pumpkin. Mix well and put into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. If top seems too moist, return to oven. Yield: 3 small loaves.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, egg yolks, sugar, vanilla, salt and butter. Thoroughly fold in egg whites.
Put in a baking dish and cover with topping.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Drain shrimp and chop.
Mix all ingredients and form into ball.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: rosa's brown bread
directions: Put dark flour in first.
Add enough white flour to form a dough.
Knead 15 minutes.
Let rise once.
Shape into loaves.
Bake with a can of water in the oven at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Makes 6 round loaves.

title: pumpkin ice cream dessert
directions: Mix gingersnaps, margarine and brown sugar.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze 15 to 20 minutes, then spread 1/2 gallon vanilla ice cream on crust and freeze.
(Thaw ice cream while making crust.)

title: frozen ice cream bar
directions: Combine brownie mix, hot water, oil and egg. Beat 50 strokes. Bake in a buttered 9 x 13 pan at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Let cool. Prepare filling. Mix ice cream and peanuts. When crust is completely cool spread this on. Cook slowly the powdered sugar, chips, milk and butter for about 8 minutes. Add vanilla. Cool. Pour over bars and freeze until firm. Serves 24.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: special cottage cheese loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and put in a shallow greased pan to bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Mix corn flake crumbs with salt and pepper.
Cut veal into serving size pieces.
Sprinkle crumbs over veal.
Pound both sides with meat mallet.
Cook garlic in frying pan until brown.
Add veal.
Cook thoroughly until brown.
Remove veal to platter.
In small frying pan, cook mushrooms; add condensed soup and lemon juice.
Bring to boil.
Pour sauce over veal.
Serves 6.

title: twyford lodge stew
directions: Cut the meat into slices.
Melt the butter in a saucepan and fry the meat with chopped onions, stirring occasionally.
Add the stock or water and seasoning and simmer for 1 hour.
Lift out the meat and add the shredded cabbage and potatoes.
Add more stock, if needed.
Place meat on top of vegetables and braise until potatoes are tender.
Serves 6.

title: meatza pie
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients; line pie plate.
Spread 1/2 can tomato sauce over meat.
Sprinkle the oregano on sauce.
Put grated cheese on top of mixture.
Add the mushrooms, onions, tomatoes and bell pepper (whatever desired).
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese; bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Sift together cocoa and sugar.
Cream butter and part of the sugar-cocoa mixture, then add vanilla and 1/4 cup milk.
Add remaining sugar-cocoa mixture and milk; stir to desired consistency.

title: whole wheat waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients; gradually add egg yolks and milk.
Beat on low speed; add oil.
Batter will be very thin.
Beat hard for a couple of minutes, then fold in beaten egg whites.
If recipe is doubled, add only 3 eggs.

title: casserole compote or curried fruit
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart casserole while oven is heating. Remove from oven
and
stir
in
flour
and curry powder.	Add fruit and stir
gently.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and ginger. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
May be prepared in a large boiler on top of stove.
Serve with your dinner.

title: irish stew
directions: In a 4-quart microwavable casserole, arrange lamb, carrots and potatoes forming 3 separate layers.
In bowl, combine 2 cups hot water, soup mix and bay leaf.
Stir together until well blended. Pour mixture over potatoes.
Cover with lid.
Cook in microwave oven at High for 10 minutes and at Low for 70 to 75 minutes.
Stir twice.

title: call it whatever you please!
directions: Slice the tomatoes and onions and put in layers.
Sprinkle on the salt and let remain overnight. Rinse well. Chop fine.
Put in kettle and cover with vinegar.
Add the sugar, cloves, cinnamon and allspice.
Stew slowly for about 1 hour.
Bottle while hot.

title: breakfast drink
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Blend and serve.

title: refrigerator candy
directions: Bring to boil all ingredients.
Boil over low heat for 5 minutes.
After ingredients start to boil rapidly, remove from heat and add Hershey bar, chocolate and marshmallows.
Mix thoroughly and pour into pan.
Let set in refrigerator 12 hours before cutting into squares.
You can add nuts, if desired.

title: ham rolls
directions: Cook asparagus spears as directed on package.
Drain.
Wrap each ham slice around 2 or 3 asparagus spears.
Place in ungreased baking dish.
Mix soup and water; pour over ham rolls.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, until bubbly for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Butter a 10-inch spring-form cake pan.
Crush 3 graham crackers and sprinkle on bottom of pan.
Cream sugar, cream cheese and vanilla with mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat.
Fold in sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn off oven and let stand 45 minutes in oven.
Top with your favorite pie filling (cherry or blueberry).

title: swiss green beans
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Stir in flour.
Add milk and seasonings and cook until bubbly.
Stir in Swiss cheese.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan (or grease).
Put already made stuffing down the middle (leave exposed).
Put chicken breasts down sides.
Cover chicken only with soup, milk, parsley, salt, pepper and thyme (mixed together) and pour over the chicken (not stuffing).
Sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes more. Serves four.

title: play dough
directions: Mix the dry ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Add oil, water and food coloring.
Cook until the mixture pulls away from the sides of the pan.
Immediately knead dough slightly.
Let cool slightly, then store in an airtight container when not in use.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Bake the 2 pie shells and cool.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into shells.
Chill 2 or 3 hours before serving.

title: old fashioned stack cake
directions: Cream shortening with molasses.
Add beaten egg.
Mix all dry ingredients and add with milk.
Beat to a stiff dough.
Roll out to thickness of pie dough.
Cut out with a scalloped pie pan. Place rounds of dough on a cookie sheet and bake 12 to 15 minutes. Put together with sweetened well flavored applesauce.
Makes about 9 layers.
Let set a few hours before serving.
May use apple butter.

title: crunchy broccoli salad
directions: Mix ingredients to make dressing.
Refrigerate overnight.
At serving, toss dressing on raw vegetables.
Serve.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops; season and transfer to shallow baking dish. Place 1 tablespoon brown sugar on top of each chop.
Add a slice of lemon to each chop. Combine catsup and water; pour over all. Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: blotkake with marzipan cover
directions: Beat egg yolks, sugar, water and extract until thick.
Sift flour, cornstarch, baking powder and salt and fold into egg mixture.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until very stiff; fold into mixture.
Bake in ungreased 9-inch spring-form pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peppermint candy
directions: Melt chips in double boiler and stir in broken peppermint candy and extract.
Spread on cookie sheet and let harden.
After it has set up, break into pieces.

title: salmon loaf casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into baking dish that has been buttered.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tofu and chicken (or pork)
directions: Cut chicken and tofu into cubes.
Shred green onion into strips, chop garlic and grate ginger.
Stir-fry chicken in hot oil for 10 minutes, or boil in water.
Add tofu, water, green onion, and spices.
Cook uncovered until heated through and most of the water has evaporated.

title: vegetable soup with vermicelli
directions: In heavy 6-quart casserole or soup pot, saute the onions in oil until soft.
Add the garlic, red peppers and carrots.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add the potatoes and stock; simmer until potatoes are almost tender.
Add green beans and zucchini; simmer 5 minutes. Stir in vermicelli and continue cooking until vermicelli is al dente.
Season with salt and pepper; sprinkle with parsley. Serve piping hot.
Serves 10.

title: applesauce nut bread(1 loaf)
directions: Turn oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8 x 4-inch loaf pan. Sift together dry ingredients in medium bowl.
Stir in walnuts with wooden spoon.
Combine egg, applesauce and oil; mix well. Add to dry ingredients, stir with wooden spoon just until blended. Spread batter with rubber scraper into prepared loaf pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Set large pot of water on to boil.
Cook rotini accordingly and then drain.
Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine all remaining ingredients and toss gently.
Add cooled rotini and toss gently to mix.
Serve immediately.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and corn syrup to soft ball stage using medium heat (about 20 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered cake pan.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: frankfurter-cheese(makes about 1 cup)
directions: Combine
cheese and milk in top of double boiler.
When cheese is melted, add frankfurters and mustard.
Mix well.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans together and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan or dish. Fix cake mix according to package directions and pour over coconut and pecans and mix together. Melt margarine and mix with cream cheese and sugar. Stir this batter with knife through the top of the cake mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and process until smooth. This thickens quickly.
It should be used as soon as it is cool. This makes the equivalent of 1 can of Eagle Brand milk.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix
together
sugar,
flour,
nutmeg,
beaten
eggs and melted butter.
Pour over rhubarb in pie crust and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: rhubarb crumble
directions: Mix together.
Press 1/2 of mixture into 9-inch pan.
Make fruit mixture.

title: grandma lucy's salad mold
directions: Cook gelatin according to directions (microwave is okay).
Add other ingredients to gelatin mix in a 1 1/2-quart mold. Refrigerate until firm.
Use as a dip with crackers or fresh veggies.

title: crabmeat-vegetable pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie pan (can also be made in a 2-quart casserole dish).
Combine the first 4 ingredients in pie pan.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth; pour over crabmeat.
Bake for 35 minutes, or until golden brown. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add sour cream.
Add vanilla and Cool Whip.
Use large bowl.
Alternate layers of pudding, bananas and wafers.
Cool at least 4 hours.

title: crab meat au gratin
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until tender (about 15 minutes) on medium heat.
Add flour and blend well; then add milk and 1/2 can water.
Beat in the egg yolks and seasonings.
Cook over low heat about 5 minutes.
Add crab meat.
Put in a greased casserole dish; top with cheese.
Bake on 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry yum yum dessert
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to directions; add vanilla and fold into the cream cheese mixture which has been creamed with the sugar until dissolved. Melt butter and mix in graham cracker crumbs for the crust. Press half crumb mixture in bottom of large baking dish. Spread with 1/2 the cream mixture. Top with cherry pie filling. Cover cherries with remaining half of cheese/Dream Whip mixture. Cover with remaining half of the crumbs. Chill overnight. Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Mix dry ingredients with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Raise to 325°.
Bake 1 1/2 hours until done.

title: open face tuna and cheese sandwich
directions: In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, mustard and lemon juice; stir in tuna and celery.
Cover toasted bread slice with pickle slices, then tuna mixture.
Top with cheese.
Broil 4 inches from source of heat until cheese melts.

title: creole rabbit
directions: Dry rabbit and place in bowl.
Mix salt, pepper, cayenne, garlic, 1/4 cup onion and vinegar and pour over rabbit.
Cover bowl and marinate overnight in fridge.

title: ham and broccoli strata
directions: Cut bread into small cubes.
Layer bread cubes, broccoli and ham in a buttered 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine eggs, milk, onion, mustard and cheese; stir well.
Pour over bread cubes, broccoli and ham; cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Garnish with parsley, egg slices and paprika, if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: waldorf bagel
directions: In small bowl, combine cream cheese, celery and walnuts. Spread half of bagel with cream cheese mixture.
Spread other half with apple butter.
Sandwich together and cut in half or into quarters.

title: fresh strawberry pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil in pan.
Turn off heat and add cornstarch.
Cook on medium until it appears to be partly clear and add lemon juice and food coloring.
Cool, then spoon part of mixture in shells of the pie crusts.
Place strawberries in shells and pour rest of mixture over the strawberries.
(Wash strawberries before and make sure they are dry.)
When cool, top with Cool Whip or other topping.

title: doug's sunday scones
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut butter into flour until it resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in egg and enough milk so dough leaves side of bowl.
Knead dough lightly 10 times on lightly floured surface.
Pat out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into diamond shapes with a sharp knife.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve hot with butter and jam.

title: old-time pound cake
directions: Beat well egg yolks, butter and sugar.
Beat egg whites until foamy, but not dry.
Fold in with eggs, butter and sugar mixture. Add flour a cup at a time; add vanilla and salt.
Spray baking pan with Pam.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of hot water.
Pour in blueberries and pineapple (undrained).
Let set until congealed.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in quarters and shake in bag of sugar mix. Drop in tube pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar good, then add rest of ingredients. Pour in can;
add
gallon
of
milk.
Stir	so it's mixed well, then turn freezer on.

title: yeast dough
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening and egg. Dissolve yeast in water and add to flour mixture.
Knead until smooth.
Roll and cut.
Make cloverleaf rolls.
Can be kept in refrigerator up to 1 week.
Raise for 1 hour, then bake at 400° until golden brown.
Makes 2 thick crusts.

title: indian pudding
directions: In saucepan, combine milk and molasses; stir in corn meal. Cook and stir until thick, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat. Combine egg, sugar, butter, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Gradually stir in hot corn meal mixture.
Bake in a 1-quart casserole uncovered at 300° about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve warm in individual dish with small scoop vanilla ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: brownies
directions: Blend butter and cocoa.
Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar and eggs to butter mixture.
Fold in the flour, vanilla, salt and nuts.
Pour into 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mint candy
directions: In mixing bowl, cream the cheese until real soft.
Add food coloring and flavoring; mix.
Gradually add confectioners sugar; mix until this resembles pie dough.
Pinch off an amount the size of marble; roll in granulated or confectioners sugar.
May be left as they are or can be pressed into a mold and turned out onto wax paper.
You may add any type of flavoring and same type of food coloring to have any flavor you want.

title: spinach dip
directions: Whip in blender or mix well by hand.
Serve with crispy fresh vegetables of your choice.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream oleo until light and fluffy. Continue creaming while adding finely grated cheese.
Sift together flour, salt and chili powder.
Turn mixer to low speed and gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Put through cookie press, using star tip, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Cut into desired length and remove from pan immediately. When cool, store in airtight container.

title: grandma's cobbler
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and add fruit. Mix 3/4 cup sugar, butter, milk, salt, flour and baking powder like a cake batter. Spread over top of fruit. Mix 1 cup sugar, salt, cornstarch and cinnamon together; sprinkle on batter. Pour 1 cup boiling water over sugar mixture. Bake 1 hour at 375°. Place baking sheet under pan as this may boil over in oven.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Mix with all remaining ingredients, except crackers and butter.
Top with cracker crumbs and drizzle butter over the casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, uncovered. Serves 12.

title: myrtle thurens frosting
directions: Measure all ingredients into large bowl.
Mix on medium speed for 3 minutes, then mix on high speed for 5 minutes.

title: strawberry daiquiri
directions: Mix Barcardi rum and strawberry mix in blender with crushed ice.
Add rum to taste.
Garnish with strawberries.

title: quick fudge sundaes
directions: Mix chocolate and milk in saucepan.
Heat slowly, stirring to blend.
Beat in Marshmallow Creme until blended.
Serve cool or warm over ice cream.
Makes 2 cups.

title: best broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Cook rice ahead of time.
Drain broccoli.
Mix with the other 3 ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute onions in oil.
Add ground beef and brown.
Drain grease.
Add chili powder.
Mix well.

title: vegetable meat loaf
directions: In large mixing bowl combine all ingredients.
Mix to desired firmness.
Shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chile-cheese dish
directions: Melt margarine in 9-inch round pan.
Beat eggs lightly.
Add blended flour and baking powder.
Add melted margarine, green chilies and cheese.
Mix and pour into pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven to 350° and bake for 15 to 20 minutes more. Freezes well.
Thaw and reheat at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be cut into cubes and served as an appetizer.

title: potato lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
In large bowl, combine eggs, bread crumbs, salt and pepper; mix thoroughly. Stir potatoes and onion.
Pour into buttered shallow 3 cup baking dish.
Top with bacon and cheese.
Dust with paprika.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serves two.

title: cheddar-spinach pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Toss cheese with flour.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Add cheese mixture and spinach; mix well. Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Cook 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 8 servings.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Blend cheese and margarine until smooth; add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, chives or onion and pimento; mix well.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles; seal perforations with your fingers.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull four corners of dough to center of mixture and seal.
Brush top with melted margarine; dip in 3/4 cup crushed, seasoned croutons (can use bread crumbs.)
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Rub meat well with dry mustard.
Heat beef broth, wine vinegar, pepper, salt, poultry seasoning, bay leaf and garlic. Pour over meat.
Refrigerate for several days, turning often. Drain, pat dry.
Brown in fat in Dutch oven. Pour marinade over. Cook 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 300° (meat thermometer for desired doneness).
Thicken gravy with cornstarch.
Serve with potato dumplings and red cabbage.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Mix cheese, crumbs and seasonings.
Dip chicken pieces in butter then coat with cheese mixture.
Place in a greased 15 x 10 x 1 inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cooked through.

title: zucchini cake(a moist cake similar to carrot cake.)
directions: Cream eggs and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add oil and mix well. Sift dry ingredients together.

Add into egg mixture by thirds, alternating with the crushed pineapple. Fold in remaining ingredients. Pour into 3 well-greased and floured loaf pans or a tube pan such as an angel food cake pan or bundt pan.

title: chocolate chip cookies(cooking for a crowd)
directions: Split dates in half with chunky peanut butter and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 1 1/2-quart loaf pan and bake 45 minutes in a 375° oven.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Very good.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into eighths.
Add onion, salt and water.
Cook together until tender; drain.
Add other ingredients and put in large baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
You may substitute 1 can Cheddar cheese soup and sprinkle some cheese on top.

title: date bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add hot water, eggs, dates, nuts and sifted flour; beat well.
Bake in a 275° oven for 45 minutes in a 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: jack mccarthy's crabmeat burger
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spread on toasted hamburger buns and brown under broiler.
This mixture can also be spread on toast points and served as a cocktail hors d'oeuvre.

title: homemade mints
directions: Blend cheese and flavoring with fork. Add coloring, one drop at a time. Mix in sugar.
Shape into balls or press into molds.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Place nuts and coconut in bottom. Pour cake mix into pan.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix vegetable oil, sugar and egg, then add molasses, flour, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Mold into small balls, then roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 1-inch apart.
Flatten ball out slightly and bake 10 minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill.
Serve with dollop of sour cream and croutons.
Yield: 2 to 4 servings.

title: macho con queso
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off the fat.
In a crockpot combine the cooked ground beef, cheese, and canned soup.
Cook until the cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Add the dry onion mix and picante sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Add milk to desired consistency, but still relatively thick.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cut cheese into pieces.
Do not drain corn.
Combine all ingredients in a large casserole.
Bake uncovered 1 hour at 325°. Stir twice during baking.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Mix tapioca pudding, orange and lemon jello together.
Add 3 cups water and cook until it boils and thickens.
Cool, put in oranges and cool whip.

title: supper in a dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a frying pan.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: rio grande onion pie
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and 4 tablespoons butter in a 9-inch pie plate. Mix with a fork. Spread crumbs and press firmly to form a crust.
Place remaining butter in a skillet.

Add onion and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until tender. Transfer to pie shell. Combine eggs, cream, salt and pepper in small saucepan. Stir over medium heat until hot, but not boiling.
Pour over onion.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lazy daisy muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add milk alternately with dry ingredients, which have been sifted 3 times (beginning and ending with the dry ingredients).
Add vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full and bake in a moderately hot oven (400°) for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Layer first 5 vegetables in 2-quart casserole and sprinkle with cornstarch, sugar, margarine, salt and pepper.
Pour tomatoes over top, cover and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick and easy fruit salad
directions: Mix strawberries, fruit cocktail, oranges and pineapple together.
Chill.
Add bananas right before serving.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in dish and top with some of the cheese.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy strawberry jam
directions: Stir strawberries and sugar thoroughly in large bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mix fruit pectin and water in small saucepan.
Bring to boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling and stirring one minute.
Stir pectin mixture into fruit mixture.
Continue stirring three minutes.
(A few sugar crystals may remain.)
Fill plastic containers to within 1/2 inch of tops; cover.
Let stand at room temperature 24 hours.
Jam is now ready to use.
Store in refrigerator or freeze extra containers.
Thaw in refrigerator. Makes about 5 (1 cup) containers.

title: dressing
directions: In bowl, mix together all the soup and water.
Heat thoroughly. In large bowl, pour dressing mix and butter.
Mix well.
Add soup mixture.
Boil onion and celery in water until they are tender. Pour in dressing mixture.
Add cut up eggs, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
If mixture is too thick, add more water.

title: bulls eyes
directions: Mix melted margarine, peanut butter and confectioners sugar; shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Chill at least 30 minutes, overnight if possible.
Melt chocolate chips in microwave.
Drop balls in and remove with fork.
Set on rack to cool.

title: tomato salad
directions: Toss tomatoes, green pepper, onion and cucumber in large bowl. Bring rest of ingredients to a boil.
Cook 1 minute and toss with vegetables.
Chill (preferably overnight, but at least 4 to 6 hours).

title: velveeta salsa dip
directions: Microwave Velveeta and Pace picante sauce in 1 1/2 quart bowl on High for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted, stirring after 3 minutes.
Stir in cilantro.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or vegetable dippers.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Heat margarine, brown sugar, syrup and salt in saucepan and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn and pecans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: doritos casserole
directions: Boil chicken; drain and chop.
Mix soup and salsa in bowl. Layer Doritos, chopped chicken, salsa mixture and cheese, in that order, in a casserole dish.
Repeat until all is used. Bake at 350° until hot or cheese is melted.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add green and red pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Remove vegetables with slotted spoon; set aside.
Add chicken and oregano to skillet. Cook 4 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink in center, stirring occasionally.
Return vegetables to skillet.
Add water. Season with salt and pepper, if desired; cover.
Continue cooking 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Meanwhile, warm tortillas following package directions.
Fill tortillas with chicken mixture; serve with guacamole, if desired.

title: chocolate puffs
directions: Beat egg whites until they hold straight peaks.
Sift powdered sugar (after it's measured).
Add to egg whites a little at a time; fold in graham cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup nuts.
Melt chocolate chips and cool slightly; add to other ingredients.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake in 325° oven about 12 minutes.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Put ingredients in a large, shallow bowl or pan.
Put boneless chicken breasts in marinade.
Poke holes in chicken breasts with a fork.
Turn occasionally.
Marinate for 6 to 7 hours or overnight. Put on grill and cook until chicken is done, turning often. Great served with rice and salad.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and whip.
Add other ingredients, except paprika. Pour into quart casserole.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients to 240°.
Put in peanuts and cook to 300°.
Add in this order:
salt, vanilla, butter and baking soda. Stir quickly and pour 1/2 into one cookie sheet and the other 1/2 on the other cookie sheet.
Make sure the cookie sheets are buttered real good.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl (except juice from pineapple and cherries) and mix.

title: original pasta salad
directions: Mix vinaigrette dressing blend with vinegar and oil.
Dump into large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs, flour, salt, extract and syrup.
Stir well and add nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until filling is firm.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Place oil and butter in shallow cooking pan (jelly roll pan is perfect).
Put in heated 375° oven to melt.
Set aside.
In large paper sack, combine flour and seasonings.
Roll chicken pieces, 3 at a time, in melted oil-butter mixture; drop in sack and shake to cover.
Place on dish or waxed paper.
Place chicken in pan, skin side down.
Bake for 45 minutes; turn and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer or until top crust begins to bubble.
Serve hot or cold, but crust texture is better if chicken is not refrigerated before eating.
Pan drippings make good gravy for mashed potatoes. Serves 4 or 5.

title: easy basic cream pie filling
directions: Use a heavy saucepan (large).
Mix milk and eggs together in your saucepan, then mix sugar and cornstarch together and add to milk and eggs.
Stir constantly until mixture thickens and boils up a little bit.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine, vanilla and food coloring.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: banana nut bread(shared by connie reimold)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add soda to buttermilk. Mix well.
Combine with creamed mixture.
Beat in flour and salt. Add bananas; blend thoroughly.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into well-greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes on bottom rack or until done.
Can spread with butter; cream cheese frosting.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Stir pudding mix in with fruits and set in refrigerator for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add Cool Whip and mix well. Keep in refrigerator for some time.
Just before serving, you can add nuts and marshmallows or a banana.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Mix sugar, margarine and eggs until fluffy.
Add mashed bananas and flour mixture alternately.
Add nuts.
Grease 2 bread tins well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from tins immediately.

title: barbecued rib sauce
directions: Cook beef, pork ribs or chicken. Then put in baking pan or dish. Pour sauce over. Bake at 300° low heat for 1 hour.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Once cake is baked and cooled, use a wooden spoon handle to poke holes in top (4 across and 8 rows down).
Combine jello packages with 2 cups of boiling water.
Stir well.
Let cool slightly, then pour in holes of cake.
Wash strawberries and remove stems.
Slice 1/2 of the strawberries.
Spread sliced strawberries on top of cake.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Spread Cool Whip on top of cake.
Decorate top with remaining strawberries. Refrigerate for 1 hour and serve.
Store in refrigerator.

title: deer roast
directions: Prepare roast by soaking in ice water overnight. Put roast in baking pan and season with garlic salt. Cut up potatoes, carrots and onion and place around roast. Open can of cream of chicken soup and spread on top. Season with Carls seasoning over all. Bake at 250° for 4 to 5 hours or until meat reaches temperature.

title: chili con carne
directions: Over medium heat, brown ground beef and onion.
Stir in tomato paste,
tomato ketchup and 1 cup water.
Add salt, pepper, chili powder and parsley flakes; mix well.
Pour in kidney beans, including liquid.
Reduce heat.
Put lid on and tilt slightly. Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Best when cooked in iron skillet.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Bring last 6 ingredients to boil.
Boil hard for 1 minute. Pour over cabbage.
Store in tightly closed container in refrigerator and will keep 3 or 4 weeks.

title: mocha fudge brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat and add sugar, cocoa and instant coffee, stirring until well blended.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs slightly.
To eggs, add corn syrup, salt, vanilla and cocoa mixture, blending well.
Add flour, mixing well.

title: holiday breakfast casserole(serves 8)
directions: In a greased pie pan, spread hash brown potatoes.
Brush with melted butter; bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Layer ham, cheese and chilies on crust.
Combine eggs, milk and salt; place on top of ham-cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Place salsa on top when serving.
This does very well when made in large quantities in larger pans.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes, cube and boil. When done, drain and add remaining ingredients. If the mixture seems too thick, add more mayonnaise or a little milk. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until the center is bubbly.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion in oleo.
Beat eggs and mix remaining ingredients.
Pour into onion and bell pepper and mix. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Combine all of the above ingredients in a bowl.
Spoon into a lightly-greased 3 cup casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.
Can sprinkle bread crumbs on top carefully and serve with assorted crackers.

title: tortilla rolls(appetizer)
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and spread onto flat tortillas.
Roll up and then cut into 1-inch sections.
Dip in picante sauce.

title: easy apple dumpling
directions: Prepare apples and butter 4 custard cups large enough to set apples in.
Mix 1/4 cup
of
the
sugar
with the cinnamon. Roll apples
in
cinnamon-sugar.
Place
into
custard
cups. Sprinkle remaining sugar mixture
over
apples.
Stir
together 1/4 cup remaining sugar with the flour, baking powder and salt. Mix egg, butter and vanilla.
Spoon
batter over apples, dividing evenly. Bake at 375° until
crust is golden and apples are cooked,
to 40
minutes.
Serve
with
slightly
sweetened whipped cream or ice cream.

title: spaghetti patties
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except salad oil.
In large skillet over medium heat in 3 tablespoons hot salad oil, drop 3 heaping 1/2 cup mounds of spaghetti mixture.
Using a pancake turner, press each mound into a 4-inch patty.
Fry patty until golden brown, about 7 minutes, turning once.
Remove to platter; keep warm.
Repeat with remaining spaghetti mixture, adding more oil if necessary.
Use as a side dish in place of potatoes or rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: harriet's sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown the chicken lightly in olive oil.
Pour off oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer covered until the chicken is done.
(You might need to add a little water to prevent sticking.) Watch and turn chicken occasionally.

title: basil chicken medley(diabetic recipe)
directions: Heat oil; saute garlic.
Add chicken and cook until done. Remove and keep warm.
Combine zucchini, tomatoes, basil and vinegar; toss to coat.
Add to skillet and stir-fry about 3 to 5 minutes.
Return chicken to skillet and heat.
Serve right away over rice or pasta.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut up chicken into cubes, slice onion.
Brown onion and chicken in margarine; season with salt and pepper and garlic powder.
Mix 1 1/2 cups of rice with 2 cans of soup.
Add in chicken, onion and peas.
Add water as needed to smooth.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: quick meal
directions: Place hamburg and onion in pan.
Add a little water and cook until meat is done.
Place spaghetti in casserole dish.
Add meat mixture and bake in hot oven until hot.
Very quick and very good.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt margarine and chocolate in double boiler; cool.
Mix sugar, flour and eggs.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into paper baking cups. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Yields 24 cupcakes.

title: jello pineapple salad and topping
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and mix with remaining ingredients.
Cover top with miniature marshmallows.
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: apple pan dowdy
directions: Wash, and slice apples into large sauce pan.
Add the sugar, molasses, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and hot water and simmer until soft.
In the meantime, prepare dough by sifting together the dry ingredients,
blending in the shortening and adding the milk. Place the apple mixture in a casserole dish, top with the dough. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until biscuit is brown.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening and margarine.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add	eggs
one
at
a
time,
beating
after each addition. Add
vanilla.
Sift
all
dry ingredients together. Add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel corn(quick and very good)
directions: Boil 10 minutes.
Pour over very large bowl of popcorn.
Stir popcorn mixture until dry, not sticky.

title: mexed up chicken
directions: Layer chips into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add chicken, soups, onion and rest of chips on top.
Cook in oven at 350° until golden brown or substance is bubbling.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Pour into well-greased 11 1/2 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Top with blueberries.
Sprinkle cinnamon crumbs over berries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chicken cashew fried rice
directions: Cut chicken breasts into bite-size pieces and set aside. Stir-fry eggs in 1 tablespoon hot oil in a skillet 3 minutes. Remove eggs from skillet and set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil; add bite-size chicken pieces and stir-fry for 8 minutes.
Add onion and next 5 ingredients; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Whisk soy sauce, sugar and red pepper.
Add to skillet; stir-fry 5 minutes. Stir in eggs and cashews; top with green onions.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mushroom cutlets
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix with chopped mushrooms, onion and salt.
Stir in bread crumbs and cheese.
(If mixture looks too mushy or loose, add a bit more bread crumbs.)
Divide into 6 patties and press into shape.
Fry in butter, not too hot, until outside is crisp and inside moist.
Makes 6 patties.

title: banana split cake
directions: Pack together graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted margarine in the bottom of pan.
Beat eggs, sugar and 3 sticks margarine for 15 minutes.
Pour mixture over crust.
Cover this with sliced bananas.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip, pecans and cherries.
Chill overnight.

title: baked chicken with zucchini
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Skin chicken pieces.
Place in pan.
Sprinkle with salad dressing.
Put under broiler and broil until brown.
Turn pieces over; sprinkle again with salad dressing and broil until brown (approximately 5 minutes each side).
Reduce oven temperature to 400°.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Quarter zucchini the long way and lay across top of chicken.
Cover with foil and return to oven for 30 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and bake 1 1/2 hours more.
Makes very tender chicken with plenty of juices to serve over rice or potatoes.

title: black magic cake
directions: Bake at 350°.
Sift all dry ingredients together into large bowl.
Add eggs and liquids, stir until it is smooth.
(Batter will be thin.)
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes or until done.
Can also be baked in 2 (8-inch) round pans.
Line pans with wax paper for easy removal (not necessary if cake is used from pan).

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions on package using 1 cup cold water and 1 cup hot water.
Cool.
Fold Cool Whip into Jell-O mixture that has cooled.
Blend slowly but well.
Add fresh strawberries and chill until set.
Serves 6.

title: fried rice
directions: Boil rice and let stand in pan while chopping carrots, onion and Spam. Melt the oleo in skillet. Break eggs and scramble. Add rice, carrots and onion, stirring constantly, about 10 minutes. Add green peas and cook until peas are done.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Separate the rolls and use pastry roller to make them larger.
Spread with the chicken mixture.
Roll up and seal.
Dip into the melted butter and the stuffing-nut mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve with warm sauce of:

title: toasted coconut cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except sugar and cinnamon.
Blend at low speed.
Beat at medium speed 3 minutes. Mix sugar and cinnamon and swirl through batter.
Do not mix completely.
Pour batter into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool on rack for 1 hour, then turn cake out of pan to cool completely, then frost with cream cheese icing and toasted coconut. Can be baked in 2 round cake pans.
