title: easy spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; rub butter over bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and sugar; beat until thoroughly mixed.
Sprinkle pie shell with spinach and cheese.
Pour milk mixture over spinach and cheese.
Put a dash of nutmeg and pepper on top.
Bake approximately 40 minutes on lower oven shelf until custard is set and the top is nicely browned.
Serve as a luncheon or main dinner dish.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: korean barbecued chicken wings
directions: Boil chicken for 8 minutes; drain.
Let cool.
Heat barbecue sauce and other ingredients in saucepan.
Let come to simmer. Remove and pour over drained chicken in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine margarine, cocoa, milk and marshmallows; melt in double boiler.
Add powdered sugar and beat well.
Ice cooled cake. Frosting is not gritty.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine crab meat, Old Bay seasoning, salt and pepper.
Stir. Add Worcestershire sauce, egg and mayonnaise.
Stir entire mixture.
Crumble day old bread into separate bowl.
Gradually add to crab mixture, until you can form crab cakes without them breaking apart.
If too much bread crumbs, add more mayonnaise, until consistency is okay to form cakes.
Pan-fry on top of stove until brown or broil in oven broiler until done.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: black forest torte
directions: Mix chocolate and chocolate chunk cookie mix according to package.
Bake in an 8 or 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at temperature on cookie package instructions.
Put first layer on serving plate. Top with 1/2 tub of Cool Whip, then top with about 1/3 of can of cherry pie filling; allow some of both to drip over sides and edges.
Repeat with the other layer, one layer on top of the other.

title: russian salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; set aside.
Blend cream cheese, milk and mayonnaise.
Mash banana; mix with lemon juice.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Stir in the gelatin and chill until set.

title: diabetic strawberry pie
directions: Combine water and cornstarch.
Cook over medium heat until it boils and thickens.
Stir constantly to prevent sticking.
Remove from heat and slowly add gelatin, stirring until well mixed.
Allow to cool 1 hour in refrigerator.
Fold in strawberries and pour into crust.
Top before serving with a spoonful of lite Cool Whip.

title: austrian christmas cookies
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Add nuts.
With a pastry blender, cut in 1/2 cup soft butter to form a soft dough.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Roll out on lightly floured surface 1/8-inch thick. Cut with cookie cutter, place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove when cool.
Cream butter with 10x sugar. Stir in melted chocolate.
Spread between cookies.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into ramekin.
Heat at 350° for 20 minutes or until mixture bubbles.
Serve with Waverly crackers for spreading.
Serves 6. Delicious.

title: sausage cheese grit casserole
directions: Fry and drain sausage; set aside.
Cook grits for 5 minutes in boiling salted water.
Add margarine and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, eggs and sausage.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle paprika on top of casserole.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherry cake
directions: Pour pie filling and pineapple in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top; pour butter over this. Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lowell's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs and flour alternately beating after each addition.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: winter salad
directions: Place cucumbers, tomatoes, onions, green beans, cabbage, carrots and salt in pot.
Cover ingredients with water; let stand 1 hour, then drain.
Add mustard, flour, sugar, vinegar and turmeric to vegetable mixture.
Stir and cook approximately 1/2 hour or more.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
In bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add condensed milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust. Chill 3 hours or until firm.
Top with cherry pie filling (or any fruit pie filling).
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 pie or can be divided into 2 crusts before adding filling.

title: refrigerated coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed. While it's hot, stick with fork (or drinking straw) and pour Eagle Brand milk over cake. Let cool completely. Ice cake with Cool Whip, then sprinkle with coconut. Refrigerate.

title: creme de menthe squares
directions: Bottom Layer:
Combine 1/2 cup butter and cocoa.
Melt and stir until blended.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, egg and vanilla.
Stir in crumbs. Press in glass 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Make plain pastry, roll out as for pie crust and cut into five-inch squares.
Place a peeled, cored apple on each square, filling apple cavity with sugar, cinnamon and a dab of butter. Pull dough up and around to neatly cover fruit.
(Press edges to seal.)
Place in earthen dish or 9 x 12-inch pan in which 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water has been placed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done (lightly brown and bubbly).
Can pierce with fork to see if tender.
Serve warm with cream, milk or plain.
(The dumplings can be prepared in advance, arranged in the pan to wait in the refrigerator until an hour before serving time, then into the oven.)

title: taco burgers
directions: Mix ground meat and salsa. Shape into 4 burgers. Broil 4-inches from heat until well done, turning once, 10 to 12 minutes. Place burgers in pita pockets. Add sour cream, lettuce and tomatoes.

title: coleslaw with tomatoes salad
directions: Remove dark leaves of cabbage; discard.
Rinse cabbage, cut in quarters, removing core.
Shred cabbage finely.
Cut tomatoes lengthwise.
Remove seed and core from pepper.
Cut pepper into thin rings.
Also, cut onion into rings.
In a large bowl, alternate cabbage, onion and pepper until gone.
Sprinkle with 1 cup sugar.
In a small pan, add mustard, 2 teaspoons sugar, salt, vinegar and oil.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour hot on vegetables; toss.
Chill for 3 hours.
Add tomatoes and serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef; drain fat and add sauce and water.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients, excpt noodles.
Pour 1 cup sauce on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer 3 lasagna noodles over sauce.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups sauce and 1/2 of the cheese filling. Repeat layers.
Top with lasagna noodles and remaining sauce. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove foil, bake 10 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Skin and bone chicken. Place broccoli in casserole and top with pieces of chicken. Combine undiluted soup with mayonnaise, milk, croutons, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over chicken and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: deer tenderloin
directions: Rinse tenderloin.
Place on foil covered baking sheet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a small bowl combine onion, barbecue sauce, soy sauce and butter.
Place in microwave for 30 seconds.
Pour over tenderloin and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: parmesan cheese pull-aparts
directions: Melt butter in round pan (8 or 9-inch).
Sprinkle next 4 ingredients on butter.
Shake last 2 ingredients together; layer over seeds.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: sarah's fruit kabobs
directions: Chop fruit into large pieces and place on skewers or kabob sticks.
Serve and enjoy.

title: date pecan balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla and mix.
Add flour and mix.
Blend in pecans and dates.
Roll teaspoons of dough into balls.
Refrigerate balls for 1 to 2 hours.
Bake at 350° on a greased cookie sheet for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; roll in powdered sugar.
Sprinkle again after cooled with powdered sugar. Good!

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour in casserole. Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dijon asparagus chicken salad
directions: In large bowl combine mayo, mustard, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Mix well. Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly. Cover and refrigerate.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt almond bar in microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Add peanut butter.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch or jelly roll pan.
Melt 1 package chocolate chips and spread over almond bar mixture and break into pieces.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Blend peanut butter and Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Add Bisquick mix and vanilla.
Mix together and roll in small balls; roll in sugar to coat.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes (ungreased cookie sheet).
Push Hershey kisses in center of hot cookies and cool.

title: dump cake
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Dump in cherry pie filling and pineapple (including the juice).
On top, dump cake mix (smooth out the lumps).
Pour 1 cup melted butter on top. Bake at 350° for one hour (until golden brown).
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: new england squash pie
directions: Beat all of the ingredients together.
Pour in pastry-lined 9-inch pie pan.
Bake until knife comes out clean.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: festive cake
directions: Let stand for a few minutes before putting on cake.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake mix until done at 350°.
Poke holes all in it.
Mix the cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour this on cake while it is still hot.
Let cake cool, then put coconut on top of Cool Whip.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook celery, onion and broccoli in 2 1/2-quart covered casserole in microwave on High for 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Set aside.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix in casserole dish.
Cook until cheese melts at 400°.

title: chicken pelpell
directions: Heat a hint of oil almost to frying temperature.
Add chicken, garlic and onion and saute 3 to 5 minutes.
Add spices, lemon juice and salt to taste.
Stir for 5 to 8 minutes.
Cooking time should not exceed 15 minutes.
Put on plates and garnish with lemon and olives, cut into juliennes.

title: saturday night special
directions: Make macaroni and cheese dinner according to directions.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: frozen lime salad
directions: In a large bowl combine both cans undrained pineapple, dry lime gelatin, marshmallows and mints.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or until marshmallows begin to melt.
Fold in dessert topping.

title: chocolate snappers
directions: Combine sugar, shortening and egg; beat until creamy.
Stir in corn syrup and melted chocolate.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt; blend in gradually.
Shape into balls, using 1 level tablespoon for each cookie.
Roll balls in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before removing from sheet.
Makes 3 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: squash casserole
directions: Dice squash and boil for 5 minutes.
Dice onion and mix with sour cream.
Drain squash well.
Mix with all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Pour into medium size casserole dish. Spread bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° until the center bubbles, approximately 30 minutes.

title: raisin cake
directions: Combine raisins, sugar, butter and boiling water in a large saucepan; bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Allow to cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve soda in warm water; add to raisin mixture. (Mixture will foam.)
Stir in eggs.
Combine dry ingredients; gradually add to raisin mixture, stirring after each addition. Stir in nuts.
Spoon batter into a lightly greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until cake tests done. Yields one 10-inch cake.

title: michael's crazy cake
directions: Spray 10-inch pan with Pam; set sifter in it.
Into sifter, put flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Sift this into pan.
Make 3 little wells into the dry mixture.
Into one pour salad oil, into the next put vinegar and into the third put vanilla.
Pour 1 cup cold water over all.
Mix with a fork but do not beat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Chop up fine and mix together.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix and serve.
Can be made the day before.

title: touchdown chocolate bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Add egg; mix until well blended.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture.
Press remainder evenly on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
In saucepan, combine sweetened condensed milk and 1 cup chocolate chips.
Over low heat, cook and stir until chips melt and mixture is smooth. Spread evenly over prepared crust.
Add nuts and remaining 1 cup chocolate chips to reserved crumb mixture.
Sprinkle evenly over top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until center is set.
Cool; cut into bars.
Store, covered, at room temperature.

title: sugar-free spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well and keep stored in an airtight container.
To make tea, add 2 teaspoons of mix to a cup of boiling water.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown onion and ground beef together.
Drain.
Add soups, milk and picante sauce to meat mixture.
Let simmer for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour half of mixture into baking dish and top with layer of crumbled up Doritos and cheese.
Add remaining meat mixture and top with chips and then both cheeses.
Bake at 400° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Let set for about 5 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate cake mix
directions: Sift all together dry ingredients and store in dry place. When ready to use, add water and shortening.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and beat again.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: best ever chocolate pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell. Add meringue.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: rhodes sticky buns
directions: Melt the brown sugar and margarine together.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan with margarine.
Spread nuts.
Place frozen rolls in pan and pour mixture of melted butter and brown sugar on top. Sprinkle with dry pudding mix.
Set in cold oven overnight, covered with foil.
Bake next a.m. at 375° for 20 minutes.
Take foil off the last 5 minutes.
Turn out on large platter or cookie sheet (upside down so caramel is on top).
Enjoy!

title: spaghetti salad
directions: The day before making the spaghetti salad, put the Salad Seasons into the Zesty Italian dressing.
Let this set overnight.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Thinly spread crescent rolls out on 2 cookie sheets, prick dough and bake according to package directions until lightly brown (watch carefully, browns quickly).
While crust is baking, drain juice from tomato, cut and crop all vegetables.
Set aside.

title: praline stix
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil (use cookie sheet with sides). Boil sugar and oleo for 2 minutes.
Separate crackers, place in rows on foil.
Pour sauce over crackers and sprinkle with nuts. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.
Peel crackers off foil.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Mix as directed on pudding package.
Pour into Tupperware ice tubs or similar.
Freeze.
Makes 12.

title: sewing club dessert
directions: FIRST LAYER:
Cook 1/2 c. margarine, 1/4 c. sugar and 3 Tbsp. cocoa over low heat until smooth.
Add 1 beaten egg and cook until thick, remove from heat.
Add 2 c. crushed graham crackers, 1 tsp. vanilla and mix well.
Pack into bottom of 11 x 7 inch pan.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute meat and drain fat. Break

tortillas into small pieces. Dilute soup with milk. Add all ingredients, except the cheese, to the browned meat. Mix together and spoon into a casserole. Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: stir-fried tangerine beef
directions: Combine orange juice, soy sauce, cornstarch and ginger.
Toss in steak until well combined.
Heat oil in a large saute pan. Stir-fry beans for 1 minute and add water carefully.
Fry for 3 more minutes and spoon onto a platter.
Add beef mixture to the pan and cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Return green beans with the tangerine sections and water chestnuts to the pan and heat through.
Serve over white rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: yogurt salad dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients and combine with egg in top of a double boiler.
Add milk slowly and stir until smooth and very thick. Remove from heat.
Add honey and vinegar and stir until cool.
Add yogurt gradually, beating constantly to keep mixture smooth.

title: corn meal pastry
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal and seasonings in a bowl.
Cut in shortening thoroughly.
Sprinkle in water 1 tablespoon at a time, mixing until all flour is moistened.
Gather into a ball.
Roll on a lightly floured surface.
Cut slits in the center.
Total cooking time: 50 to 60 minutes.
Recipe yields 6 servings.

title: rhubarb custard
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake as directed.
Put rhubarb on top of cake.
Pour sugar over rhubarb.
Pour unwhipped cream over top of sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in a large pot with 6 quarts of water and 1 teaspoon salt until tender.
Take chicken off bones and cube.
Set aside.
Mix dumplings.
First the flour, the broth, the milk and egg.
Mix well, then roll out on a floured surface until 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into noodles.
Put into boiling broth; cook covered 10 minutes and then cook uncovered for 10 minutes.
Add chicken and simmer until done.

title: welch currant cookies
directions: Stir dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening, then currants.
Beat eggs and milk; add to flour-fruit mixture.
Mix well.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Divide dough in thirds.
Roll out each 1/4-inch thick on floured board.
Cut into round cookies.
Heat griddle slowly. Grease lightly before each baking.
Bake cookies slow until top puffs and turns shiny.
Turn and bake other side until golden. Cool.
Store in a tight container.

title: lemon-peach pickle jello salad
directions: Save juice from pineapple and to 4 tablespoons pickle juice, add enough water to make 1 cup.
Dissolve Jell-O in second cup of hot water.
Add shredded carrots, if desired.

title: jake's hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients together and drop by teaspoons full into hot frying oil.

title: fruit salad
directions: Beat together and add lots of fresh fruits (apples, strawberries, bananas, grapes).

title: kitty litter
directions: Combine cookies and graham crackers and pat 1/2 in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the powdered sugar, butter and eggs.
Drop by teaspoon on top of crumb mixture.
Spread 12 ounces Cool Whip over top.
Add other half of crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats and milk.
Mix all ingredients.
Put into greased muffin tins (1/2 full).
Bake at 325° until done.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Put
all
ingredients
in blender and blend 30 seconds. Pour in	the middle of buttered and floured Pyrex dish.	Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: festive pumpkin bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, water and pumpkin in a mixing bowl; set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, nutmeg and spices.
Add to pumpkin mixture; beat until smooth.
Fold in cherries and pecans.
Spoon into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cut shrimp fine and add all remaining ingredients.
Stir well. Refrigerate for a few hours or overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: dan's cherry delight dessert
directions: Cream the cheese and sugar until smooth; whip cream and fold into cheese mixture.
Top with 1 can of cherry pie filling. Spread over ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Serve with a dash of whipped cream on top.

title: mushroom salad
directions: Wash, chop and cook mushrooms in boiling salted water until mushrooms come to a full boil.
Drain and mix remaining ingredients all together in a large bowl with mushrooms.
Chill overnight before serving.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: pasties(mom's recipe)
directions: Divide pie crust dough into 6 balls; set aside. Peel carrots and potatoes, then dice. Chop celery and onion in small pieces. Mix uncooked hamburger and vegetables together with hands. Add pepper, salt and a little flour; mix well. Roll each ball of dough out and put mixture on half of it. Dot with oleo and a sprinkle of flour. Fold over and seal with a fork. Make 2 small slits on top of crust. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, then at 375° for about 30 minutes. Test to see if done in 45 minutes.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Beat egg white, slowly adding sugar.
Add vanilla.
Stir in nuts and corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Brown sausage.
Drain.
Allow both to cool, then combine.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Top party bread with mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: rich 'n' easy pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker shell or regular pie shell that has been baked and cooled.
Chill several hours. Garnish with whipped cream, sliced star fruit, pecan halves, whole maraschino cherries, etc.
Invite your parish priest in for dessert!!!

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: yummies
directions: Mix ingredients and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done (about 10 minutes).
Check with a toothpick.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat oleo until fluffy in a large bowl; gradually beat the sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each; then add buttermilk and beat.
Add flour slowly, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla, walnuts, dates and candy; mix well, using your hands to mix (if you want).

title: caramel topping
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Cook without stirring, until it forms a soft ball when dropped into water.
Let cool. Then stir the milk into mixture.
If it gets too stiff; add more milk.

title: apricot preserve bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients, including sugar.
Stir in remaining ingredients, just until moistened, not smooth.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
When baked, cover with marshmallows and let melt in oven a little.
Cover with icing.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients in a large bowl, reserving 1/2 of the can of onions.
Pour mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake, uncovered, until brown.

title: cranberry pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce. Add crushed pineapple, orange juice and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch dish. Chill until firm.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaf, then top with a dollop of salad dressing.

title: quick and easy cobbler
directions: Put first 3 ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan and mix well. Then sprinkle yellow cake mix over all the fruit mix.
Then dot completely with oleo, cut in pieces about 1/8-inch thick.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes or until cake is well browned.

title: spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze all of the water out. Melt butter in large saucepan and add spinach. Drain and chop artichokes in large mixing bowl and add sour cream. Mix well. Add cream cheese and stir until mixed. Mix in Parmesan cheese thoroughly. May refrigerate, but best served at room temperature. Dip with bread or tortilla chips.

title: white wine cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add liquids and eggs.
Beat per cake mix directions.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hot fudge sauce for ice cream
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients. Slowly add milk over medium heat; cook and stir until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat and add the margarine and vanilla.
Serve warm over ice cream.

title: best ever fruit pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon together; cut in butter until crumbly. Add cider and mix until moistened. Roll out on floured board. Makes 1 (2 crust) pie.

title: spanish delight
directions: Fry ground beef, onion, bell pepper, garlic, salt, pepper and chili powder in a large skillet.
Add soups and corn.
Simmer for 20 minutes. Add noodles.
Mix in cheese, reserving some for topping. Sprinkle reserved cheese over top. Simmer until topping is melted.
Serves 12.

title: hash brown cheese bake
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: peaches "n" cream pie
directions: Combine marshmallows, orange and lemon juice.
Heat in microwave or over low heat until marshmallows are melted.
Drain peaches if too juicy.
Fold into marshmallow mixture (which has cooled a bit).
Whip cream and fold into peaches.
Pour into pie shell and chill.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Simmer	all
ingredients
except
wings.
Broil chicken wings at 425° for 1 hour.
Turn halfway through cooking.	Pour the simmered sauce over chicken.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix everything except Cool Whip.
Mix well and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Cover with other half of coconut. Makes 2 pies.

title: tuna-cheese spread
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature for about 1 hour. Drain tuna and mash with a fork.
In medium bowl, combine cream cheese, tuna fish and mayonnaise. Add lemon juice, curry and salt. Mix until blended well. Add onions, stirring to blend.
Chill 1 hour.
(Excellent.)

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Core and steam cabbage.
Pull leaves apart.
Combine remaining ingredients except tomatoes.

title: delectable popover recipe
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Generously grease 6 (6 ounce) custard cups.
Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in remaining ingredients just until smooth (do not overbeat).
Fill custard cups about 1/2 full. Bake 20 minutes.
Decrease oven temperature to 350°.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
Immediately remove from cups.
Serve hot, topped with "I Can't Believe It's Not Butter!".
Makes 6 popovers.

title: no-fuss fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, combine milk and chocolate bits.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
Stir in vanilla wafer crumbs and nuts.
Blend until smooth.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer salad
ingredients
as
listed,

making sure that tomatoes are sliced and attractively spaced. Bacon bits should be added just before serving, but the rest of the salad can be covered and refrigerated for several hours or even overnight.

title: smokey brisket (sunday favorite)
directions: Turn crock-pot to high.
Pour in one bottle of liquid smoke. Place brisket in crock-pot.
Add celery salt and enough water to cover.
Cook overnight or all day.

title: chocolate dipped strawberries
directions: In saucepan heat chocolate, margarine and corn syrup over low heat until melted; stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Beat with wooden spoon until cool but still pourable.
Dip fruit halfway into chocolate.
Place on waxed paper.
Refrigerate overnight.
Store in one layer in tightly covered container in refrigerator.

title: chocolate covered cherry cake
directions: Mix and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured in 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not follow cake mix directions.

title: banana muffins
directions: Cream egg, vanilla, sugar and margarine.
Dissolve soda in warm water; add to egg mixture with bananas.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together; add to egg mixture.
Pour into muffin pans, filling 3/4 full.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon supper
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until onion is golden. Blend in salt and flour.
Gradually stir in soup and milk.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Add flaked salmon, peas and lemon juice.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 450 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: french cherry pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla together. Whip the cream and fold in carefully.
Pour into pastry shell and spread evenly; cover with prepared cherry pie filling.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Use almond extract in the cherry pie filling to impart flavor.

title: plain old sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, vanilla and eggs until creamy.
Add baking powder, soda, salt and alternate with milk.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: honey-mustard marinade for pork or chicken
directions: Combine mustard and honey first, then add remaining ingredients.
Marinate meat for 4 hours in refrigerator.
Grill.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute green peppers, onions and celery in 1 stick of butter in a large pot.
Add in the rest of the ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain well.
Set aside.
Mix margarine, Cheez Whiz, soup, rice and broccoli.
Stir until mixed.
Place in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Layer 1:
Crush Oreo's; save out a couple of the cookies to decorate top.
Mix cookies and oleo; press in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill approximately 30 minutes.

title: mrs. leigh's hamburger with barbecue sauce
directions: Handling as little as possible, mix beef, egg, bread crumbs, milk, salt and pepper; shape into balls.
Brown in the oil until brown on both sides.
Mix the tomatoes, sauce, vinegar, chili powder and onion well; pour over hamburger balls and let simmer for 30 minutes.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease and flour bottom of Bundt pan. Pour nuts in bottom of pan. Mix all ingredients together and pour in pan. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes. Top with glaze.

title: 95 house dressing
directions: Mix sour cream and mayonnaise together; then place in blender. Add other ingredients; blend 1 second.

title: caramel layer chocolate squares
directions: In double boiler, on low heat, melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Stir constantly; set aside.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk, salt and nuts.
By hand, stir until dough is thoroughly moistened and stiff.
Press half of dough into pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over baked crust.
Spread caramel mixture over chocolate chips.
Crumble reserved dough over caramel mixture.
Return to oven and bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Refrigerate for about 30 minutes, to set caramel layer.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a buttered casserole dish place chicken.
Add rice, soup, milk, water and onion soup mix.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake 2 hours at 350 degrees.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and heat to boiling.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Pour caramel over popcorn. Mix well.
Spread on greased baking sheets.
Cook in preheated oven at 200° for 1 hour.
Turn every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in covered container.

title: crab quiche
directions: Mix mayonnaise, flour, milk and eggs in bowl.
Stir in crab, cheese and green onions.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cover raisins with water and simmer until soft.
Drain and cool.
Coat chopped nuts with flour and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Heat sauce until very warm and add baking soda.
Add this mixture to creamed sugar and butter.
Add nuts and raisins. Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from oven and let set 10 minutes covered with a tea towel, then turn out onto a plate covered with powdered sugar.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Mix crumbs with butter.
Place, alternating crumbs and oysters, in 3 layers in casserole.
Add liquids. Top with remaining crumbs. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: salad for slaw(cooked mayonnaise)
directions: Stir well over the fire until a thick as custard.
Let it cool and pour over cabbage.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, oats, baking soda, dates and nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and slice. Add celery, sliced eggs and onion. Beat eggs and add sugar, spices and vinegar mixture.
Mix well. Pour egg mixture into hot bacon fat and stir until mixture thickens.
Pour over potatoes and mix lightly. Top with bacon. Serve warm or chilled.

title: pennsylvania dutch pork chops
directions: In large frypan, brown chops in small amount of hot oil. Remove chops from pan.
Drain off excess fat.
Combine sauerkraut and caraway seed in frypan.
Add water.
Place chops on top and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine applesauce, brown sugar and onion.
Pour mixture over chops.
Cover frypan tightly and simmer for 30 to 35 minutes or until chops are tender.

title: blueberry goop
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add pineapple and pie filling to jello.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate; let set.
Then mix cream cheese, sour cream and sugar.
Put on top of jello mixture after it sets.

title: snappy seafood chowder
directions: Saute onion lightly in butter.
Add rest of ingredients including the juices from salmon and lobster.
Over medium heat, bring to a scald, but do not boil.
Let stand 1 hour.
Reheat and serve.

title: madras dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Allow to chill at least 2 hours before using.
This dressing will keep up to 4 days under refrigeration. Serve over salad or use as a dip for raw vegetables.

title: southern style cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and lightly dust with flour a 9 x 13 baking pan. In a mixing bowl, combine milk, eggs, melted shortening and sugar; mix well and add remaining ingredients. Stir well and pour into prepared pan. Spread evenly from center toward corners of pan to provide a more even baking. If corners are left thin, they will overbake and the center will still be doughy. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until golden brown. Allow to cool about 5 minutes. Invert onto serving plate. Cut into squares to serve.

title: spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into 2 rib servings.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Brown in hot fat in heavy skillet.
Lay in baking pan and cover with juice and sauce mixture.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: punch(serves 100)
directions: Combine sugar and 5 cups water to make syrup.
Cool.
Mix juices, 4 quarts water and tea and add to syrup.
Add ginger ale and ice when ready to serve.

title: jalapeno cheese
directions: Using 9 x 13-inch cake pan, spray first with Pam.
Put sliced jalapenos on bottom of pan all over.
Then put grated Cheddar cheese, about 1-inch deep, on top of peppers.
Beat eggs with a fork until foamy.
Spoon eggs evenly over cheese and bake in oven at 350° about 30 minutes or until brown.
Cut into squares right away.
Freezes well!!

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Add milk and beaten egg yolks.
Bake at 350° until done.
Whip egg whites and 4 tablespoons of sugar.
Spread over pie when done and brown.

title: blueberry orange bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Melt butter in boiling water in a small bowl.
Add orange juice and orange rind.
Beat egg with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with orange liquid, beating until smooth.
Fold in blueberries.

title: garlic rice
directions: Put the soup in to a large pot on the stove and add the garlic. Bring this mixture to a boil and then add the stick of butter. Once the butter has dissolved into the soup/garlic mixture, stir in the uncooked rice and the mushrooms. Reduce heat to medium and cover. Let the rice cook for approximately 30 minutes.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Melt butter until hot in medium saucepan.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in cream, Parmesan cheese and yolk.
Pour over hot pasta to coat.

title: shortcut baked beans
directions: In a skillet cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving 1 tablespoon for the drippings.
Drain and crumble bacon.
Set aside.
Cook onion in reserved bacon drippings over medium heat until tender but not brown.
Combine onion, pork and beans, ketchup, brown sugar or molasses, mustard and Worcestershire sauce in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or to desired consistency.
Stir bean mixture; top with bacon. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Or, if preferred, you may cook ingredients in saucepan over low heat about 15 minutes or to desired consistency, stirring frequently.
Top with bacon.
Makes 4 servings.

title: camembert appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove Camembert from wrapping and allow to come to room temperature.
Place Camembert in small tart pan.
Mix together butter and brown sugar.
Spread over top of cheese.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Serve warm with fancy crackers or French bread.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add vanilla and sour cream, then flour with salt, baking powder, soda and spice. Mix to a smooth soft dough.
Chill thoroughly.
Roll 1/3-inch thick and cut into 3 1/4 to 4-inch rounds.
Arrange on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle each cookie with sugar.
Bake at 375° until lightly brown.

title: candy cookies
directions: In saucepan bring to boil the sugar, cocoa, butter and milk. Boil 1 minute.
Then add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well. Add oatmeal and mix well.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: mulled cider
directions: Put everything in large kettle.
Simmer; remove cinnamon and lemon slices.
Keep hot to serve.

title: sacramento fruit bowl
directions: Early in day:
In a medium saucepan over medium heat, cook 2 cups water with sugar, lemon juice, anise seed and salt 15 minutes or until mixture becomes a light syrup; chill.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. Cut circle in top of all potatoes.
Peel off top.
Scoop out potatoes.
Mix in large bowl with electric beater the potatoes, sour cream, margarine, salt, pepper and parsley flakes to taste. Add milk.
Mixture should look like mashed potatoes.
Scoop potato mixture into the potato skins.
Top with cheese.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake until warm and slightly browned at 325°.

title: easy healthy lasagna
directions: Brown turkey; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce to turkey; mix well. Spread thin layer of sauce on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with dry noodles.
On top of noodles, spread 1/2 sauce mix, follow with 1/2 of cheese, another layer of noodles, rest of sauce and all but 1/4 cup of cheese.
Pour boiling water to within 1/2-inch of top of dish.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes. Uncover; bake 20 more minutes.
Top with rest of cheese and let melt.
